William Cattley ( 1788 -- 8 August 1835 ) was an international merchant and horticulturist .
Francis Fauquier ( 1703 -- 3 March 1768 ) was a Lieutenant Governor of Virginia Colony ( in what is today the United States ) , and served as acting governor from 1758 until his death in 1768 .
Eduard Caudella ( 22 May ( or 3 June ) 1841 -- 15 April 1924 ) was a Romanian opera composer , also a violin virtuoso , conductor , teacher and critic .
Abdulkareem Adisa died in a London hospital in February 2005 from injuries sustained in a car accident .
Lorinda Munson Bryant ( 21 March 1855 − 13 December 1933 ) was a writer and educator .
Otto I , Margrave of Hachberg - Sausenberg ( 1302 - -1384 ) was a member of the House of Zähringen .
John Buonarotti Papworth ( London 24 January 1775 -- 16 June 1847 Little Paxton , Huntingdonshire ) was a prolific architect , artist and a founder member of the Royal Institute of British Architects .
Sir John Edward Kynaston Studd , 1st Baronet OBE ( 26 July 1858 -- 14 January 1944 ) , known as `` JEK '' , was a British cricketer , businessman and Lord Mayor of London .
Bernard Lefebvre ( 27 March 1906 - 30 November 1992 ) , known as Ellebé , was a French photographer .
Elizabeth Russell , Duchess of Bedford VA ( née Sackville - West ; 23 September 1818 -- 22 April 1897 ) was born the daughter of the 5th Earl De La Warr and his wife Lady Elizabeth Sackville .
Clemens Blume ( 31 January 1862 Billerbeck - 1932 ) was a Jesuit hymnologist .
Sengalipuram Anantarama Dikshitar ( Tamil : செங்களிபுரம் அனந்தராம தீட்சிதர் ; 2 August 1903 -- 30 October 1969 ) was a Śrauti scholar and also was a great exponent of the art of upanyasas ( discourses ) on various subjects in Hinduism .
Rawdon Briggs Lee ( 9 July 1845 -- 29 February 1908 ) was an English dog breeder and writer on dogs .
Manasseh Dawes ( died 1829 ) was an English barrister and miscellaneous writer .
Odhise Paskali ( 22 December 1903 -- 13 September 1985 ) is one of the most acclaimed Albanian sculptors .
Eleanor Hudson , known professionally as Erlund Hudson , ( 18 February 1912 - 9 March 2011 ) , was a watercolourist , etcher and designer best known for her depictions of women at work during the Second World War and her post - war paintings of ballet dancers .
Sir William Parkyns or Perkins ( 1649?--1696 ) was an English lawyer and Jacobite conspirator , executed for high treason .
John Elphinstone , 2nd Lord Balmerino ( died 1649 ) was a Scottish aristocrat , convicted in a celebrated trial of the 1630s which became a crux of the religious issue of the time .
Aderald ( died 1004 ) was a canon and archdeacon of Troyes , France , when he led a pilgrimage to the Holy Land .
Frederic Crowninshield ( 1845 - -1918 ) was an American artist and author .
Philip Frederick Mayer ( 1 April 1781 , in New York City - 16 April 1858 , in Philadelphia ) was a United States Lutheran clergyman .
Maximilian of Hesse - Kassel ( 28 May 1689 , Marburg -- 8 May 1753 , Kassel ) was a prince of Hesse - Kassel and a Generalfeldzeugmeister , Generalfeldmarschall and finally Reichsgeneralfeldmarschall in the army of the Holy Roman Empire .
Emicho I , Count of Nassau - Hadamar ( also known as Emich , first mentioned in 1289 , died on 7 June 1334 ) , was the second son of Count Otto I of Nassau and his wife Agnes ( d. 1303 ) , the daughter of Count Emich IV of Leiningen - Landeck .
Thornton Chase died on 30 September 1912 in Los Angeles , of complications following unsuccessful surgery .
Ruth Pine Furniss ( 1893 -- 1957 ) , was an American writer who published several short stories and novels .
Carl Wilhelm Hugo Schnars - Alquist ( 29 October 1855 - 20 August 1939 ) was a German art collector and painter of maritime scenes .
Andreas Tscherning ( 18 November 1611 -- 27 September 1659 ) was a German poet , hymn writer and literary theorist in the tradition of Martin Opitz .
Emily Farmer ( 25 July 1826 , London - 8 May 1905 , Portchester , Hampshire ) was an English watercolour painter .
Rebecca Cox Jackson ( 1795 - -1871 ) was an African - American free woman , best known for her religious activism and for her autobiography .
Muiredach mac Ainbcellaig was king of the Cenél Loairn , and of Dál Riata ( modern western Scotland ) , from about 733 until 736 .
Franz Burri ( 1901 - -1987 ) was a Swiss political figure who , from his base in Germany , became the leading disseminater of Nazi propaganda in the country .
Kiowa Costonie led an adventurous , busy life helping those in need until his death in 1971 .
Magnus I , Duke of Mecklenburg ( 1345 -- 1 September 1384 ) was Duke of Mecklenburg from 1383 until his death .
Jack Donahue ( 1804 -- 1 September 1830 ) was a bushranger in Australia between 1825 and 1830 .
Harry Hutchens ( born Henry Hutchins , 1858 -- 2 January 1939 ) was a professional British runner .
Kate Mason Rowland ( 22 June 1840 - -28 June 1916 ) was an American author , historian , genealogist , biographer , editor and historic preservationist .
Henry Barley or Barlee ( 1487 -- 12 November 1529 ) , of Albury , Hertfordshire , was a Member of Parliament during the Tudor period .
Samuel James Kitson ( 1848 - -1906 ) was a fine arts sculptor active in the United States from about 1876 to 1906 .
Robert Logan Jack ( 16 September 1845 -- 6 November 1921 ) was Queensland government geologist for twenty years .
Mir Ghaus Bakhsh Bizenjo died on 11 August 1989 .
Pyotr Romanovich Bagration ( Russian : Пётр Рома́нович Багратио́н ; 24 September 1818 -- 17 January 1876 ) , the son of general Prince Roman Bagration , was a Russian - Georgian statesman , general and scientist who invented the first dry galvanic cell .
Jiang Wei ( 202 - -264 ) , courtesy name Boyue , was a military general and regent of the state of Shu Han during the Three Kingdoms period .
Johann Zwelfer ( 1618 - -1668 ) was a German chemist , pharmacist and physician .
Jacob ben Ephraim ( died in Lublin 1648 ) was a Polish rabbi .
Lebo Mathosa ( 17 July 1977 - 23 October 2006 ) was a popular South African kwaito singer .
Francesco Magini ( Fano , between 1668 and 1670 -- 1714 ) was a minor Italian composer active in Rome in the first decade of the eighteenth century .
Admiral Sir Richard Spry ( 1715 - - 25 November 1775 ) was a Royal Navy officer who served as Commander - in - Chief , North American Station .
Angelo Pietrasanta ( 1837 --1876 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of historical canvases .
Ieng Thirith ( née Khieu ; Khmer : អៀង ធីរិទ្ធ ; 10 March 1932 -- 22 August 2015 ) was an influential figure in the Khmer Rouge , although she was neither a member of the Khmer Rouge Standing Committee nor of the Central Committee .
John Henry Dearle or J. H. Dearle ( London 1859 -- 15 January 1932 ) was a British textile and stained - glass designer trained by the artist and craftsman William Morris who was much influenced by the Pre - Raphaelite Brotherhood .
Kalle Nämdeman ( 1883 - -1945 ) was the stage name of Karl Gustafsson , a Swedish songwriter , performer and recording artist .
Thomas Gatacre ( by 1533 - 1593 ) was an English politician and cleric .
Edgar Smith Wigg ( 7 June 1818 -- 15 October 1899 ) was an Adelaide , South Australian bookseller and stationer , founder of the firm E. S. Wigg and Son .
Marc Mortier ( 9 December 1948 -- 3 May 2004 ) was CEO of Flanders Expo from its foundation in 1986 to 2002 .
Sam McAughtry ( 24 March 1921 -- 28 March 2014 ) was a Northern Irish writer and broadcaster .
Joff Ellen ( 20 May 1915 -- 30 December 1999 ) ( real name Raymond Charles Ellen ) was an Australian entertainer , actor and comedian .
John Hicks Adams ( 1820 - -1878 ) was an American 49er of the California Gold Rush , and Sheriff of Santa Clara County between February 6 , 1864 and 1870 , then again between 1871 and 1875 .
Nyimpine Chissano ( 1970 -- 19 November 2007 ) was the eldest son of former Mozambican president Joaquim Chissano .
Thomas Edward Cliffe Leslie ( 21 June 1825 -- 27 January 1882 ) was an Irish jurist and economist .
Wolfgang Paul ( 10 August 1913 -- 7 December 1993 ) was a German physicist , who co - developed the non - magnetic quadrupole mass filter which laid the foundation for what we now call an ion trap .
Hans von Obstfelder ( 6 September 1886 -- 20 December 1976 ) was a German general of infantry , serving during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves and Swords awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership .
Charlie Longhurst ( 8 April 1911 -- 12 February 1970 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Bernie Treweek ( 27 September 1914 -- 27 November 1957 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thomas Marsham ( died 1819 ) was an English entomologist , specializing on beetles .
Matthew Baird ( 1817 - -1877 ) was one of the early partners in the Baldwin Locomotive Works .
Robert Hewitt Barker ( 1887 -- 14 February 1961 ) was a British textile mill owner .
Cairell mac Muiredaig Muinderg ( died 532 ) also Cairell Coscrach ( `` victorious '' ) was a king of Ulaid from the Dal Fiatach .
Hubert Leitgeb ( 31 October 1965 -- 4 February 2012 ) was an Italian biathlete .
Frank Kennedy ( 31 July 1920 -- 27 December 1990 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Joseph Sedgwick , CC , QC ( 24 November 1898 -- 27 December 1981 ) was a Canadian lawyer .
Flying Childers stood as a private stallion at the Duke 's Chatsworth estate in Derbyshire , until his death in 1741 at age 26 .
Lila Meade Valentine ( February 4 , 1865 -- July 14 , 1921 ) was an American educational reformer and a participant in the woman 's suffrage movement .
Derek Austin ( 11 August 1921 -- 22 May 2001 ) was a librarian and an author .
Hugh Merewether ( 20 May 1924 in South Africa -- 13 September 2006 ) was a British test pilot who pioneered the vertical and short take - off and landing ( V / STOL ) techniques that led to the development of the Hawker Siddeley Harrier .
Richard St John Tyrwhitt ( 1827 - -1895 ) was an English cleric and academic , known as a writer on art .
Dinos Iliopoulos ( Greek : Ντίνος Ηλιόπουλος ; 12 June 1915 -- 6 June 2001 ) was a Greek actor .
Joe Oakley ( 28 January 1914 -- 8 December 1980 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Erik Kristen - Johanssen ( 13 March 1901 -- 30 January 1976 ) was a Norwegian jurist and theatre director .
Marietta Pallis ( 1882 - -1963 ) was a Greek - Briton ecologist and botanical artist .
Basil Collier ( 1908 -- 1983 ) , full name John Basil Collier , was a British author of books of military history , particularly military aviation and World War II , and military and political strategy .
Sicco Polenton ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈsikko polenˈtɔn ; -ton ) ; 1375 - -1447 ) was an Italian jurist , Neolatin author , and Renaissance humanist .
When he died in Luxembourg City on 5 February 1975 , Tissen left an extensive collection of paintings and other artistic artifacts , most of which are presented in the commemorative book Rétrospective Foni Tissen 100 Joer .
Lucius Vipstanus Claudius Poplicola Messalla ( c. 105 -- aft . 140 ) was a sal .
Peter Hollander Ridder ( 1608 - -1692 ) was the governor of the Swedish colony of New Sweden from 1640 until 1643 .
Saint Margaret of Fontana ( 1440 - 1513 ) was a Dominican of the Third Order and is a Roman Catholic saint .
Christian Eric Fahlcrantz , ( 30 August 1780 -- 6 August 1866 ) , Swedish author , was born at Stora Tuna in Dalarna .
Bridget Barrett ( died 10 September 1845 ) was an Irish murder victim .
Henry Howard , 2nd Earl of Effingham DL ( 23 August 1806 -- 5 February 1889 ) , styled Lord Howard of Effingham from 1837 to 1845 , was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
Carl Axel Løvenskiold ( 13 January 1912 -- 28 September 1980 ) was a Norwegian landowner and painter .
Hugh Exton ( 26 March 1864 Western Cape - 1955 ) was a South African self - taught photographer noted for creating more than 23000 glass slides during his career spanning 1892 to 1945 , and preserved at the Hugh Exton Photographic Museum , a former Dutch Reformed church built in Pietersburg in the 1890s .
Roustam Raza , also known as Roustan or Rustam ( 1783 -- 7 December 1845 ) , was Napoleon 's mamluk bodyguard .
Josiah Merritt ( ? - 1882 ) , sometimes known as `` Uncle Si '' was an early pioneer of the Pacific Northwest .
Philip Edward MacKenzie , P. E. MacKenzie ( January 9 , 1872 -- May 1946 ) , joined the firm McCraney & Hutchinson in 1909 as barrister which then became , McCraney , McKenzie and Hutchinson .
Sir Peter Manwood ( 1571 -- 1625 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1589 and 1621 .
Zeferino Nandayapa ( born 26 August 1931 , Copainalá -- died 28 December 2010 , Tlalnepantla ) was a Mexican folk and classical marimba player .
Ole Borge ( 4 May 1916 -- 24 May 1995 ) was a Norwegian jurist and resistance member during World War II . He was born in Kristiania .
Hugh Stowell Brown ( 10 August 1823 -- 24 February 1886 ) was a Manx Christian minister and renowned preacher .
Mary Crawford Fraser ( April 8 , 1851 -- 1922 ) , usually known as Mrs. Hugh Fraser , was a writer noted for her various memoirs and historical novels .
General Sir Henry Finnis KCB , MC ( 21 April 1890 -- 31 May 1945 ) was a British officer in the Indian Army .
Frederick George Scott ( 7 April 1861 -- 19 January 1944 ) was a Canadian poet and author , known as the Poet of the Laurentians .
Wilfred Barber , known as Wilf Barber ( 18 April 1901 -- 10 September 1968 ) , was a professional first - class cricketer who played for Yorkshire County Cricket Club from 1926 to 1947 .
Trần Văn Cẩn ( Kiến An , now part of Hải Phòng city , 13 August 1910 -- 1994 ) was a Vietnamese painter .
Andreas Hofgaard Winsnes ( 25 October 1889 -- 9 July 1972 ) was a Norwegian literary historian and historian of ideas .
Arsène Herbinier ( 1869 -- before 1955 Paris ) was a French lithograph artist .
Rudolf F. Haffenreffer III ( c. 1902 -- April 28 , 1991 ) was a Rhode Island industrialist and philanthropist .
Ján Móry ( or Johann Mory ) ( 10 July 1892 -- 5 May 1978 ) was a Slovak composer and pedagogue also known under pseudonym H. Tschirmer .
Nathaniel Clements , 2nd Earl of Leitrim , KP PC ( Ire ) ( 9 May 1768 -- 31 December 1854 ) , styled The Honourable from 1783 to 1795 , and then Viscount Clements to 1804 , was an Irish nobleman and politician .
Libero Liberati ( 20 September 1926 -- 5 March 1962 ) was an Italian motorcycle racer and the 1957 500cc Grand Prix World Champion .
Albert Beresford Horsley CBE , QC ( 2 January 1880 -- 19 November 1923 ) was an English cricketer .
Lina Franziska Fehrmann ( born in Dresden on 11 October 1900 ; died 10 June 1950 ) was an artist model generally called Fränzi and associated to Die Brücke .
Khem Shahani died on 6 July 2001 while on a speaking tour in Sicily ( Italy ) .
Muriel Stuart ( 1885 , Norbury , South London -- 18 December 1967 ) , born Muriel Stuart Irwin , was a poet , the daughter of a Scottish barrister .
Lewis Morris Wilkins ( ca 1768 -- January 3 , 1848 ) was a lawyer , judge and political figure in Nova Scotia .
Pyotr Yegorovich Chistyakov ( 1790 -- 21 January 1862 ) was a Russian explorer , chief manager of the Russian - American Company and admiral .
Pierre - Antoine Bellangé ( 1757 - -1827 ) was a French ébéniste ( cabinetmaker ) working in Paris .
Liu Qubei ( Chinese : 劉去卑 ; pinyin : Liú Qùbēi ) , ( died 272 ) was a Tiefu Hun ( Ch . Xiongnu ) chieftain from 260 to 272 .
Safi Lakhnavi ( Urdu : صفی لکھنوی , Hindi : सफ़ी लखनवी pronunciation ) , born Syed Ali Naqi Zaidi ( January 2 , 1862 - -1950 ) , was a prominent Urdu poet .

Lady Clare Rendlesham ( died 1987 ) was a British fashion editor and boutique manager .
John Frederick Smith ( 1806 - 1890 ) was a popular English novelist , who has been called `` England 's most popular novelist of the mid - nineteenth century '' .
Charles Bathurst , 1st Viscount Bledisloe GCMG KBE PC ( 21 September 1867 -- 3 July 1958 ) , was a British Conservative politician and colonial governor .

Mary Lacy ( born circa 1740 , died 1801 ) was a British sailor , shipwright and memoirist .
Alexander John Goodrum ( 1960 - -2002 ) was an internationally known African - American transgender civil rights activist , writer , and educator .
Oda of Metz ( ca . 910 -- 10 Apr 963 ) was a German noblewoman .
Archibald Henderson died suddenly on 6 January 1859 .
Moore Gwillim ( died 1611 ) , of Monmouth and Rockfield , Monmouthshire , was a Welsh politician .
M. V. Subbaiah Naidu ( 1896 - 21 July 1962 ) was an Indian stage artiste in the silent movies era .
Roland Vila ( 6 May 1949 -- 15 May 1998 ) was a Catalan / French author based in Sweden .
Nihat Nikerel ( 05 February 1950 -- 26 September 2009 ) was a Turkish actor , best known for his role in the crime drama series Kurtlar Vadisi .
Dhimiter Çani ( 1904 , Korçë , Manastir Vilayet , Ottoman Empire -- 1990 ) was an Albanian sculptor .
Miervaldis Birze ( born Augusts Miervaldis Bērziņš ; 21 March 1921 -- 6 July 2000 ) was a Latvian writer , publicist , physician and Holocaust survivor .
Neddy Lohan , Captain of Irish Whiteboys , died in 1820 .
Thomas Penswick ( 1772 - -1836 ) was an English Roman Catholic bishop who served as the Vicar Apostolic of the Northern District from 1831 to 1836 .
Jonas Zeuner ( Kassel 1727 - -1814 ) , was an artist and engraver .
Stafford Allen ( 1806 -- 14 October 1889 ) was a British industrialist , abolitionist , Quaker and philanthropist .
John H. Mercer ( Cheltenham , England , 19 October 1922 -- Columbus , Ohio 3 July 1987 ) was a glaciologist , chiefly known for his theoretical work on , and field studies of Antarctic ice streams , especially in the Transantarctic Mountains and in West Antarctica .
Giorgio Vladagni ( Latin : Georgius Vladagnus , Albanian : Gjergj Vladanji , Serbo - Croatian : Đorđe Vladanji ; 1712 - 1765 ) was an Albanian prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .

Sir William Button , 1st Baronet ( 1584 -- 16 January 1655 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1629 .
Pino Mlakar ( pronunciation ) ( 2 March 1907 -- 30 September 2006 ) was a Slovenian ballet dancer , choreographer , and teacher .
Cajetan von Textor ( 28 December 1782 -- 7 August 1860 ) was a German surgeon born in the Ebersberg district of Upper Bavaria .
Basil Milovsoroff ( 1906 - 1992 ) was an accomplished Russian - American puppeteer .
Andrew Fountaine ( 7 December 1918 -- 14 September 1997 ) was an activist involved in the British far right .
Fred Knee ( 1868 - 1914 ) was a British trade unionist and socialist politician .
Jorge del Moral Ugarte ( Mexico City , 23 December 1900 - 1941 ) was a Mexican concert pianist and songwriter .
Clay Huffman ( 1957 - -2001 ) was a multi - medium artist , most well known for his vibrant , multicolored serigraphs of local roadside architecture .

Aimée Julie Cheron ( née Jovin in Paris , 26 April 1821 -- c. 1890 ) was a French miniature painter .

William de Cornhill ( or William of Cornhill ; died 1223 ) was a medieval Bishop of Coventry .

Anna Loginova ( Russian : Анна Логинова , 3 September 1978 -- 27 January 2008 ) was a Russian fashion model and later a trained bodyguard .
Sayyed Gholamreza Rouhani alias Ajjeneh ( Persian : غلامرضا روحانی‎ ) 17 May 1897 to 29 August 1985 , was an Iranian humorous poet .
Reimond Stijns ( Mullem , 10 May 1850 -- Sint - Jans - Molenbeek , 12 December 1905 ) was a Belgian writer .
José García Narezo ( November 26 , 1922 -- July 8 , 1994 ) was a Mexican painter and a founding member of the Salón de la Plástica Mexicana .
Sancho Garcés III ( Basque : Antso III.a Gartzez ; c. 990 -- 18 October 1035 ) , also known as Sancho III of Pamplona and nicknamed the Great , was King of Pamplona and Count of Aragon from 1004 until his death in 1035 .
Richard Mique ( French pronunciation : ​(ʁiʃaːʁ mik ) ) ( 18 September 1728 -- 8 July 1794 ) was a neoclassical French architect born in Lorraine .
Blessed James Salomoni ( Italian : Giacomo Salomoni ; 1231 - -1314 ) was an Italian Dominican priest , ascetic , and mystic who is venerated as a beatus by the Catholic Church .
Thomas Shelmerdine ( 1845 - -1921 ) was an English architect who was appointed to the post of City Surveyor of Liverpool at the age of 26 .
Camill Heller ( 26 September 1823 -- 25 February 1917 ) was a zoologist and anatomist .
Hugues Cosnier was a French engineer who conceived of the Briare Canal who was born in Tours , 1573 , and died in 1629 .
Joseph Stirling Coyne ( 1803 - -1868 ) was a humorist and satirist in the tradition of Jonathan Swift and Alexander Pope .
Major William M. Jones ( b. Bear River , Nova Scotia , 1895 - d. Ontario , 1969 ) was a soldier of WW1 and WW2 who served with distinction with the Yugoslav Partisans .
Edward Bruce , 1st Lord Kinloss PC ( 1548 -- 14 January 1611 ) was a Scottish lawyer and judge .
Torbjørn Sikkeland ( 3 August 1923 -- 7 November 2014 ) was a Norwegian chemist , nuclear physicist and radiation biophysicist .
Daniele Seccarecci ( 10 June 1980 -- 3 September 2013 ) was an Italian bodybuilder .
Manoug Parikian ( 15 September 1920 -- 24 December 1987 ) was a British concert violinist and violin professor of Armenian descent .
Mercy Hunter MBE ( 22 January 1910 -- 20 July 1989 ) was a Northern Irish artist , calligrapher and teacher .
Swaminarayan ( IAST : Svāmīnārāyaṇa , 3 April 1781 -- 1 June 1830 ) , also known as Sahajanand Swami , is the central figure in a modern sect of Hinduism known as the Swaminarayan Hinduism .
Al - Mu'tadid I ( Arabic : المعتضد بالله‎ ) was an Abbasid Caliph of Cairo , Egypt for the Mamluk Sultans between 1352 and 1362 .
Deva Raya II ( r. 1425 - -1446 CE ) was an emperor of the Vijayanagara Empire .
Park Won - jong ( korean:박원종;朴元宗,1467 - 1510 ) was a Korean Joseon Dynastys politician and soldier , served as Prime Minister or Chief State Councillor from 1506 to 1510 .
Menahem Gnessin ( 1882 - -1952 ) was an early Jewish actor and Hebrew language instructor who created the Amateur Dramatic Arts Company in 1907 for presentation of plays in Hebrew .
Satyen Sen ( Bengali : সত্যেন সেন ) , ( 1907 - 1981 ) , a historian of Bengali literature from Bangladesh .
Sergio Ciani ( 7 September 1935 -- 5 September 2015 ) , best known as Alan Steel , was an Italian bodybuilder and actor .
Gareth Hughes ( 23 August 1894 -- 1 October 1965 ) was a Welsh stage and silent screen actor .

Duncan McDuffie ( September 24 , 1877 -- 1951 ) was a real estate developer , conservationist , and mountaineer based in Berkeley , California , USA .
Françoise Demulder ( 9 June 1947 -- 3 September 2008 ) was a French war photographer who in 1976 became the first woman to win the prestigious World Press Photo of the Year award .
Richard Partridge FRS , FRCS ( 19 January 1805 ; Ross - on - Wye , Herefordshire -- 25 March 1873 ; London ) was a British surgeon .
Zev Wolfson ( 27 September 1928 -- 13 August 2012 ) was an American real estate businessman and philanthropist , especially notable among the Haredi community .
Léopold Jorédié ( 1947 -- 8 September 2013 ) was a former Vice - President of the Government of New Caledonia under Jean Lèques .
Sir Edward Dering , 6th Baronet ( 28 September 1732 -- 8 December 1798 ) , was the British Member of Parliament for New Romney .
Cui Riyong 崔日用 ( 673 - -722 ) , formally Duke Zhao of Qi 齊昭公 , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty , briefly serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Ruizong .
Knud Jessen ( 29 November 1884 -- 14 April 1971 ) was a Danish botanist and quaternary geologist .
Clara Haskil ( 7 January 1895 - 7 December 1960 ) was a Romanian classical pianist , renowned as an interpreter of the classical and early romantic repertoire .
Nancy Tyson Burbidge AO ( 5 August 1912 -- 4 March 1977 ) was an Australian systemic botanist , conservationist and herbarium curator .
Manuel Canaveris ( 1787 - -1830 ) was an Argentine army officer , Lieutenant in the Regiment of Patricians .
Jack Cusack ( November 17 , 1890 -- 1973 ) was one of the prominent early figures in professional football in Ohio .
Khachatur Avetisyan ( 1926 - -1996 ) ( Armenian : Խաչատուր Ավետիսյան , Xačatur Avetisyan ; alternate transliterations include Avetisian or Avetissian ) was an influential Armenian composer .
Harry Wallis Kew ( 1868 - 1948 ) was an amateur English zoologist .
Jean - Baptiste Madou ( 3 February 1796 -- 31 March 1877 ) , was a Belgian painter and lithographer .
Paulus Traudenius ( born Gouda , died 9 July 1643 , Batavia , Dutch East Indies ) was the Dutch Governor of Formosa from 1640 to 1643 .
Henry Fitz - Ailwin de Londonestone ( ca . 1135 -- 19 September 1212 ) was the first Mayor of London ( later known as Lord Mayor of London from 1347 and then Lord Mayor of the City of London from 2006 ) .
Battista Antonelli ( or Bautista ) ( 1547 - -1616 ) was a military engineer from a prestigious Italian family of military engineers in the service of the Habsburg monarchs of Austria and Spain .
Auguste Jean François Grenier ( 22 September 1814 , Andelys - 13 July 1890 , Bagnères ) was a French doctor and entomologist .
Reham Al - Farra of Jordan was 29 years old when she died along with other United Nations staff members in the terrorist Canal Hotel bombing of the UN Headquarters in Baghdad , Iraq on 19 August 2003 .
Gernot Zippe PhD ( November 1917 -- 7 May 2008 ) was an Austrian - German mechanical engineer who is widely credited with leading the team which developed the Zippe - type centrifuge , a centrifuge machine for the collection of Uranium-235 .
Father Pablo Gazzarri was an ordained priest who worked in the Parish of Nuestra Señora del Carmen de Villa Urquiza ( Buenos Aires ) who was abducted on November 27 , 1976 ; being the fifth anniversary of his ordination .
Tito Azzolini ( Bologna , June , 1837-December 8 , 1907 ) was an Italian architect , active mostly in or near Bologna .
Sir John Colleton , 1st Baronet ( 1608 - -1666 ) served Charles I during the English Civil War .
Adelle August ( 12 February 1934 -- 24 April 2005 ) , born Adele M. Slaybough , was an American movie actress .
Axel Hamberg ( 1863 - -1933 ) was a Swedish mineralogist , geographer , explorer and professor in geography at the University of Uppsala 1907 - 1928 .
Stéphanie Caroline Anne Syms , Lady Edward FitzGerald ( c. 1773 -- 9 November 1831 ) was the wife of Lord Edward FitzGerald , the radical revolutionary and leading United Irishman , and was herself an enthusiastic supporter of Irish independence , scarcely less celebrated at the time than Lord Edward himself .
Phineas Lyman ( 1716 - -1774 ) was a colonial American soldier known for his service in the provincial British army of the French and Indian War .
Marjorie Muir Worthington ( 1900- February 17 , 1976 ) was an American author of novels and short stories .
Francis M. Nickell ( 1843 - -1913 ) was a contractor , a builder and a member of the Los Angeles City Council in the 1890s .
Sallie - Anne Huckstepp ( 12 December 1954 -- 6 February 1986 ) was an Australian prostitute and heroin addict who became a writer and whistleblower .
Ted Esposito ( 23 May 1908 - 1 May 1985 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Edward Stuart Cardinal Dyke ( 24 August 1872 -- 21 January 1915 ) was a prominent naturalist , photographer , and botanical explorer in South Africa during the late 19th to early 20th century .
Ralph Howard , 1st Viscount Wicklow PC ( I ) ( 1726 -- 26 June 1786 ) was an Irish politician and nobleman .
At the Synod of Whitby in 664 , Alhfrith was the chief supporter of Wilfrid .
William Duff , 1st Earl Fife ( 1696 -- 30 September 1763 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
James Alexander , 4th Earl of Caledon KP , DL ( 11 July 1846 -- 27 April 1898 ) was a soldier and politician and the son of James Du Pre Alexander , 3rd Earl of Caledon and Lady Jane Grimston , styled Viscount Alexander until 1855 .
Karolina Kózka ( 2 August 1898 -- 18 November 1914 ) was a Polish teenager who has been beatified as a virgin - martyr by the Roman Catholic Church .
Charles Pelham Villiers ( 3 January 1802 -- 16 January 1898 ) was a British lawyer and politician from the Villiers family who sat in the House of Commons from 1835 to 1898 , making him the longest - serving Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
William Burnes or William Burness ( 11 November 1721 -- 13 February 1784 ) , the father of Robert Burns the poet , was born at either Upper Kinmonth or Clochnahill Farm , Dunnottar , Kincardineshire , and trained as a gardener at Inverugie Castle , Aberdeenshire , before moving to Ayrshire and becomimg a tenant farmer .
Maud of Lancaster , Countess of Ulster ( c. 1310 -- 5 May 1377 ) was an English noblewoman and the wife of William Donn de Burgh , 3rd Earl of Ulster .
Peter Safar ( 12 April 1924 -- 2 August 2003 ) was an Austrian physician of Czech descent .
William Vasey Houghton MLC ( 3 January 1921 - -11 January 2001 ) , better known as Vasey Houghton , was an Australian politician , grazier , and conservationist .
Beatrice Gubbins ( 1878 - -1944 ) was an Irish artist in watercolour .
William Jack Grisman ( 30 August 1914 -- 6 April 1944 ) , known as Jack , was a British Vickers Wellington bomber crew member who was taken prisoner during the Second World War .
Sid Colin ( 1920 -- 1989 ) was an English screenwriter , working for both television and the cinema .
Rev Dr David Welsh DD FRSE ( 11 December 1793 -- 24 April 1845 ) was a Scottish divine and academic .
Sir John Hannah Gordon ( 26 July 1850 -- 23 December 1923 ) was a Scottish - Australian politician and judge .
Sirima ( 14 February 1964 - 7 December 1989 ) was a singer who sang in English .
Harikesanallur Muthiah Bhagavatar ( 15 November 1877 -- 30 June 1945 ) , commonly known as Muthiah Bhagavatar , is one of Carnatic classical music 's famous twentieth - century composers .
Philip Gray ( 1821 -- 28 February 1857 ) was an Irish republican , revolutionary and a member of the Irish Confederation .
Carl Johan Adlercreutz ( 27 April 1757 -- 21 August 1815 ) was a Swedish general and statesman , born in Borgå , Finland on family estates .
Patrick Lindsay , 6th Lord Lindsay of the Byres , ( 1521 - -1589 ) , Scottish courtier and Confederate lord .
Cecilia Glaisher ( 20 April 1828 -- 28 December 1892 ) was an English amateur photographer , artist , illustrator and print - maker , working in the 1850s world of Victorian science and natural history .
Johanna Klink died on either 19 or 20 February 2015 , at age 112 years and 33 or 34 days .
Ivor Spencer , MBE ( 20 November 1924 -- 10 January 2009 ) was the founder of the Ivor Spencer International School for Butlers and the Professional School for Toastmasters .
Fred Lind died on 28 February 1976 , aged 71 at Bateau Bay , New South Wales .
Robert Carleton Smith ( b. 19 Feb 1908 ; d. 28 March 1984 Centre Island , New York ) Smith was the director of the National Arts Foundation and organized the International Awards Foundation to establish awards in fields not covered by the Nobel Prize .
Šimun Kožičić Benja ( born ca . 1460 in Zadar , died 1536 in Zadar ) was a Croatian nobleman , the bishop of Modruš and the founder of the Glagolitic printing house in Rijeka .
Jacob Marschak ( 23 July 1898 -- 27 July 1977 ) was a Ukrainian - American economist , known as `` the Father of Econometrics '' .
Rob Foster ( 25 March 1947 -- 12 March 2014 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
( Walter ) Trevelyan Thomson ( 30 April 1875 -- 8 February 1928 ) was a British Liberal Member of Parliament , iron and steel merchant and soldier .
Johnny Wardle ( 8 January 1923 -- 23 July 1985 ) was an English spin bowler of post - war cricket .
Hubert Stanley Middleton ( 11 May 1890 - -13 August 1959 ) was a cathedral organist , who served at Truro Cathedral and Ely Cathedral before an appointment to Trinity College , Cambridge .
Korbinian Brodmann ( 17 November 1868 -- 22 August 1918 ) was a German neurologist who became famous for his definition of the cerebral cortex into 52 distinct regions from their cytoarchitectonic ( histological ) characteristics , known as Brodmann areas .
Awaji Nichiken ( 淡路日賢 , 1243 - -1338 ) was a disciple of Nichiren who studied under Nichigen and founded Honjoji ( 本成寺 ) in Sanjō , Niigata in 1309 .
Alfred Vanderpol ( 7 April 1854 -- 17 June 1915 ) was a French engineer , philanthropist and author who was one of the leaders of the pacifist movement in France in the years leading up to World War I ( 1914 - -18 ) .
Otto van Rees ( 4 January 1823 -- 10 March 1892 ) was a liberal 19th century Dutch politician and colonial governor of the Dutch East Indies .
Gerhard I of Metz ( c. 875 -- 22 Jun 910 ) was count of Metz .
Dr Lonnie D. Kliever ( 1932 - -2004 ) was chair of the Department of Religious Studies at the Southern Methodist University ( SMU ) .
Dominic Barberi ( 22 June 1792 - 27 August 1849 ) was an Italian theologian and a member of the Passionist Congregation .
Charles Muzzicato ( March 1 , 1901 -- December 1968 ) was an American physician and politician from New York .
Domenico Tardini ( 29 February 1888 -- 30 July 1961 ) was a longtime aide to Pope Pius XII in the Secretariat of State .
Sir Hugh Willoughby of Risley , Derbyshire ( died 1554 ) was an early English Arctic voyager .
Dr Arthur Melville Clark FRSE PhD DLit ( 1895 - 1990 ) was a Scottish educationalist and author of several academic books concerning English literature and poetry .
Cornelius Coolidge ( August 30 , 1778 - September 4 , 1843 ) was a real estate developer in early 19th - century Boston , Massachusetts , who constructed buildings in Boston 's Beacon Hill neighborhood , and elsewhere .
Henry Hele M.D. ( 1688/9 - 1778 ) was an English physician , who became a substantial landowner in Wiltshire and Somerset .
James Pitot ( 1761 - -1831 ) , also known as Jacques Pitot , was the third Mayor of New Orleans , after Cavalier Petit served for a ten - day interim following Mayor Boré 's resignation .
Fray Diego Maroto ( 7/5/1618 Camarena , Toledo ( Spain)--1696 ) was the most important Peruvian architect of the second half of the 17th century .

Daniel Heinsius ( or Heins ) ( 9 June 1580 -- 25 February 1655 ) was one of the most famous scholars of the Dutch Renaissance .
Ove Bjelke ( 26 October 1611 -- 29 March 1674 ) was a Norwegian nobleman and statesman .
Guillaume - François Debure ( 1731 - -1782 ) was a French printer .
Mabelle Gilman Corey ( 1882/?1874 - March 1966 ) was an American stage actress and Broadway beauty at the close of the nineteenth century and beginning of the twentieth century .
Arthur Searcy ( born 6 January 1852 near Mount Barker , South Australia ; died 9 December 1935 in Harrow Road , St Peters , South Australia ) was President of the Public Service , Deputy Commissioner of Taxes and Stamps and President of the Marine Board in South Australia .
Sir Edward Atholl Oakeley , 7th Baronet of Shrewsbury ( 31 May 1900 -- January 1987 ) , known under the ring name Atholl Oakeley was a British professional wrestler and wrestling promoter who was one of the pioneers of professional wrestling in the United Kingdom .
Hermann Dörnemann ( 27 May 1893 -- 2 March 2005 ) of Germany was hailed in the press as the oldest living man in the world upon the death of 113-year - old American Fred Hale on 19 November 2004 .
Ali Hassan al - Jaber ( 12 December 1955 -- 12 March 2011 ) was a Qatari national working as a camera operator for the TV channel Al Jazeera .
Nigel Randell Evans ( often credited simply as Nigel Evans ) ( born 1943 - 2014 ) was a British author , campaigner for people with disabilities and film maker , with over 40 social documentaries to his credit , including Walter the feature film screened on the inaugural night of the UK 's Channel 4 .
Benjamin Ingelow ( 1834/35 - -1925 ) was an English architect who practised from an office in London .
August Spennemann ( c. 1878 -- 1945 ) was a German amateur ornithologist who lived in Java for 25 years ( 1915 - -1940 ) .
Jean Théodore Delacour ( 26 September 1890 -- 5 November 1985 ) was an American ornithologist of French origin .
Samson Lennard ( died 1633 ) was an English genealogist , officer of arms , and translator .
Agnes of Eltham ( 1498 - -1530 ) was an English woman , allegedly the illegitimate daughter of Princess Bridget of York .

Cao Jun ( died 259 ) , courtesy name Zi'an , was a prince in the state of Cao Wei in the Three Kingdoms period .
John Wisker ( 30 May 1846 in Kingston upon Hull , England -- 18 January 1884 in Richmond , Victoria ) was an English chess player and journalist .

Robert de Ferrers , 2nd Baron Ferrers of Chartley ( Chartley , Staffordshire , 25 March 1309 -- 28 August 1350 ) , was the son of John de Ferrers , 1st Baron Ferrers of Chartley and Hawise de Muscegros , a daughter of Robert de Muscegros .

Lodovico Bellanda ( c. 1575 -- after 1613 ) was an Italian composer and organist who lived in the transition period between the Renaissance and Baroque eras .
William Dell ( c. 1607 - -1669 ) was an English clergyman , Master of Gonville and Caius College , Cambridge from 1649 to 1660 , and prominent radical Parliamentarian .
Margaret Windeyer ( 24 November 1866 -- 11 August 1939 ) was an Australian librarian and feminist .
Carl Paivio , born Karl Einar Päiviö , 23 November 1893 in Töysä , died April 1952 in Ellis Island , New York , was a Finnish American labor activist and anarchist .
Alfred Cowles III ( 15 September 1891 -- 28 December 1984 ) was an American economist , businessman and founder of the Cowles Commission .
Philip Wenman , 7th Viscount Wenman ( 18 April 1742 -- 26 March 1800 ) , styled The Honourable Philip Wenman until 1760 , was a British landowner and politician .

Rudolf Rominger ( 21 August 1908 -- 8 November 1979 ) was a Swiss former alpine skier .
Fernando Sánchez de Tovar or Fernán Sánchez de Tovar , 1st Lord of Belves ( died 1384 ) was a significant Castilian soldier and Admiral of the Middle Ages .

Miklós Tótfalusi Kis ( Hungarian : Misztótfalusi Kis Miklós ) ( 1650 - March 20 , 1702 ) was a Hungarian letter cutter , typeface designer , typographer and printer .

William Douglas , 10th Earl of Angus ( 1552 -- 3 March 1611 ) was the son of William , the 9th Earl ( 1533 - -1591 ) .
Benjamin Vandergucht or Van der Gucht ( 1753 - -1794 ) was a picture - dealer , restorer and painter .
Sir Gawaine Baillie , 7th Baronet ( 8 March 1934 -- 21 December 2003 ) was an amateur motor racing driver , engineer , industrialist , stamp collector , and the owner of the estate surrounding Leeds Castle , the ancient fortress in Kent .

Moritz Fuerst ( March 1782 -- 1840 ) was an American artist of Jewish - Slovak origin .
Denise Marshall OBE ( 12 December 1961 -- 21 August 2015 ) was a British feminist and lesbian campaigner and charity executive involved in campaigning against and helping victims of domestic violence , sex trafficking and homophobia .
Mameshbirde ( Mari : Мамич Бердей , Tatar : Mämeşbirde/ Мәмешбирде , Mamışbirde/ Мамышбирде , Russian : Мамич-Берде́й ) ( died 1556 ) was a rebel commander during Kazan War for the independence of Kazan Khanate in 1552 - 1556 .
Ambroz Haračić ( born Mali Lošinj , 5 December 1855 , died Mali Lošinj , 1 October 1916 ) , was a Croatian botanist .
Kostas Andritsos , also known as George Andrews ( Greek : Κώστας Ανδρίτσος ; May 1 , 1916 , Athens -- October 10 , 1993 ) , was a Greek film director and writer .
Marudur Gopala Chakrapani ( 13 January 1911 -- 17 August 1986 ) , commonly known as M. G. Chakrapani or Yettan ( `` elder brother '' in Malayalam ) , was an Indian actor based in the Tamil film industry .
Willy Fritsch ( 27 January 1901 -- 13 July 1973 ) was a German theater and film actor , a popular leading man and character actor from the silent - film era to the early 1960s .
Edward Angelo Goodall ( 8 June 1819 -- 16 April 1908 ) was an English landscape and orientalist painter , a member of the distinguished Goodall family of artists .
Agnes Tyrrell ( 20 September 1846 -- 18 April 1883 ) was a Czech - born pianist and composer .
Sir William Edward Briggs Priestley ( 12 April 1859 -- 25 March 1932 ) was a Liberal politician from the West Riding of Yorkshire .
Olav Jakobsen Høyem ( 1830 - 1899 ) was a Norwegian teacher , telegrapher , supervisor of banknote printing and linguist .
Hugh Cholmondeley , 3rd Baron Delamere KCMG ( 28 April 1870 -- 13 November 1931 ) , styled The Honourable from birth until 1887 , was a British peer .
John Brandard ( Birmingham 1812 -- 15 December 1863 London ) was an English lithographic artist .
Dimitrios Ioannidis ( Greek : Δημήτριος Ιωαννίδης ( ðimiˈtros ʝoaˈniðis ) , 13 March 1923 -- 16 August 2010 ) , also known as Dimitris Ioannidis , was a Greek military officer and one of the leading figures in the Greek military junta of 1967 - -1974 .
Lloyd Zucker ( 23 March 1929 -- 21 September 2009 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Port Adelaide Football Club in the South Australian National Football League during the 1950s .
Antoine Barthélemy Jean Guillemot ( 11 November 1822 , Thiers −25 August 1902 , Thiers ) was a French entomologist .
Edward Irving ( 4 August 1792 -- 7 December 1834 ) was a Scottish clergyman , generally regarded as the main figure behind the foundation of the Catholic Apostolic Church .
Thomas St. Lawrence , also called Thomas Howth ( c.1480 - 1553 ) was a leading statesman and judge in sixteenth - century Ireland .
Robert Hyland , Jr. ( 1920 - -1992 ) was CBS regional vice president and general manager of radio station KMOX in St. Louis , Missouri for four decades .
Willibald Peter Prasthofer ( 17 May 1917 - 30 July 1993 ) was an Austrian rocket scientist and educator .
Marco Facoli ( c. 1540 - 1585 ) , Venice , was an Italian organist , harpsichordist and composer .
George Robert Jebb ( 1838 - -1927 ) was a civil engineer from the United Kingdom .
Velma Wallace Rayness ( 1896 - -1977 ) was an American artist , author , and instructor who lived in Iowa .
Philippe de Cabassole or Philippe de Cabassoles ( 1305 - -1372 ) , the Bishop of Cavaillon , Seigneur of Vaucluse , was the great protector of Renaissance poet Francesco Petrarch .
Ángel Recasens ( 4 March 1938 in Cambrils -- 2 August 2007 ) was a Catalonian organist , teacher , composer and musicologist best known as a choral conductor .
Alexander Duff , 3rd Earl Fife ( 18 April 1731 -- 17 April 1811 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Rosa Palumbo , better known by her stage name as Rosita Contreras ( March 15 , 1913 - 1962 ) , was an Argentine actress , singer and vedette .
Wei Daijia ( 韋待價 ) ( died 689 ? ) was a general and official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as chancellor during the first reign of Emperor Ruizong .
John FitzAlan , 13th Earl of Arundel , 3rd Baron Maltravers ( 1 August 1385 -- 21 April 1421 ) was an English nobleman .
Judith Huxley ( 1926 - 17 October 1983 ) was an American food columnist for the Washington Post .
Carlo Antonio Delpini ( died 1828 ) was an Italian pantomimist and theatrical manager .
Haydar al - Kuzbari ( Arabic : حيدر الكزبري‎ , 1920 -- 1996 ) was a Syrian lieutenant colonel who took part in the 1961 Syrian coup d'état that led to the dissolution of the United Arab Republic .
Sir Samuel Cleland Davidson , KBE ( 18 November 1846 -- 18 August 1921 ) was an Irish inventor and engineer .
Aditya Vikram Birla ( 14 November 1943 -- 1 October 1995 ) , was an Indian industrialist .
Kuldeep Manak ( Punjabi : ਕੁਲਦੀਪ ਮਾਣਕ‌ ; 15 November 1951 -- 30 November 2011 ) was a noted Punjabi singer of Indian Punjab .
June Keithley - Castro ( 10 March 1947 -- 24 November 2013 ) was a Filipina actress and broadcast journalist .
Jakob Hermann ( 16 July 1678 -- 11 July 1733 ) was a mathematician who worked on problems in classical mechanics .
Han Shizhong ( 韓世忠 ) ( 1089 - -1151 ) was a Chinese general of the late Northern Song Dynasty and the early Southern Song Dynasty .
Leopold Willem Ras ( died 1847 ) was a Dutch merchant - trader and diplomat .
Olaus Islandsmoen ( 1873 in Sør - Aurdal -- 1949 ) was a Norwegian educator , museologist and politician .
John Chishull or John de Chishull ( died 1280 ) was Lord Chancellor of England , Bishop of London , and Lord High Treasurer during the 13th century .
Marie - Luise Jahn ( 28 May 1918 -- 22 June 2010 ) was a German physician and a member of the anti - Nazi resistance movement White Rose .
Sir John Keith , 1st Earl of Kintore ( died 1714 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Zhang Haoruo ( Chinese : 张皓若 ; 1932 -- 27 March 2004 ) was a politician and petroleum engineer of the People 's Republic of China .
Edmund Willard born 19 December 1884 in Brighton , Sussex , England -- died 6 October 1956 in Kingston upon Thames , England , was a British actor of the 1930s and 1940s .
Leo Rowlands ( 1891 - 1967 ) was a Franciscan Catholic priest and composer , associated with Rhode Island .
Frank Curtis ( 12 November 1890 -- 1957 ) was a Welsh footballer , who played in the Football League for Wolverhampton Wanderers and Reading .
Edgar Williamson , Jr. ( November 24 , 1903 - April 1981 ) was an American Republican Party politician who served four terms in the New Jersey General Assembly .
Jerry Jofen ( 1925 - -1993 ) was an American painter , collagist , and experimental filmmaker .
Herbert Armitage James , CH ( 3 August 1844 -- 15 November 1931 ) was a Welsh cleric and headmaster of three leading public schools , who ended his `` remarkable scholastic career '' , as it was later described by Austen Chamberlain , by becoming President of St John 's College , Oxford .
Francis Boyle , 1st Viscount Shannon ( 1623 - -1699 ) was a Privy Counsellor of Ireland and held the office of Governor of County Cork .
Jocelyn Brooke ( 30 November 1908 -- 29 October 1966 ) was an English author born in Kent .
David Richard Porter ( 1882 - -1973 ) was a major figure in the Young Men 's Christian Association ( YMCA ) during the height of the organization 's popularity and influence on American high school and college campuses .
Richard Cowley ( died 1619 ) was an actor in English Renaissance theatre , a colleague of William Shakespeare and Richard Burbage in the Lord Chamberlain 's Men and the King 's Men .
Enrique de la Mora y Palomar ( 16 June 1907 -- 9 May 1978 ) was a Mexican architect who designed prominent university buildings and Roman Catholic churches in which he experimented with hyperbolic - paraboloid roofs .
Robert Sackville , 2nd Earl of Dorset ( 1561 - -1609 ) was an English aristocrat and politician , with humanist and commercial interests .
Kaspar Fürstenau ( 26 February 1772 , Münster -- 11 May 1819 , Oldenburg ) was a German flautist and composer .
Malik Barkat Ali ( 1886 -- 1946 ) was a Muslim Indian politician , lawyer and journalist .
Louis Isaac Jaffe ( 1888 - -1950 ) was editorial page editor of the newspaper Virginian - Pilot of Norfolk , Virginia from 1919 to 1950 .
Henry Wellesley , 1st Baron Cowley GCB ( 20 January 1773 -- 27 April 1847 ) was a British diplomat and politician .
Anthony Durand ( 1956 - -2009 ) was a Native American potter from Picuris Pueblo , New Mexico , United States .
Vladimir Constantinescu ( born 1895 , died 1965 ) was a Romanian Major - General during World War II . He began his military career as Commandant of Cavalry School in 1941 , and in 1942 became Commanding Officer 8th Rosiori Cavalry Regiment and Commandant of Cavalry School .
Bennie Le Sueur ( 22 March 1917 -- 17 August 1994 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray and Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Henry Malden ( 1800 - -1876 ) was a prominent British academic .
William Francis de Vismes Kane ( 1840 -- 1918 ) was an Irish entomologist Born in Exmouth , Devon Kane lived at Drumreaske Housein Monaghan .
Alex Ebel ( November 14 , 1923 -- December 6 , 2013 ) was a science fiction and fantasy illustrator .
Harald Normann ( 15 February 1893 -- 18 June 1978 ) was a Norwegian military officer and non - fiction writer .
Sir Shah Muhammad Sulaiman ( 3 February 1886 -- 12 March 1941 ) ( popularly known as Sir Shah Sulaiman or Sir Sulaiman ) was the Chief Justice of the Allahabad High Court from 16 March 1932 to 30 September 1937 and was the first Indian and one of the youngest ever to hold this coveted post .
Barkhad Awale Adan , also spelled Burkhat , ( 1950 ? -- 24 August 2010 ) was a Somali journalist .
Wilbur Harris ( 28 May 1912 - 28 June 1981 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Admiral of the Fleet Sir ( George ) Rodney Mundy , GCB ( 19 April 1805 -- 23 December 1884 ) was a Royal Navy officer .
Cyrille Verbrugge ( 9 November 1866 -- 1929 ) was a Belgian Olympic fencer .
Samuel Bogart ( 2 April 1797 -- 11 March 1861 ) was an itinerant Methodist minister and militia captain from Ray County , Missouri who played a prominent role in the 1838 Missouri Mormon War before later moving to Collin County , Texas , where he became a Texas Ranger and a member of the Texas State Legislature .
Nancy Price , CBE ( 3 February 1880 -- 31 March 1970 ) , was an English actress on stage and screen , author and theatre director .
Kenton Couse ( 1721 -- 10 October 1790 ) was an English architect and Secretary to the Board of Works from 1775 to 1782 .
Hermann Kinkelin ( 11 November 1832 -- 2 January 1913 ) was a Swiss mathematician and politician .
Arthur Walters Wills BA , LLB ( 1868 - 17 November 1948 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician .
Charles Masson Fox ( 9 November 1866 -- 11 October 1935 ) was a Cornish businessman who achieved international prominence in the world of chess problems and a place in the gay history of Edwardian England .
Charles Troedel ( 1835/6 Hamburg -- 1906 ) ( born Johannes Thedor Carl Troedel ) was a German - born lithographic printer prominent in Melbourne during the late 19th century .
David of Augsburg ( early 13th century -- 19 November 1272 ) was a medieval German mystic , and a Franciscan friar .
Lieutenant - General Lij Abiye Abebe , KBE , ( 1918 -- 23 November 1974 ) was an Ethiopian politician and son - in - law of Emperor Haile Selassie .
Millard Webb ( 6 December 1893 -- 21 April 1935 ) , was an American screenwriter and director .
Though Heinz List died in 1988 , he is remembered both as a pioneering engineer -- one of only 26 members of the Polymer Processing Hall of Fame at the University of Akron , Ohio , USA -- and as a business leader .

Sir Thomas Maclear ( 17 March 1794 -- 14 July 1879 ) was an Irish - born South African astronomer who became Her Majesty 's astronomer at the Cape of Good Hope .
Robert McGregor Innes Ireland ( 12 June 1930 -- 22 October 1993 ) , was a British military officer , engineer , and motor racing driver .
Arthur Hauffe ( 20 December 1892 -- 22 July 1944 ) was a German career soldier .
Thomas Savage , 3rd Earl Rivers ( c. 1628 -- 14 September 1694 ) was an English peer .
Marceli Harasimowicz ( 1859 , Warsaw - 1935 , Lwów ) was a Polish landscape painter and museum curator .
Ye Chengzhong ( simplified Chinese : 叶澄衷 ; traditional Chinese : 葉澄衷 ; pinyin : Yè Chéngzhōng 1840 - -1899 ) , was a Chinese businessman active during the final years of the Qing Dynasty and a pioneer in the hardware industry who also made considerable contributions to education .
Sir David Milne - Watson ( 10 March 1869 -- 3 October 1945 ) was a Scottish industrialist who served as managing director of the Gas Light and Coke Company between 1916 and 1945 , and president of the National Gas Council of Great Britain and Ireland from 1919 to 1943 .
Seán Ó Síocháin ( 24 March 1914 -- 2 February 1997 ) was an Irish footballer , hurler and ballad - singer who became General - Secretary of the GAA .
George S. Griggs ( 1805 - 1870 ) was a pioneer master mechanic in the earliest days of railroading in the United States .
Joseph J. Daniels ( 1826 - -1916 ) , most commonly known as J. J. Daniels , was an American bridge builder active in Indiana .
Julius Stern ( 8 August 1820 -- 27 February 1883 ) was a Jewish - German musical pedagogue and composer .
Jean Wade Rindlaub ( 9 February 1904 -- 19 December 1991 ) was one of the first American women to become a major advertising executive .
Rabbi Yom - Tov Ehrlich ( 1914 - -1990 ) was a renowned Hasidic musician , composer , lyricist , recording artist , and popular entertainer known for his popular Yiddish music albums .
John Fisher ( c. 19 October 1469 -- 22 June 1535 ) , venerated by Roman Catholics as Saint John Fisher , was an English Catholic bishop and theologian .
Birger Ljungberg ( 7 June 1884 -- 20 April 1967 ) was the Norwegian Minister of Defence 1939 - -1942 .

Olive Banks ( 2 July 1923 -- 14 September 2006 ) was a professor at Leicester University who worked upon the sociology of education and the history of feminism .
William Edward Love ( 1806 - -1867 ) was an English impressionist .
Henry de Maunsfeld DD ( also Henry Mansfield , Maunsfeild , Maunsfield , Maunnesfeld , Mammesfeld , or Maymysfeld ; died 1328 ) was an English medieval theologian , philosopher , churchman , college fellow , and university chancellor .
Osama Youssef Kashmoula was a Governor of Mosul killed during an attack in 2004 .
Arabella Chapman ( 1859 - -1927 ) was an African - American woman who is best remembered for being the first student to graduate from upstate New York 's Albany School for Educating People of Color , later known as Albany High School .
Sabine Zlatin ( 13 January 1907 -- 21 September 1996 ) was a Polish - born Frenchwoman who hid Jewish children during World War II .
Louis Charles Folliot de Crenneville ( 3 July 1763 -- 21 June 1840 ) joined the French royal navy in the 1770s .
Sarah Harlowe ( 1765 - -1852 ) was a popular actress of the London stage around the turn of the 19th century .
Dongshan Liangjie ( 807 - -869 ) ( Chinese : 洞山良价 ; pinyin : Dòngshān Liángjiè ; Wade -- Giles : Tung - shan Liang - chieh ; Japanese : Tōzan Ryōkai ; Korean : Tongsan Lianggye ; Vietnamese : Động Sơn Lương Giới ) was a Chan Buddhist monk of ninth - century China .
Therese Grob ( 16 November 1798 -- 17 March 1875 ) was the first love of the composer Franz Schubert .

Ken Battefield ( died 1967 ) was a prolific comic book artist in the 1940s and early 1950s , during the Golden Age of Comic Books .
Güzelce Ali Pasha ( Ali Pasha the Handsome ; died 9 March 1621 ) , also known as Çelebi Ali Pasha or İstanköylü Ali Pasha , was an Ottoman statesman .

Jackie Law , Jr died in 1996 and remained a committed QoS fan right up until his death .
Heinrich Bullinger ( 18 July 1504 -- 17 September 1575 ) was a Swiss reformer , the successor of Huldrych Zwingli as head of the Zurich church and pastor at Grossmünster .

Louis Van Hege ( 8 May 1889 -- 24 June 1975 ) was a Belgian football Inside - Forward who played for AC Milan from 1910 to 1915 , scoring 97 goals during five Italian Football Championship seasons .

Lesser Samuels ( 26 July 1894 - 22 December 1980 ) enjoyed a 20-year career as a Hollywood screenwriter .

Hans Aarnes ( 6 May 1886 -- 25 October 1960 ) was a Norwegian entrepreneur , journalist , newspaper editor , magazine editor , publisher and proponent for the Nynorsk language .

Aldo Maldera ( 14 October 1953 -- 1 August 2012 ) was an Italian footballer , who played as a fullback or as a wide midfielder on the left .

Ralph Linton ( 27 February 1893 -- 24 December 1953 ) was a respected American anthropologist of the mid-20th century , particularly remembered for his texts The Study of Man ( 1936 ) and The Tree of Culture ( 1955 ) .
Countess Palatine Dorothea of Simmern ( 6 January 1581 -- 18 September 1631 ) was a Countess Palatine of Simmern by birth and Princess of Anhalt - Dessau by marriage .

Marco Acerbi ( Aosta , 29 April 1949-Cervinia , 24 July 1989 ) was an Italian hurdler .
Gerard Hoffnung ( 22 March 1925 -- 28 September 1959 ) was an artist and musician , best known for his humorous works .
Timothy Matlack ( May 28 , 1736 -- April 14 , 1829 ) was a brewer and beer bottler who emerged as a popular revolutionary leader and powerful official in the American Revolutionary War .
Raymond Bessone ( 11 May 1911 -- 17 April 1992 ) , known as Mr Teasy - Weasy , Teasie Weasie Raymond and various combinations of these , was a British hairdresser from the 1930s to the 1960s .

Enrico Del Debbio ( 26 May 1891 -- 12 July 1973 ) was an Italian architect and university professor .
Karol Castillo ( 29 August 1989 -- 10 April 2013 ) was a model and beauty pageant contestant from Peru .

Kalyan Kumar ( 28 July 1928 -- 1 August 1999 ) , born as Chokkanna , was an Indian film actor , and an occasional film director and producer , who worked primarily in Kannada and Tamil cinema .

Josef Keil ( 13 October 1878 -- 13 December 1963 ) was an Austrian historian , epigrapher and an archaeologist .

Laurence John Hartley Teakle ( 2 August 1901 -- 8 December 1979 ) was Professor of Agriculture from 1947 until 1963 at the University of Queensland in Brisbane , Australia .
Sir Henry North , 1st Baronet ( c 1609 -- 29 August 1671 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1656 and 1671 .
Joseph A. Pechman ( 1918 - -1989 ) was a highly influential economist and taxation scholar in the United States .
Bernie Knee ( Feb. 14 , 1924 , New York City -- Nov. 20 , 1994 , Fort Lauderdale ) was an actor and singer / musician .
Pieter Adrianus Ossewaarde ( 14 August 1775 -- 21 March 1853 ) was a Dutch technocratic politician , who was twice interim Minister of Finance , the first time from April to June 1828 and the second time in May and June 1848 after the resignation of Gerrit Schimmelpenninck .
James Hatley Frere ( 1779 - -1866 ) , was an English writer on prophecy .
Luo Yi ( Chinese : 羅藝 ) ( died 627 ) , known during service to Tang Dynasty as Li Yi ( 李藝 ) , courtesy name Ziyan ( 子延 ) or Ziting ( 子廷 ) , was a Sui Dynasty official who rose against the rule of Emperor Yang of Sui and occupied the modern Beijing region .
John Mottley ( 1692 - -1750 ) was an English writer , known as a dramatist , biographer , and compiler of jokes .
Tote Du Crow ( 1858 - -12 December 1927 ) was a Native American silent film actor originally from Watsonville , California .
Knud Olsen ( 1919 on Præstø -- 31 August 2010 in Bandholm ) is a Danish builder and designer of boats , who designed one of the most popular sailing dinghies in use over the past 50 years , the OK Dinghy , which became an ISAF International Class in 1974 .
George Goldsmith ( 11 March 1905 -- 1974 ) was a professional footballer who played for Bishop Auckland , Loftus Albion F.C. , Hull City , Tottenham Hotspur and Bolton Wanderers .
Christopher Brinchmann ( 1 April 1864 -- 26 February 1940 ) was a Norwegian historian and archivist .
Jane Pope ( 1744 -- 30 July 1818 ) was an English actress , daughter of a London theatrical wig - maker .
John Paul Rylands , FSA ( 1846 -- 2 March 1923 , Birkenhead ) , was an English barrister , genealogist and topographer .
Lina Pires de Campos née Del Vecchio ( 18 June 1918 -- 14 April 2003 ) was a Brazilian pianist , music educator and composer of both classical and popular music .
Robert Lugar ( 1773 -- 23 June 1855 ) , was an English architect and engineer in the Industrial Revolution .
Margaret Ely Webb ( 1877 - -1965 ) was an American illustrator , printmaker , and bookplate artist .
Lambert Hitchcock ( May 28 , 1795 , Cheshire , Connecticut -- 1852 ) was an American furniture manufacturer , famous for designing and mass - producing the Hitchcock chair .
Sir Thomas Rouse , 1st Baronet ( 27 March 1608 - 26 May 1676 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1654 and 1660 .
Stewart Judah ( February 16 , 1893 - June 11 , 1966 ) began a career in magic in 1920 .
Dale Nichols ( 1904 -- October 19 , 1995 ) , also published under his full name , Dale William Nichols , was an American visual artist whose works included illustrations , paintings , lithographs , and wood carvings .
Christian Gullager ( March 1 , 1759 -- November 12 , 1826 ) was a Danish - American artist specializing in portraits and theatrical scenery in the late 18th century .
Edward Valpy ( 1764 - -1832 ) was an English cleric , classical scholar and schoolteacher .
Kent Durden ( 1937 - -2007 ) was an American wildlife photographer , documentary producer and writer .
Jovan Ružić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Јован Ружић ) , ( 12 December 1898 -- 25 September 1973 ) was a Serbian footballer .
Count August of Legnica ( Polish : August hrabia legnicki ; German : Graf August von Liegnitz ; Brzeg , 21 August 1627 -- Siebenhufen near Przeworno , 14 May 1679 ) , was a member of the House of Piast .
Joseph Wild ( also Wilde ) ( c.1759 or 1773 - -1847 ) was an early explorer of Australia .
Mario Zanini , or simply Zanini ( September 10 , 1907 in São Paulo -- August 16 , 1971 in São Paulo ) , was a Brazilian painter and interior designer .
Gordon Abbott ( 26 September 1914 - 19 April 1986 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sebastiaen van Aken or Sebastiaen Aken ( bapt . 31 March 1648 - 21 November 1722 ) was a Flemish historical painter .
Leontius of Caesarea ( died 337 ) was a bishop of Caesarea Mazaca , in Cappadocia .
Kalidas Nag ( 1892 - 1966 ) was an Indian historian , author and parliamentarian .
Samuel Caldwell Nicholson ( died 1891 ) was a British trade unionist .
Dorrit Cohn ( 1924 -- 10 March 2012 ) was a scholar of German and Comparative Literature whose work centered on the formal analysis of narrative fiction .
P. Dawood Shah ( Tamil : பா. தாவூத் ஷா ) ( 1885 - 1969 ) was a Tamil scholar and activist .
Preserved Smith ( July 22 , 1880 -- May 15 , 1941 ) was an American historian of the Protestant Reformation .
Archimandrite Ilya Denisov ( 22 January 1893 in Saint Petersburg , Russian Empire -- 7 September 1971 in Chicago , USA ) was a Russian Greek - Catholic priest .
Lady Anne Barnard ( née Lindsay ; 12 December 1750 -- 6 May 1825 ) was a Scottish travel writer , artist and socialite , and the author of the ballad Auld Robin Gray .
Richard Fenner Burges ( 1873 - -1945 ) was a Texan attorney , legislator and conservationist .
Venant de Viviers ( d. 544 ) was the Bishop of Viviers in the Ardèche , southern France .
Horace Fisher ( 3 August 1903 -- 16 April 1974 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played fifty two games for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1928 and 1936 .
William Malcolm Hailey , 1st Baron Hailey OM GCSI GCMG GCIE PC ( 15 February 1872 -- 1 June 1969 ) , known as Sir Malcolm Hailey between 1921 and 1936 , was a British peer and administrator in British India .
George Halket or Hacket ( died 1756 ) , was a Scottish poet and songwriter .
Alfred Hope Patten ( 17 November 1885 , Town Brewery , Sidmouth - 11 August 1958 , The College , Little Walsingham ) , known as Pat to his friends , was an Anglo - Catholic priest in the Church of England , best known for his restoration of the shrine of Our Lady of Walsingham .
Charles Anselm Bolton ( 1905 to 1970 ) was for many years a priest of the Roman Catholic Church , being the Priest of Salford Diocese in 1950 .
Catarina Wentin ( 1637 - 1707 ) was a Swedish ( originally German ) midwife , official midwife of the royal court .
Karl Zsigmondy ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈʒiɡmondi ) ) ( 27 March 1867 - 14 October 1925 ) was an Austrian mathematician of Hungarian ethnicity .
George Norman Douglas ( 8 December 1868 -- 7 February 1952 ) was a British writer , now best known for his 1917 novel South Wind .
Valentin de Boulogne ( before 3 January 1591 -- 19 August 1632 ) , sometimes referred to as Le Valentin , was a French painter in the tenebrist style .
Silvia Cambir ( 24 January 1924 - 2007 ) is a Romanian Expressionist painter , portraitist , and book illustrator .
Emmanuel McEachern ( ca 1816 -- November 5 , 1875 ) was a farmer and political figure on Prince Edward Island .
Wally Mutimer ( 30 July 1907 -- 14 October 1984 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Dezső Pattantyús - Ábrahám de Dancka ( 10 July 1875 -- 25 July 1973 ) was a conservative Hungarian politician who served as Prime Minister and temporary Minister of Finance of the second counter - revolutionary government in Szeged for one month in 1919 .
Doug Palmer ( 23 June 1930 -- 23 November 1992 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the early 1950s .
Bernhard Erasmus von Deroy ( 11 December 1743 -- 23 August 1812 ) from the Electorate of the Palatinate became a noted general officer in the army of Bavaria .
Memduh Ünlütürk ( died 7 April 1991 ) was a Turkish general associated with the Counter - Guerrilla and the anti - communist Ziverbey interrogations following the 1971 coup .
Alexander Zeitlin ( 28 August 1900 in Russia -- 19 April 1998 ) was a prominent figure in the US Air Force major press design program following the Second World War and Korean War years .
Norman Maen ( 1932 -- 22 April 2008 , born `` Norman Maternaghan '' ) was a director and choreographer .
Na'od ( Amharic : ናዖስ ? ) ( ? -- 31 July 1508 ) was Emperor ( nəgusä nägäst ) ( 1494 - 31 July 1508 ) of Ethiopia , and a member of the Solomonic dynasty .
Jean Victor Mottez ( 31 October 1866 in Paris -- 7 December 1942 in Saint Gervais D'Auvergne ) was a French naval officer .
Nora Connolly O'Brien ( 1893 -- 17 June 1981 ) was an activist and writer ; she was also a member of the Irish Senate .
Flann mac Congalaig ( died 812 ) was a King of Brega from the Uí Chonaing sept of Cnogba ( Knowth ) of the Síl nÁedo Sláine branch of the southern Ui Neill .
Teddy Johnston ( 3 September 1891 -- 3 October 1922 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Hawkin ( fl . 1397 - 1406 ) , of Huntingdon and Great Gidding , Huntingdonshire , was an English politician .
Murong Hui ( 慕容廆 ) , ( 269 - -333 ) Xianbei chief and Duke Xiang of Liaodong , posthumously honored as Prince Wuxuan of Yan .
Georg Ulrich Wasmuth ( 19 March 1788 -- 16 October 1814 ) was a Norwegian military officer and who served as a representative at the Norwegian Constitutional Assembly .
Ilia Fibiger ( 5 October 1817 - 10 June 1867 ) was a Danish writer and playwright as well as Denmark 's first professional nurse .
Bert Greeves MBE ( born Oscar Bertram Greeves , 5 June 1906 -- 15 July 1993 ) was a British engineer who founded Invacar Ltd in 1942 and Greeves motor cycles in 1953 .
Ricardo Lancaster - Jones y Verea , MA BE KHS ( 9 February 1905 -- 20 January 1983 ) was a Mexican historian , diplomat , scholar , professor , art collector and sugarcane entrepreneur who made significant contributions toward the study of the haciendas of the State of Jalisco ( Mexico ) in the twentieth century .
Pierre de Pardaillan de Gondrin ( 1692 -- 4 November 1733 ) was the Duke - Bishop of Langres , France .
Sir Benjamin Rudyerd or Rudyard ( 1572 -- 31 May 1658 ) was an English poet and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1621 and 1648 .
Joseph W. Yost ( 1847 - -1923 ) was a prominent architect from Ohio whose works included many courthouses and other public buildings .
Jesse Chickering ( born Dover , New Hampshire , 31 August 1797 ; died West Roxbury , Massachusetts , 29 May 1855 ) was a political economist .
Mia May aka Hermine Pfleger ( 2 June 1884 -- 28 November 1980 ) was an Austrian actress .
Wilhelm Kettler ( 20 June 1574 in Mitau -- 7 April 1640 in Kucklow ) was the second Duke of Courland , a region of Latvia .
Alfred P. Wolf ( February 23 , 1923 -- December 17 , 1998 ) was an American nuclear and organic chemist .
Pierre Beauchamp ( also Beauchamps , called `` Charles '' or Charles - Louis Beauchamp ) ( 30 October 1631 -- February 1705 ) was a French choreographer , dancer and composer , and the probable inventor of Beauchamp - Feuillet notation .
Sanapia , born Mary Poafpybitty ( ca . 20 May 1895 - -23 January 1984 ) was a Comanche medicine woman and spiritual healer .
Seán Dublin Bay Rockall Loftus ( 1 November 1927 -- 10 July 2010 ) was an Irish environmentalist , barrister and politician who drew attention to his campaign issues by changing his name .
Matija Ivanić ( Vrbanj , Hvar around 1445 -- Rome 1523 ) was a prominent 16th century citizen of the Dalmatian city of Hvar that led the Hvar Rebellion ( 1510 - -1514 ) against the Venetian Republic .
Muircheartach mac Pilib Ó Ceallaigh , Archbishop of Tuam and patron of An Leabhar Ua Maine , died 1407 .
Matthew of Kraków ( c. 1335 -- 5 March 1410 ) was a renowned German - Polish scholar and priest of the fourteenth century .
Squadron Leader Sarfaraz Ahmed Rafiqui ( 18 July 1935 -- 6 September 1965 ) was a fighter pilot in the Pakistan Air Force .
Giuseppe Antonio Sorbilli ( Zammarò . a frazione of San Gregorio d'Ippona , in what is now the Province of Vibo Valentia , Calabria , 1824 - 1890 ) was an Italian sculptor .
Mary Elvira Weeks ( 1892 - -1975 ) was an American chemist and science historian who wrote Discovery of the Elements .
Bakin Pertin ( 1 May 1942 , in Damro village -- 5 January 1996 , in Guwahati ) was an Indian politician .
Hakim Syed Niamatullah ( 1900 - 1961 ) was an Indian politician and practitioner of Unani medicine who served as mayor of Madras city in 1943 - 44 .
Sir Charles James Jackson ( 2 May 1849 -- 23 April 1923 ) was a British businessman , collector , barrister , newspaper executive , politician , and writer , who was an authority on antique gold and silver plate .
Axel Collett ( 6 August 1880 in Kolvereid -- 17 January 1968 ) was a Norwegian landowner , timber merchant and sawmill owner .
Bogdan Zimonjić , ( Serbian Cyrillic : Богдан Зимоњић ; 1813 -- 21 January 1909 ) was a Serbian Orthodox priest , and Voivode ( military commander ) in two major uprisings against the Ottoman Empire in 19th - century Herzegovina : in 1852 - -62 , and 1875 - -78 .
Richard FitzJames ( died 15 January 1522 ) was a medieval Bishop of Rochester , Bishop of Chichester and Bishop of London .
Sidney Bowser ( 6 April 1891 -- 10 February 1961 ) , better known as Sid Bowser , was an English footballer who played at inside - left and centre - half .
Franciscus van den Enden was condemned to death and on 27 November 1674 , after the decapitation of the noble conspirators , he was hanged before the Bastille .
Wilhelm Brückner ( 11 December 1884 in Baden - Baden -- 18 August 1954 in Herbsdorf , Upper Bavaria ) was until 1940 Adolf Hitler 's chief adjutant .
Anna Atkins ( née Children ; 16 March 1799 -- 9 June 1871 ) was an English botanist and photographer .

José Iglesias Fernández ( 23 December 1926 -- 12 July 2007 ) , nicknamed Joseíto , was a Spanish football outside right and manager .
Charles Schweinfurth ( 13 April 1890 -- 16 November 1970 ) was an American botanist and plant collector who distinguished himself by his studies on orchids .
William Chalmers Burns ( 宾惠廉 , 1 April 1815 -- 4 April 1868 ) was a Scottish Evangelist and Missionary to China with the English Presbyterian Mission who originated from Kilsyth , North Lanarkshire .
Sergo Zakariadze ( Georgian : სერგო ზაქარიაძე ( sɛrɡɔ zakʰariad͡zɛ ) ; 18 July ( O.S. July 1 ) 1909 -- 13 April 1971 ) was a renowned Georgian actor .
Paul Friedrichs ( 21 March 1940 ; Buchholz -- 30 August 2012 ; Erfurt ) was an East German professional motocross racer .
Abraham Pihl ( 3 October 1756 -- 20 May 1821 ) was a Norwegian clergyman , astronomer and architect .
Theophilus Bird , or Bourne , ( 1608 -- 1663 ) was a seventeenth - century English actor .

Peter Womersley ( 24 June 1923 - -1993 ) was a British architect , best known for his work in the modernist style .
Jacques Dinet ( 1584 - 1653 ) was a French Jesuit , confessor to Louis XIII and an associate of René Descartes .
Herbert Langley ( 1888 - -1967 ) was a well - known early twentieth - century British opera singer ( baritone ) who later also played various minor acting roles in a number of British films .
William Bonville , 1st Baron Bonville , KG ( c. 1392 - -93 -- 18 February 1461 ) of Shute , Devon , was an English nobleman , soldier , and administrator .
John Coggeshall ( 1601 -- 27 November 1647 ) was one of the founders of Rhode Island and the first President of all four towns in the Colony of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations .
Alice Chestre ( sometimes written `` Chester '' or `` Chestour '' ) ( died 1485 ) was a merchant and a benefactor of the city of Bristol , England .
Giuseppe Galeòtti ( 1708 - 1778 ) was an Italian painter , active in a Baroque style , mainly in Liguria .
Dan Laksov ( 10 July 1940 -- 25 October 2013 ) was a Norwegian - Swedish mathematician and human rights activist .
Ivane Kazbegi ( Georgian : ივანე ყაზბეგი ; Polish : Jan ( Iwan ) Kazbek ; Russian : Иван Николаевич Казбек , Ivan Nikolayevich Kazbek ) ( June 11 , 1860 -- December 2 , 1943 ) was a Georgian soldier , who served , successively , in the Imperial Russian , Georgian and Polish armies .
Simon Harcourt , 1st Earl Harcourt , of Stanton Harcourt , Oxfordshire , PC FRS ( 1714 -- 16 September 1777 ) , known as 2nd Viscount Harcourt , of Stanton Harcourt , Oxfordshire , between 1727 and 1749 , was a British diplomat and general who became Viceroy of Ireland .
Jan van Call ( 1655 - 1703 ) was an artist born , according to Descamps , at Nijmegen in 1655 .
François Sublet de Noyers ( 1589 - -1645 ) , one of Cardinal de Richelieu 's political creatures , who derived his position and political weight from the Cardinal 's consistent patronage , was a secretary of state to Louis XIII , and a member of his Conseil du Roi .
Jacques Besson ( 1540 ? - 1573 ) was a French Protestant inventor , mathematician , and philosopher , chiefly remembered for his popular treatise on machines Theatrum Instrumentorum ( 1571 - -72 ) , which saw many reprints in different languages .
Timothy Grubb ( 30 May 1954 -- 11 May 2010 ) was a British show jumping champion .
Dionysis Papagiannopoulos ( Greek : Διονύσης Παπαγιαννόπουλος ; 12 July 1912 -- 17 April 1984 ) was a Greek actor .
Alan Gowen ( 19 August 1947 -- 17 May 1981 ) was a fusion / progressive rock keyboardist , best known for his work in Gilgamesh and National Health .
Sir Man - kam Lo , CBE ( 1893 -- 7 March 1959 ) was a prominent Eurasian lawyer in Hong Kong and unofficial member of the Executive Council and the Legislative Council of Hong Kong .
Mihály Dávid ( July 31 , 1886 - 1944 ) was a Hungarian athlete who competed mainly in the shot put .
José Cascante , José de Cascante or Joseph Cascante ( 1646 -- December 1702 ) was a Colombian Baroque composer and organist .
Arthur Brough ( born Frederick Arthur Baker ) ( 26 February 1905 -- 28 May 1978 ) was a British actor , best known for portraying the character of senior menswear salesman Mr. Ernest Grainger on the BBC sitcom Are You Being Served ?
Richard Flecknoe ( c. 1600 -- 1678 ) was an English dramatist , poet and musician who was made the butt of satires by Andrew Marvell ( 1681 ) and John Dryden ( 1682 ) .
Ferdinand Rebay ( 11 June 1880 -- 6 November 1953 ) was an Austrian composer , music teacher , choir director , and pianist .
Liu Zongzhou ( simplified Chinese : 刘宗周 ; traditional Chinese : 劉宗周 ; pinyin : Liú Zōngzhōu , 1578 - -1645 ) , also known as Liu Jishan ( simplified Chinese : 刘蕺山 ; traditional Chinese : 劉蕺山 ) , was a Confucian scholar from the Ming dynasty , born in Shanyin , Shaoxing .
Reg Isidore ( 4 April 1949 -- 22 March 2009 ) was a rock drummer best known for his work with Robin Trower .
Sadhu Kuppuswami ( 1890 - -1956 ) was a Fiji Indian who inspired South Indians in Fiji to have pride in their culture and language and was instrumental in the establishment of the Sangam organisation in Fiji .
Meta Vidmar ( born Metoda Vidmar , 15 May 1899 , Ljubljana -- 1 November 1975 , Ljubljana ) was the first Slovene modern dancer , notable for establishing the Mary Wigman dance school in Ljubljana in 1930 , the first modern dance school in Slovenia .
Engelbert Arnold ( 7 March 1856 -- 16 November 1911 ) was a Swiss - born electrical engineer .

Gerald Gladstone ( 7 January 1929 -- 7 March 2005 ) was a Canadian sculptor and painter .
Ajdin Muzaka ( ? - 1444 ) was the brother in law of George Kastrioti Skanderbeg and one of his commanders .

Manohar Nath Kaul ( 27 May 1923 - 21 August 2009 ) was a Kashmiri Pandit politician .

Gudmund Grytøyr ( born 15 July 1920 in Sør - Varanger died 21 July 2001 ) was a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party .
Gojko Šušak ( pronounced ( gȏːjko ʃûʃak ) ; 16 March 1945 -- 3 May 1998 ) was a Croatian politician who held the post of defence minister from 1991 to 1998 .

Maisie Shiell ( 1916 - -2008 ) became involved in anti - nuclear issues in 1976 when public concern developed about a new uranium mine in Saskatchewan .

Charles Fane , 1st Viscount Fane PC ( Ire ) ( January 1676 -- 4 July 1744 ) was an Anglo - Irish courtier , politician and a landowner in both England and Ireland .

Ats Bonninga ( fl . 1494 ) , was a Dutch noble , known for her defence of the fortress in Warns in Gaasterland during the conflict between the Schieringers and the Vetkopers party in 1494 .
Margarito or Margaritone d'Arezzo ( fl . c. 1250 - -1290 ) was an Italian painter from Arezzo .

Richard Badiley ( c. 1616 -- 7 or 11 August 1656 ) was an English naval officer .

Rev. Augustine Kirwan , D.D. , 1724 -- 7 August 1791 .
William Burge ( 1786 -- 12 November 1849 ) was a British lawyer and Privy Councillor .

William Cairnes ( c. 1669 -- August 1707 ) was an Irish politician and merchant .
Les Frauenfelder ( 26 February 1888 -- 26 July 1955 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Obaysch ( 1849?- 11 March 1878 ) was the first hippopotamus seen in Great Britain since prehistoric times , and the first in Europe since Ancient Rome .
Friedrich Wilhelm von Dossow ( 17 December 1669 -- 28 March 1758 ) was a Prussian Generalfeldmarschall and Governor of Wesel .
Joseph Cassey Bustill ( 1822 - -1895 ) was an African American conductor in the Underground Railroad .
Francis Gurney du Pont ( 1850 - -1904 ) was the creator of smokeless gunpowder .
Jang Bogo ( 787 - 846 , alternately 841 ) , also known as Gungbok , rose to prominence in Korea in the late Unified Silla period as a powerful maritime figure who for several decades effectively controlled the West Sea ( Yellow Sea ) and Korean coast between southwestern Korea and China 's Shandong peninsula .
Francisco Hurtado Izquierdo ( 10 February 1669 -- 30 June 1725 ) was a Spanish architect of the baroque period , author of the Sancta Sanctorum ( sacristy ) in the Granada Charterhouse .
