Pierre Vallières ( 22 February 1938 -- 23 December 1998 ) , was a Canadian journalist and writer from the province of Québec .
Freda Bedi ( sometimes spelled Frida Bedi , also named Sister Palmo , or Gelongma Karma Kechog Palmo ) ( 5 February 1911 -- 26 March 1977 ) was a British woman born in Derby , England , who became famous as the first Western woman to take ordination in Tibetan Buddhism .
Austin Osman Spare ( 30 December 1886 -- 15 May 1956 ) was an English artist and occultist who worked as both a draughtsman and a painter .
Giovanni Paisiello ( or Paesiello ; 9 May 1740 -- 5 June 1816 ) was an Italian composer of the Classical era .
John Fitling ( died 1434 ) , of Kingston upon Hull , Yorkshire , was an English politician and merchant .
Ferdinand Kovačević ( 1838 - -1913 ) was a Croatian inventor , engineer , and pioneer in telegraphy who originated from Gospić .
G. H. Elliott ( November 1882 - -19 November 1962 ) was a British music hall singer and dancer .
James Mundell ( died 1762 ) was a Scottish educator .
Sun Yefang ( Chinese : 孙冶方 ; 1908 - -1983 ) was a pioneering Chinese economist .
James Douglas , Earl of Angus ( 1671 -- 3 August 1692 ) was a Scottish nobleman and soldier .
Richard Lichfield ( died 1630 ) was a barber surgeon in Cambridge , England , during the late 16th and early 17th century .
David Cushman Coyle ( 1887 - -1969 ) was an American structural engineer , economist , and writer .
Arthur Hambling ( 14 March 1888 -- 6 December 1952 ) was a British actor , he was best known for appearances in the films Henry V ( 1944 ) and The Lavender Hill Mob ( 1951 ) .
Samuel Morse Felton , Sr . ( 1809 - -1889 ) was a civil engineer and railroad executive .
Tamara Shakryl ( 1925 or 1926 -- 12 November 2004 ) was a linguist , academic and human rights activist from Abkhazia .
Colonel Kyi Maung ( Burmese : ကြည်မောင် , pronounced : ( tɕì màʊɴ ) ; 20 December 1940 -- 19 August 2004 ) was a Burmese Army officer and politician .
Yusuf Ma Dexin ( also Ma Tesing ; 1794 - -1874 ) was a Hui Chinese scholar of Islam from Yunnan , known for his fluency and proficiency in both Arabic and Persian , and for his knowledge of Islam .
Marco Donat - Cattin ( 28 September 1953 - 19 June 1988 ) was an Italian terrorist .
Hargrave Jennings ( 1817 - 1890 ) was a British Freemason , Rosicrucian , author on occultism and esotericism , and amateur student of comparative religion .
John Crickmere ( 1822- Oxford 20 September 1846 ) was an English steeplechase jockey who took part in the Grand National steeplechase four times during the 1840s , finishing in the first four on each occasion and winning the race on Discount ( racehorse ) in 1844 .
Sir Samuel Gluckstein ( 28 September 1880 -- 19 August 1958 ) was a British solicitor and politician .
George Abraham von Dyhrn , 1st Baron of Dyhrn ( 1620 - -1671 ) , was an Austrian Chancellor in the province of Silesia , politician and a landowner in the Habsburg monarchy .
Isoda Koryūsai ( 礒田湖龍斎 1735 - -1790 ) was a Japanese ukiyo - e printmaker and painter active from 1769 to 1790 .
Brigadier Anne Field , CB , ADC Hon ( née Hodgson ; 4 April 1926 -- 25 June 2011 ) was a senior British military officer .
Thomas Dunckerley ( 23 October 1724 -- 19 November 1795 ) was a prominent freemason , being appointed Provincial Grand Master of several provinces , promoting Royal Arch masonry , introducing Mark Masonry to England , and instituting a national body for Templar masonry .
Bernat Martínez Mas ( 10 January 1980 -- 19 July 2015 ) was a Spanish motorcycle racer .
John Adam Day ( 6 July 1901 -- 7 June 1966 ) , was a British Liberal Party parliamentary candidate who later became a prominent Conservative in Devon local government .
Ya'akov Nitzani ( Hebrew : יעקב ניצני‎ , born Ya'akov Chechik ; 6 December 1900 -- 15 September 1962 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapai from 1952 until 1959 .
Bartol Gyurgieuvits ( also Bartol Jurjevic or Gjurgjevic ) ( 1506 - -1566 ) was a Croatian musicologist and lexicographer born in Turopolje near Zagreb .
Arthur Pomeroy , 1st Viscount Harberton ( 16 January 1723 -- 9/11 April 1798 ) was an Irish politician .
Martin Divilly ( died August 1979 ) was Mayor of Galway from 1963 to 1964 and from 1970 to 1971 .
Spasoje Hadži Popović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Спасоје Хаџи Поповић ; 18 August 1882 -- 3 July 1926 ) was a Serbian teacher in Bitola and newspaper editor of Južne Zvezde ( Southern Stars ) .
Alice Drew Chenoweth ( 1903 - -1998 ) was a physician who specialized in pediatrics and public health , and served as the Chief of the Division of Health Services in the United States Children 's Bureau .
Clement King Shorter ( 19 July 1857 -- 19 November 1926 ) was a British journalist and literary critic .
William J. Durham ( 1896 - 1970 ) was a resident of Sherman , Texas for much of his life .
Stanford Mark Juddery ( 9 March 1971 -- 13 January 2015 ) was an Australian freelance journalist , author , humorist and columnist for The Canberra Times .
Annibale Zoilo ( c. 1537 - -1592 ) was an Italian composer and singer of the late Renaissance Roman School .
Jacqueline Moss ( 1927 - -2005 ) was an American art historian , lecturer , writer and art critic .
Sir Robert Holborne ( died 1647 ) was an English lawyer and politician , of Furnival 's Inn and Lincoln 's Inn ( where he was bencher and reader in English law ) .
John Herbert Harington ( died 9 April 1828 ) was a British orientalist and judge .
Eugen de Haën ( 26 December 1835 -- 16 November 1911 ) was a German chemist and founder of the chemistry factory E. de Haën .
Oliver St John , 3rd Baron St John of Bletso ( c. 1540 - -1618 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1588 until 1596 when he inherited the peerage as Baron St John of Bletso .
Benjamin Hawkshaw ( died 1738 ) was an Irish Anglican divine .
Edward Byng ( ca . 1676 -- 1753 ) , sometimes spelt Bing , was an English portrait artist .
Lena Constante ( June 18 , 1909 -- November 2005 ) was a Romanian artist , essayist and memoirist , known for her work in stage design and tapestry .
Dino Shafeek ( born Gholam D. Shafeek , 21 March 1930 -- 10 March 1984 ) was a Bangladeshi actor and comedian based in the United Kingdom and the star or co - star of several popular English TV comedies during the 1970s and early 1980s .
Leo Schamroth ( 2 June 1924 , Belgium -- 24 May 1988 , Johannesburg ) was a South African cardiologist remembered for his work in electrocardiography and for describing Schamroth 's window test .
Jamyang Shakya Gyaltsen ( Tibetan : འཇམ་དབྱངས་ཤ་ཀྱ་རྒྱལ་མཚན , Wylie : aJam dbyangs sha kya rgyal mts'an , 1340 - -1373 ) was a ruler of Central Tibet in 1364 - -1373 .
Danny Guinane ( 18 May 1911 -- 28 August 1992 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Ita Martadinata Haryono was an Indonesian human rights activist , who was murdered in 1998 , a case which is still unsolved .
John Ó Madadhan , Lord of Síol Anmchadha and Chief of the Name , died 1556 .
Riccardo Paletti ( 15 June 1958 -- 13 June 1982 ) was an Italian motor racing driver .
Anne Hamilton , Countess of Huntly ( c.1535 -- after 17 April 1574 ) , was a Scottish noblewoman and a member of the powerful Hamilton family which had a strong claim to the Scottish crown .
Peter Foulger ( His surname is often spelled `` Folger , '' which was the form used by his descendants ; 1617 - -1690 ) was a poet and an interpreter of the American Indian language for the first settlers of Nantucket .
Julius Anatolyevich Schrader , OP ( 28 October 1927 -- 24 August 1998 ) was a mathematician , cyberneticist , philosopher , and a convert to Roman Catholicism .
Leopold Quehl ( 1849 - -1922 , Halle an der Saale ) was a German amateur botanist who specialized in Cactaceae .
Deshabandu N. H. Keerthiratne ( 7 November 1902 - 15 November 1992 ) was a distinguished Sri Lankan politician , philanthropist , and Cabinet Minister of Posts and Broadcasting .
James Sandilands , 7th Lord Torphichen ( died 1753 ) was a Scottish nobleman and army officer , a loyalist of the 1715 Jacobite Rebellion .
Tiburzio di Maso ( executed 31 October 1460 ) was a leader of an anarchic faction in Rome that briefly attempted to restore the medieval commune of the city , the last attempt at populist government in the States of the Church .
John Poulett , 4th Earl Poulett KT ( 3 April 1756 -- 14 January 1819 ) , styled Viscount Hinton between 1764 and 1788 , was a British peer and militia officer .
John David Hennessey ( 1847 -- 31 July 1935 ) , also known as Rev. J. D. Hennessey and David Hennessey , journalist and author , was born in London and went to Australia in 1875 .
Sir Faithful Fortescue ( 1581?--1666 ) , was a royalist commander during the English Civil War .
Professor Charles Ernest Fay ( 1846 - -1931 ) was an American alpinist and educator .
Elizabeth Fetzer Bates ( 1909 - -1999 ) was a Latter - day Saint musician , most noted for being the author of the children 's song `` Book of Mormon Stories '' .
Emma Nicol ( 1800 -- 2 November 1877 ) was a British actress who became known for playing older women in Edinburgh as her mother had before her .
Henry Joseph Woodside ( 1858 - -November 8 , 1929 ) was a Canadian businessman , journalist , writer , and photographer .
Sir George Fleming , 2nd Baronet ( 1667 -- 2 July 1747 ) was a British churchman .
Grigory Dmitriyevich Stroganov ( Russian : Григорий Дмитриевич Строганов ) ( 1656 -- 21 November 1715 ) was a Russian landowner and statesman , the most notable member of the prominent Stroganov family in the late 17th century - early 18th century , a strong supporter of the reforms and initiatives of Peter the Great .
Herbert Welsh ( December 4 , 1851 -- 1941 ) was a United States political reformer and worker for the welfare of the indigenous peoples of North America .
James Henry Hurdis ( 1800 - 1857 ) was an amateur artist and the elder son of James Hurdis , a renowned professor of poetry .
Sir George Reeves - Smith ( 17 July 1863 -- 29 May 1941 ) was an English hotelier .
John L. Behler ( 1946 - -2006 ) was an American naturalist , herpetologist , author , and activist known for his work in conserving endangered species of turtles , snakes , and other reptiles .
Martha Stearns Marshall ( 1726 - -1754 ) was a Separate Baptist preacher in the Southern United States .
Al-'Abbas ibn ' Amr al - Ghanawi ( Arabic : العباس بن عمرو الغنوي‎ ) ( died 917 ) was a military commander and provincial governor for the Abbasid dynasty .
Saint Wulfric , otherwise Wulfric of Haselbury ( c.1080 ( ? ) --20 February 1154 ) was an anchorite and miracle worker in Wiltshire and Somerset , England , frequently visited by King Stephen .
Daniel Rees ( 8 February 1793 -- 13 June 1857 ) was a Welsh clergyman and hymnwriter .
Roger Rees ( 5 May 1944 -- 10 July 2015 ) was a Welsh actor and director , widely known for his stage work .
Pery Burge ( 1955 -- 10 February 2013 ) was an English artist who , during the 2000s , worked with abstract images using ink in water or ink on paper , invoking natural processes such as surface tension driven flow , gravity , turbulence , rotation and erosion .
Leonidas Kestekides ( 1876 - 1954 ) was a Greek chocolate manufacturer , founder of the internationally famous Leonidas company in Belgium .
Archie Sam ( 30 June 1914 -- 23 May 1986 ) was a Natchez - Cherokee - Muscogee Creek traditionalist , stomp dance leader , scholar , enrolled member of the United Keetoowah Band of Cherokee Indians , and the Sun Chief of the Natchez Nation .
Pamela Hinkson ( 19 November 1900 -- 26 May 1982 ) was an Anglo - Irish writer , the daughter of Katharine Tynan and barrister Henry Albert Hinkson ( 1865 - -1919 ) .
Beatrice Harrison ( 9 December 1892 -- 10 March 1965 ) was a British cellist active in the first half of the 20th century .
Sigismondo di Giovanni ( died 1540 ) was an Italian architect in Naples , Italy , working in the Renaissance style .
Richard Drake of Esher ( 1535 -- 11 July 1603 ) , was Equerry of the Stable and Groom of the Privy Chamber to Queen Elizabeth I. He also held office as a Member of Parliament and Justice of the Peace .
Zhao Jiliang ( 趙季良 ) ( d. 946 ) , courtesy name Dezhang ( 德彰 ) , was an official of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period states Jin , Later Tang , and Later Shu , serving as a chancellor during Later Shu .
Shirley Fleming ( 1929 -- 10 March 2005 ) was an American music critic and editor .
Alice Magaw ( 1860 - -1928 ) was an American nurse known for her work on anesthesia .
Frederick Smeeton Williams ( 1829 -- 26 October 1886 ) was an English minister in the Congregational Church , best known for his books on the early history of UK railways .
Julius Schaub ( 20 August 1898 -- 27 December 1967 ) was the chief aide and adjutant to German dictator Adolf Hitler up until the dictator 's suicide on 30 April 1945 .
Rowland Detrosier , also Rowley Barnes , ( c. 1800 - 23 November 1834 ) was an English autodidact , radical politician , preacher and educator , particularly associated with Manchester .
Jules Cantini ( 1826 - -1916 ) was a French sculptor and philanthropist .
Manfred von Ardenne ( 20 January 1907 -- 26 May 1997 ) was a German research and applied physicist and inventor .
Eligius Pruystinck ( fl . 1525 -- 24 October 1544 ) was a Dutch slater who became leader of a radical Anabaptist faction in Antwerp .
Ratko Vujović ( 16 December 1916 -- 29 October 1977 ) was a Montenegrin political activist and soldier .
Evaristo Garbani - Nerini ( 26 October 1867 -- 16 February 1944 ) was Swiss politician and president of the Swiss National Council ( 1920/1921 ) .
John of Arkel or Jan van Arkel ( 1314 -- Liège , 1 July 1378 ) was a Bishop of Utrecht from 1342 to 1364 and Prince - Bishop of Liège from 1364 to 1378 .
John Hooker Leavitt ( 1831 - -1906 ) was an early banker and Iowa state senator who was born at Heath , Massachusetts , but who later moved westward to Iowa in search of fortune .
Albert Willimsky ( 29 December 1890 - -22 February 1940 ) was a German Roman Catholic priest active in resistance movement against the National Socialism , martyred in the Sachsenhausen concentration camp .
Robert Dundas of Arniston , the younger FRSE ( 1713 - -1787 ) was a Scottish judge .
Gladys Ewart ( 1892 -- 19 July 1957 ) was a Canadian pianist and music educator .
Nigoghos Sarafian ( Armenian : Նիկողոս Սարաֆեան , 1905 in Varna , Principality of Bulgaria - 1973 in Paris , France ) , was an Armenian writer , poet , editor , and journalist .
Mashel Teitelbaum ( 1921 - -1985 ) ( variant name Mashel Alexander Teitelbaum ) was a Canadian painter , born in Saskatoon , Saskatchewan in 1921 .
Johann Ulich , the younger ( Wittenberg , 1677-Zerbst , 1742 ) was a German organist and composer in Zerbst , and music teacher to the princely family .
Cao Xiu ( died 228 ) , courtesy name Wenlie , was a military general serving under the warlord Cao Cao in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
Arthur St Leger , 2nd Viscount Doneraile ( c. 1695 -- 13 March 1734 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and peer .
Jasper Ridley ( 25 May 1920 -- 1 July 2004 ) was a British writer , known for historical biographies .
Giorgi Antsukhelidze ( Georgian : გიორგი ანწუხელიძე ; 18 August 1984 -- c. 9 - -10 August 2008 ) was a Georgian soldier who was killed during the hostilities in South Ossetia in the course of the Russia--
Stewart Mulvey ( May 1834 -- 26 May 1908 ) was a Canadian teacher , newspaper editor , militia officer , office holder and politician .
Ormonde Maddock Dalton ( 1866 - -1945 ) was a British museum curator and archaeologist .
Ángel Alcázar de Velasco ( Mondéjar , 1909 -- Galapagar , 2001 ) was an apprentice bullfighter , Falangist , journalist and spy .
Charles Fremont Dight ( 1856 - -1938 ) was medical professor and promoter of the human eugenics movement in Minnesota .
John Man ( 1512 - -1569 ) was an English churchman , college head , and diplomat .
Cerverí de Girona ( Catalan pronunciation : ( sərβəˈɾi ðə ʒiˈɾonə ) ) ( fl . 1259 - -1285 ) was a Catalan troubadour born Guillem de Cervera in Girona .
Grand Ayatollah Sayyid Morteza Hosseini Fayaz ( 9 April 1929 - 20 August 2014 , Arabic : السيد مرتضى الحسيني فياض ) was an Iraqi Twelver Shi'a Marja .
Sir Thomas Jamieson Boyd DL FRSE ( 1818 - -1902 ) publisher and philanthropist , was Lord Provost of Edinburgh from 1877 to 1882 .
Nicolaus Copernicus ( /koʊˈpɜːrnɪkəs , kə-/ ; Polish : Mikołaj Kopernik ( miˈkɔwaj kɔˈpɛrɲik ) ; German : Nikolaus Kopernikus ; 19 February 1473 -- 24 May 1543 ) was a Renaissance mathematician and astronomer who formulated a model of the universe that placed the Sun rather than the Earth at the center of the universe .
Francis Jeffrey , Lord Jeffrey ( 23 October 1773 -- 26 January 1850 ) was a Scottish judge and literary critic .
James Cecil , 1st Marquess of Salisbury , KG PC ( 4 September 1748 -- 13 June 1823 ) , styled Viscount Cranborne until 1780 and known as The Earl of Salisbury between 1780 and 1789 , was a British politician .
Amy Catherine Walton ( 9 August 1849 -- 1939 ) , better known as Mrs O. F. Walton , was a British author of Christian children 's books , mainly but not exclusively fiction .
Yukhym Medvedev ( Ukrainian : Юхим Медведєв , Russian : Ефим Григорьевич Медведев ) ( 1 April 1886 - -7 June 1938 ) was the first elected chairman of the Soviet parliament in Ukraine .
Su Gang ( Chinese : 苏钢 ) ( 1920 - -2002 ) was a People 's Republic of China politician .
Pirro Colonna ( 1500 -- November 1552 ) was an Italian military leader in the service of Charles V during the Italian War of 1542 .
Sir William Cameron Gull , 2nd Baronet OBE MP JP ( 6 January 1860 -- 15 December 1922 ) , known as Sir Cameron Gull , was a barrister and Liberal Unionist politician in England , who served for five years as a member of parliament ( MP ) .
Henry Collins Brown ( 1862 - 1961 ) was a Scottish - born New York historian , lecturer , and author .
Abel Pann ( 1883 - -1963 ) , born Abba Pfeffermann in Latvia or in Kreslawka , Vitebsk , Belarus , sources vary , was a European Jewish artist who spent most of his adult life in Jerusalem .
Hugh II , Count of Rethel ( died 1227 ) was a son of Manasses IV and his wife , Matilda of Kyrburg .
Otto Schmirgal ( 15 December 1900 -- 24 October 1944 ) was a German workman , politician , and a resistance fighter against the Nazi régime .
T. Abdul Rahman ( Malayalam : ടി. അബ്ദുല്‍ റഹ്‌മാന്‍ ) ( 1934 -- 15 December 2002 ) , popularly known as Olympian Rahman , was an Indian Olympian footballer from Kozhikode , Kerala .
Radie Britain ( 17 March 1899 -- 23 May 1994 ) was an American pianist , writer , music educator and composer .
Michel Marcel Navratil , Jr. ( 12 June 1908 -- 30 January 2001 ) was one of the last survivors of the sinking of Titanic on 15 April 1912 .
Binka Zhelyazkova ( Bulgarian : Бинка Желязкова , 15 July 1923 -- 31 July 2011 ) , was a Bulgarian film director who made films between the late 1950s and the 1990s .
Wei Shifang ( 韋什方 ) ( died 695 ) , also known as Wu Shifang ( 武什方 ) , was briefly a chancellor during Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty .
Ewart Smith OBE ( 1920 -- 1991 ) was an Australian public servant .
Đuraš Ilijić ( Serbian : Ђураш Илијић , fl . 1326 - -62 ) was a nobleman that served the Serbian monarchs Stefan Dečanski ( r. 1321 - -1331 ) , Stefan Dušan ( r. 1331 - -1355 ) and Uroš V ( r. 1355 - -1371 ) , from 1326 until his death in 1362 .
Alfredo Catalani ( 19 June 1854 -- 7 August 1893 ) was an Italian operatic composer .
Fra Damiano da Bergamo ( Damiano di Antoniolo de Zambelli ) ( circa 1480 - -1549 ) was an Italian artist and Dominican monk , mainly known for his wood - engraving and intarsia completed in a Renaissance style .
Annie Marion MacLean ( 1869 - -1934 ) was a pioneering American sociologist of the women 's Chicago School , and is sometimes referred to as the `` mother of contemporary ethnography . ''
Louisa Anne Meredith ( 20 July 1812 -- 21 October 1895 ) , also known as Louisa Anne Twamley , was an Anglo / Australian writer and illustrator .
Prince Luiz Gastão of Orléans - Braganza ( Portuguese : Príncipe Luiz Gastão Antônio Maria Filipe de Orleans e Bragança ; 19 February 1911 -- 8 September 1931 ) was a member of the House of Orléans - Braganza , and was descended from the Brazilian Imperial Family .
Julius Waring Walker , Jr. ( February 21 , 1927 -- December 5 , 2003 ) was an American diplomat and United States Ambassador to Upper Volta ( now Burkina Faso ) from 1981 to 1984 .
John Hilsey ( aka Hildesley or Hildesleigh ; died 4 August 1539 ) was an English Dominican , prior provincial of his order , then an agent of Henry VIII and his church reformation , and Bishop of Rochester .
Ishwor Ballav ( Nepali : ईश्वरबल्लभ , 11 July 1937 -- 22 March 2008 ) is one of the most influential Nepali poet .
Xu Jingcheng ( Chinese : 許景澄 ; 1845 -- 28 July 1900 ) was a Chinese diplomat and Qing politician supportive of the Hundred Days ' Reform .
Jędrzej Kitowicz ( 1727 or 1728 -- 3 April 1804 ) was a Polish historian and diarist .
André Kertész ( French : ( kɛʁtɛs ) ; 2 July 1894 -- 28 September 1985 ) , born Kertész Andor , was a Hungarian - born photographer known for his groundbreaking contributions to photographic composition and the photo essay .
Urtaku was an Elamite king who reigned from 676 - -664 BCE .
Luigi Lavitrano ( 7 March 1874 -- 2 August 1950 ) was an Italian Cardinal of the Catholic Church who served as Archbishop of Palermo from 1928 to 1944 , and as Prefect of the Sacred Congregation for Religious from 1945 until his death .
Dawit Amanuel ( 1862 -- 1944 ) is noted in Ethiopian and Eritrean church history as being the main translator of the New Testament in the Tigre language , published in 1902 .
Guy Byam - Corstiaens ( died 3 February 1945 ) was a British journalist and sailor .
Sir Samuel Roberts , 2nd Baronet JP ( 2 September 1882 -- 13 December 1955 ) was a British politician .
Zygmunt Milczewski ( 1 October 1905 -- 2 June 2001 ) was a Polish historian associated with Pomerania , a community leader in the Second Polish Republic , and World War II resistance fighter in the underground Home Army ( Armia Krajowa ) with the postwar rank of Lieutenant ( porucznik ) .
Johan Brautigam ( 18 May 1878 , Uithoorn - 24 June 1962 , Rotterdam ) was a Dutch trade unionist and politician .
Sidney Hunt ( 1896 - -1940 ) was a British draughtsman , painter , poet and editor who published the avant - garde journal Ray between 1926 and 1927 .
The Great Omani ( 10 July 1915 -- 15 October 2007 ) , real name Ronald Cunningham , was one of the oldest recorded escapologists and stuntmen .
Nicolae Secăreanu ( 12 July 1901 - 29 September 1992 ) was a well - known Romanian opera singer and actor .
Kang Mun - sok ( 1906 - 1955 ) was a Korean socialist activist during the Japanese occupation period and thereafter .
Dr. Jenő Hammersberg ( 14 March 1845 -- 20 February 1918 ) was a Hungarian politician and lawyer , who served as Crown Prosecutor of Hungary from 1896 to 1902 .
Carl Alexander Gibson - Hill ( 23 October 1911 - 18 August 1963 ) was a British medical doctor , naturalist , ornithologist and curator of Singapore 's Raffles Museum .
Samdup Taso ( b. 1928 ; d. 29 October 2011 , aged 83 ) was the last shaman to lead the indigenous Lepcha people of Sikkim ( now part of India ) in prayers to the mountain deity of Kanchenjunga , the world 's third - highest mountain peak .
Jin Au Kong ( Traditional Chinese : 孔金甌 ; Simplified Chinese : 孔金瓯 ) , ( 27 December 1942 -- 13 March 2008 ) was an American expert in applied electromagnetics .
Mary Lum Girard ( 1758 - -1815 ) Mary Lum ( otherwise known as Mary Girard ) is known for being the wife of banker , philanthropist and merchant millionaire Stephen Girard .
George Bugg ( 1769 - -1851 ) was an Anglican deacon and curate for several churches in England and a scriptural geologist who wrote a two volume book called Scriptural Geology .
Jacob Swoope ( ca . 1770 -- 1832 ) was an eighteenth and nineteenth century politician from Virginia .
Panagiotis Toundas ( Greek : Παναγιώτης Τούντας ; 1886 - -1942 ) was a Greek composer of the early 20th century .
Charles Yale Harrison ( 16 June 1898 - -17 March 1954 ) was a Canadian author and journalist , best known for his 1930 anti - war novella Generals Die in Bed .
Miriam Waddington ( née Dworkin , 23 December 1917 -- 3 March 2004 ) was a Canadian poet , short story writer and translator .
Sir Hugh Acland , 6th Baronet ( 26 January 1697 -- 29 July 1728 ) was the son of John Acland and Elizabeth Acland .
Hans Wolter ( 11 May 1911 -- 17 August 1978 ) was a German physicist who designed an aplanatic system of grazing incidence mirrors that satisfied the Abbe sine condition ( i.e. free of both spherical aberration and coma ) .
John Baskett ( 1664/5 -- 1742 ) , was the king 's printer .
Angus Robertson Fulton ( 1871 - -1958 ) was a Scottish Engineer and Academic who served as ' Interim ' Principal of University College Dundee for seven years .
William Watkiss Lloyd ( 11 March 1813 -- 22 December 1893 ) , was an English writer with an interest in fine art , architecture , archaeology , Shakespeare , and classical and modern languages and literature .
Arthur Tashko ( 1901 - 1994 ) was an Albanian born in Korçë , in the Manastir Vilayet of the Ottoman Empire ( present - day Albania ) 10 April 1901 , an American modern painter , lawyer and musician .
John Long Wilson ( 1914 - -2001 ) was a medical professor and administrator at American University of Beirut , Lebanon , and at Stanford University .
Pedro Rodríguez de Castro ( fl . 1171 - -1191 ) , second son of Rodrigo Fernández de Castro the bald and Eylo Álvarez , daughter of Álvar Fáñez , and of the Countess Mayor Perez , was a Castilian ricohombre of the lineage of the Castro .
Ralph Corbie ( Corby , Corbington , at times Corrington ) ( 25 March 1598 - 7 September 1644 ) was an Irish Jesuit .
James Mure - Campbell , 5th Earl of Loudoun ( 11 February 1726 -- 28 April 1786 ) was a Scottish aristocrat and soldier .
Hoca Ishak Efendi ( Arta ca . 1774 -- Suez 1835 ) was an Ottoman mathematician and engineer .
Nop Bophann ( died 1959 ) was a Cambodian newspaper editor .
Sir Arthur Leycester Scott Coltman ( 24 May 1938 -- 2003 ) , known as Leycester Coltman , was the British ambassador to Cuba from 1991 to 1994 .
Rosina von Graben von Rain zu Sommeregg , also called Rosina von Rain ( 15th century -- 1534 ( ? ) ) was an Austrian noble woman descending from the House of Graben von Stein , a cadet branch of the Meinhardiner dynasty .
Bodil Katharine Biørn ( 27 May 1871 -- 22 July 1960 ) , also known as Mother Katharine , was a Norwegian missionary .
Radomiro Tomic Romero ( 7 May 1914 -- 3 January 1992 ) was a Chilean politician of Croatian origin .
Alfredo Malerba ( 24 September 1909 in Rosario - 9 January 1994 in Mexico ) was an Argentine pianist and musician , producer and screenwriter , with an illustrious career .
Christopher Kempster ( 1627 -- 1715 ) was an English master stonemason and architect who trained with Sir Christopher Wren , working on St Paul 's Cathedral .
Charles Abbott , 1st Baron Tenterden PC SL ( 7 October 1762 -- 4 November 1832 ) , was a British barrister and judge who served as Lord Chief Justice of the King 's Bench between 1818 and 1832 .
Enrico di Robilant ( 1924 - 10 October 2012 ) was an Italian philosopher of law .
John William Hayward ( 1844 - -1913 ) is a Newfoundland artist and inventor .
Zelimkhan Yaqub ( Azerbaijani : Zəlimxan Yaqub ; 21 January 1950 -- 9 January 2016 ) was an Azerbaijani poet .
Reginald of Burgundy ( died 1321 ) was Count of Montbéliard , jure uxoris , from 1282 to 1321 .
Luo Tong ( 193 - -228 ) , courtesy name Gongxu , was an official serving under the warlord Sun Quan in the late Eastern Han dynasty and early Three Kingdoms period .
John Alcindor ( 8 or 9 July 1873 - -25 October 1924 ) was a physician from Trinidad who settled in London .
Giovanni Battista Crosato ( 1686 - July 15 , 1758 ) was an Italian painter of quadratura , active in the 18th - century in Piedmont .
William Frederick Bailey PC ( 9 February 1857 -- 16 April 1917 ) , was an Irish lawyer and writer .
Henry John Hatch ( 1818 - -1895 ) was a British clergyman who was sent to prison for the indecent assault of two female children in his care .
Emily Inez Denny ( December 23 , 1853 - August 23 , 1918 ) was a painter who drew scenes from Seattle 's early history .
Francesco Antonio Franzoni ( 1734 - -1818 ) was an Italian sculptor and restorer .
Adolf Froelich ( December 24 , 1887 -- November 1943 ) was a Polish inventor , dentist and participant in the Polish - Soviet War .
Leib Glantz ( Yiddish : לייב גלאנץ‎ ; June 1 , 1898 - January 27 , 1964 ) was a Ukrainian - born lyrical tenor cantor ( chazzan ) , Composer , Musicologist of Jewish music , Writer , Educator and Zionist leader .
Richard Ullerston DD ( died August or September 1423 ) was a Vice - Chancellor and Chancellor of Oxford University .
Hugo Fredrik Hjorthøy ( 9 May 1741 -- 29 August 1812 ) was a Norwegian priest and topographer .
Leo Francis ( 4 December 1922 -- 13 December 2003 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thomas Byers Huling ( 1804 -- 1865 ) , was a businessman who , along with Henry Millard and Joseph Pulsifer , helped lay out the original plans for Beaumont , Texas .
Thomas Rackett ( 1757 - -1841 ) was an English clergyman , known as an antiquary .
Luis Napoleón Morones ( 1890 -- 1964 ) was a Mexican union boss who served as secretary general of the Regional Confederation of Mexican Workers ( Confederación Regional Obrera Mexicana , CROM ) and as secretary of economy under President Plutarco Elías Calles , 1924 - 1928 .
Yacoub Artin ( 15 April 1842 - 21 January 1919 ) was an Ethnic Armenian educator and scholar working in Egypt .
Manuel Saumell Robredo ( 19 April 1818 -- 14 August 1870 ) , was a Cuban composer known for his invention and development of genuinely creolized forms of music .
Nilamani Routray ( Odia : ନୀଳମଣି ରାଉତରାୟ ) ( 24 May 1920 -- 4 October 2004 ) was an Indian politician and the Chief Minister of Odisha from 1977 to 1980 .
Per Tommy Jansson ( 2 October 1952 -- 20 May 1976 ) was a motorcycle speedway rider .
Hartmann von An der Lan - Hochbrunn , O.F.M. , ( 21 December 1863 & nsp ; 6 December 1914 ) was an Austrian Friar Minor and Catholic priest , who worked as a composer , organist and conductor .
Pietro Bonato ( 1765 - -1820 ) was an Italian painter and engraver of the Baroque .
Velmer A. Fassel ( 26 April 1919 -- 4 March 1998 ) was an American chemist who developed the inductively coupled plasma ( ICP ) and demonstrated its use as ion source for mass spectrometry .
Alexander Fry ( 10 September 1821 , Pencraig , Herefordshire −1905 ) was an English entomologist who specialised in Coleoptera .
Allen Hiram Curtiss ( 1845 - -1907 ) was a noted botanist in the United States .
Ruth L. Kirschstein , M.D. ( 12 October 1926 -- 6 October 2009 ) was a pathologist and science administrator at the National Institutes of Health ( NIH ) .
Gudō Toshoku ( 1577 - -1661 ) was a Japanese Rinzai school zen monk from the early Tokugawa period .
Harry K. Harring ( 1871 - -1928 ) was a zoologist specializing in the study of Rotatoria .
Hiltrud ( died 754 ) , was a Duchess consort of Bavaria .
Karol Langner ( June 28 , 1843 in Deutsch Piekar in Oberschlesien ( today Piekary Śląskie ) -- January 1912 in Negaunee , Michigan ) was a Polish priest and schoolmate of Jan Pitass .
Ernest François Guillaux , ( 24 January 1883 -- 21 May 1917 ) , better known by his adopted name Maurice Guillaux , was a French aviator who spent seven months in Australia in 1914 .
James Fillans ( 27 March 1808 -- 27 September 1852 ) was a Scottish sculptor , poet and artist with a short but influential career in the early 19th century .
Thomas Gardyne of Middleton and Finavon ( 1780 - -1841 ) was a Scottish laird and founder of the village of Friockheim in Angus , Scotland .
Antonio Salamanca or Martinez de Salamanca ( Salamanca , 1479 - Rome , 1562 ) was a Spaniard who settled in Rome and was active as a book - seller , publisher and engraver .
Konstantinos Triaridis ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Τριαρίδης ; c. 1937 -- 27 June 2012 ) was a Greek politician who served as Minister for Macedonia - Thrace from 1993 to 1996 .
Alonso de Benavides ( Portuguese : Afonso de Benavides ) ( c.1578 - 1635 ) was a Portuguese Franciscan missionary active in New Mexico , in the early part of the seventeenth century .
Michael Marlow ( died 1828 ) was an academic administrator at the University of Oxford and an Anglican priest .
Clement Charlton Palmer ( 1871 - 1944 ) was an cathedral organist , who served at Canterbury Cathedral .
Major - General Sir Robert Rollo Gillespie ( 21 January 1766 -- 31 October 1814 ) was an officer in the British army .
Gustavo Re ( 4 July 1908 - 5 June 1979 ) was an Italian actor who mainly worked in Spain .
Flavius Claudius Constantius Gallus ( ca . 325/326 - -354 ) , commonly known as Constantius Gallus , was a member of the Constantinian dynasty and Caesar of the Roman Empire ( 351 - -354 ) .
Richard Spurr ( 1800 - -1855 ) was an English cabinet maker and lay preacher who was imprisoned for his part in leading the political movement Chartism .
Sean Hales ( 30 March 1880 -- 7 December 1922 ) was an Irish political activist and member of Dáil Eireann in the early 20th century .
Víctor Cabedo Carda ( 15 June 1989 -- 19 September 2012 ) was a Spanish professional road racing cyclist .
Basil Christopher Butler , OSB ( 7 May 1902 -- 20 September 1986 ) was a convert from the Church of England to the Roman Catholic Church .
Bartolomé Ruiz ( Moguer , Spain c. 1482 - Cajamarca , Peru c. 1532 ) was a Spanish conquistador .
Abu Yahya ibn Abd al - Haqq ( died 1258 ? ) was a Marinid ruler .
Reinhold Wilhelm Buchholz ( 2 October 1837 , Frankfurt an der Oder -- 17 April 1876 ) was a German zoologist who made contributions in the fields of herpetology , carcinology and ichthyology .
Ransom Cook ( 1794 -- 1881 ) was an inventor who lived much of his life in Saratoga Springs , New York .
Banke Chamar was a freedom fighter who died for his actions in the Indian Rebellion of 1857 .
Reuben Atwater , also known as Reuben Attwater , ( May 11 , 1768 -- February 1831 ) was the Secretary of Michigan Territory and served as acting governor during 1811 - -1812 .
John Joe McGee ( died 2002 , Dundalk , County Louth , Ireland ) was an IRA volunteer who was formerly in the British Special Boat Service .
Donn mac Cumasgach , King of Maigh Seóla ? , died 752 .
Dr Reginald Spencer Ellery ( 1897 - 1955 ) , was a pioneer in the practice of psychiatry in Melbourne , Australia .
Dora Birtles ( 1903 - -1992 , née Toll ) , was an Australian novelist , short - story writer , poet and travel writer .
John Dobbie ( died 1952 ) was a popular Australian actor of theatre and film .
Francisco da Costa Gomes , ComTE , GOA ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( fɾɐ̃ˈsiʃku dɐ ˈkɔʃtɐ ˈɡomɨʃ ) ; 30 June 1914 , in Chaves -- 31 July 2001 , in Lisbon , Lapa ) was a Portuguese military officer and politician , the 15th President of the Portuguese Republic ( the second after the Carnation Revolution ) .
John Hudson Thomas ( 1878 - 1945 ) was an American architect who practiced in the northern California area .
Christopher Tancred ( 8 April 1659 -- 22 November 1705 ) , of Whixley in Yorkshire , was Member of Parliament for Aldborough from 1689 to 1698 .
Mary Morison or Mary Morrison ( 1771 -- 29 June 1791 ) , may have been the `` lovely Mary Morison '' , whom the poet Robert Burns admired as a girl of sixteen .
Dorothy Lonewolf Miller ( 1920 - 2003 ) was a Blackfoot activist from Iowa .
Vernon March died of pneumonia at age 38 on 11 June 1930 in Farnborough , Kent , England .
Sascha Jacobsen ( Helsinki , Finland , 11 December ( O.S. 29 November ) 1895 -- Los Angeles , California , 19 March 1972 ) was a Jewish - American violinist and teacher born in Russia , now Finland .
Mostafa Khomeini ( 12 December 1930 - -23 October 1977 ) was an Iranian cleric and the son of Ayatollah Khomeini .
John Latton ( 1484/1485 - -1548 ) , of the Inner Temple , London and Upton in Berkshire ( now Oxfordshire ) , was an English politician .
Arild Feldborg ( 18 April 1912 -- 26 October 1987 ) was a Norwegian playwright , revue writer , script writer , humorist and broadcasting person .
Thierry Manoncourt ( September 1917 , -- 27 August 2010 ) was a French winery owner of the Grand Cru estate Château Figeac in Bordeaux , and for many decades a major figure of Bordeaux and the Saint - Émilion appellation .
William Croome ( 1790 - -1860 ) was an American illustrator and wood engraver in the 19th century .
Derek Deadman ( 11 March 1940 -- 22 November 2014 ) was a British character actor who appeared in numerous British films and television series over a 40-year period .
Abu Yaqub al - Masri also known as Zakkariya ( The Doctor ) and labeled `` The Emir of Taji '' ( died 31 August 2007 ) was the organizer of the 23 November 2006 Sadr City bombings .
Lieutenant General Sir John Jarvis Bisset KCMG , CB ( 25 December 1819 - 25 March 1894 ) was a British Army officer who became colonel of the 106th Regiment of Foot .
Albert Edward Jones ( 1878 - 1954 ) was an English silversmith and designer .
John Aynsley ( 1823 -- 7 February 1907 ) was an English potter who established the Portland Works in Longton , Staffordshire .
Jacques Van Melkebeke ( 12 December 1904 -- 8 June 1983 ) was a Belgian painter , journalist , writer , and comic strip writer .
Edward North , 1st Baron North ( c. 1496 - -1564 ) was an English peer and politician .
Hersleb Vogt ( 20 May 1912 -- 9 November 1999 ) was a Norwegian diplomat .
Allen Tough ( 1936 -- 27 April 2012 ) was a Canadian educator and researcher .
George Webb Slaughter ( 1811 - -1895 ) was an American Baptist minister , cattle breeder and drover , and rancher in Texas .
Hugo Sánchez Portugal ( 15 June 1984 -- 8 November 2014 ) was a Mexican footballer and sports commentator with Televisa Deportes .
John E. Richards was an associate justice of the California Supreme Court from 1924 until 1932 .
Charles Bennet , 1st Earl of Tankerville KT PC ( 1674 -- 21 May 1722 ) , known as The Lord Ossulston between 1695 and 1714 , was a British peer .
Kay Dick ( 29 July 1915 -- 19 October 2001 ) was an English journalist , writer , novelist and autobiographer , who sometimes wrote under the name Edward Lane .
James Thayer Addison ( 1887 - -1953 ) was an American Episcopalian teacher and writer .
David William Ramsay ( 1943 - 2008 ) was a Canadian lawyer and judge notorious for being sent to prison for sexual assault on minors , some of whom appeared before him in court .
Elizabeth Seymour , Duchess of Somerset and suo jure Baroness Percy ( 26 January 1667 -- 24 November 1722 ) was a great heiress .
William Jane ( 1645 - -1707 ) was an English academic and clergyman , Regius Professor of Divinity at Oxford from 1680 .
Willard Cochrane ( 1914 - 2012 ) was an agricultural economist and a leading architect of farm policy in the United States .
Hayyim Mordecai Margolioth ( mid-18th century - 1818 ) ( Hebrew : חיים מרדכי מרגליות ) was a Polish rabbi , brother of Ephraim Solomon Margolioth .
Demeter Hunyadi ( 1579 - -1592 ) was a Hungarian Unitarian .
Franz Kessler ( c. 1580 - -1650 ) was a portrait painter , scholar , inventor and alchemist living in the Holy Roman Empire during the 16th and 17th centuries .
Reba Rakshit ( Bengali : রেবা রক্ষিত ) ( - 2010 ) was an Indian bodybuilder and exponent of yoga who performed astonishing feats .
François Rauber ( 19 January 1933 -- 14 December 2003 ) was a French pianist , composer , arranger and conductor known for his works with chansonnier Jacques Brel .
Francesco Caetani , 8th Duke of Sermoneta , ( 11 March 1613 -- 9 October 1683 ) was an Italian nobleman .
Sven Ingemar Ljungh , also spelled Liungh ( 5 June 1757 , Björkö , Jönköping County - 12 September 1828 , Bälaryd , Jönköping County ) was a Swedish civil servant , naturalist and collector .
Alec John Dawson ( 1872 - 3 February 1951 ) , generally known as A. J. Dawson ( pseudonyms Major Dawson , Howard Kerr , Nicholas Freydon ) was an English author , traveller and novelist .
Reuven Dov Dessler ( 1863 - -1935 ) was a rabbinic leader of the Musar movement and the director of the Kelm Talmud Torah from 1918 until 1931 .
Sir Israel Brodie KBE ( 10 May 1895 , Newcastle -- 13 February 1979 ) was the Chief Rabbi of Great Britain and the Commonwealth 1948 - -1965 .
Marek Żuławski ( 13 April 1908 in Rome -- 30 March 1985 in London ) , was a painter and graphic artist , son of Jerzy Żuławski .
Stanisław Zając ( Polish pronunciation : ( staˈɲiswav ˈzajɔnts ) , 1 May 1949 -- 10 April 2010 ) was a Polish lawyer and politician .
Owen Morgan , also known by his bardic name Morien ( 1836 -- 16 December 1921 ) was a Welsh journalist , historian and writer of books on the subject of neo - druidism .
Maduluwawe Sobitha Thero ( Sinhalese : මාදුළුවාවේ සෝභිත හිමි ; 29 May 1942 -- 8 November 2015 ) was an influential Sinhalese Buddhist monk regarded by many , a nonviolent revolutionary .
Nicholas Georgiadis CBE ( 14 September 1923 -- 10 March 2001 ) was a Greek painter , stage and costume designer , best known for his work in ballet , particularly in collaboration with Kenneth MacMillan .
Frederick Theobold ( 1 February 1839 -- 5 January 1888 ) was an English cricketer who played for Kent .
George Abram Miller ( 31 July 1863 -- 10 February 1951 ) was an early group theorist whose many papers and texts were considered important by his contemporaries , but are now mostly considered only of historical importance .
Charles Hubert de Castella ( 27 March 1825 -- 30 October 1907 ) was a Swiss - Australian writer , artist and winemaker .
Lee Huan ( Chinese : 李煥 ; pinyin : Lǐ Huàn ; 24 September 1917 -- 2 December 2010 ) was a politician in the Republic of China .
George Noble Jones ( 1811 - -1876 ) was an American wealthy southern plantation owner who owned the El Destino Plantation and Chemonie Plantation .
Bjarne Gran ( 23 February 1918 -- 14 December 1992 ) was a Norwegian journalist , historian and literary consultant .
Balthasar Oomkens von Esens ( died 1540 ) was an East Frisian nobleman who died during the siege of his castle in Esens by the Bremen army .
James Charles Cox ( 21 July 1834 -- 29 September 1912 ) was an Australian physician and conchologist .
Pope Timothy II of Alexandria ( died 477 ) , also known as Αἴλουρος/Aelurus ( from Greek cat because of his small build or in this case probably `` weasel '' ) , succeeded twice in supplanting the Chalcedonian Patriarch of Alexandria .
George Strachan died on 29 December 1901 , at Middelburg , Transvaal , South Africa .
Elisabeth Plainacher , or Elsa Plainacher ( 1513 -- 27 September 1583 ) , was an alleged Austrian witch .
Juan Rodríguez Botas ( 1880 - -1917 ) is considered the first Canarian impressionist .
Paul Feiler ( 30 April 1918 -- 8 July 2013 ) was a German - born artist who was a prominent member of the St Ives School of art : he has pictures hanging in major art galleries across the world .
Frances Fabri , born Sárika Ladányi ( 22 September 1929 -- 9 January 2006 ) , was a Hungarian - born author and Holocaust survivor .
Jiang Shaoji ( simplified Chinese : 江绍基 ; traditional Chinese : 江紹基 ; pinyin : Jiāng Shàojī ; 1919 - -1995 ) was a Chinese internist and gastroenterologist .
Colonel John James Mellor ( 12 August 1830 -- 12 January 1916 ) was a British industrialist and Conservative politician .
John Maltravers , 1st Baron Maltravers ( 1290?--1365 ) was an English nobleman and soldier .
Teofil Pożyczka ( 1912 -- c. 1974 ) was a Polish pilot during World War II . He served as technical officer in the Centralne Warsztaty Lotnicze ( Central Aerial Works ) in the Polish September Campaign of 1939 .
George Rainsford Fairbanks ( 1820 - 1906 ) was a lawyer , Clerk of the Circuit Court , Florida State Senator , president of Florida Fruit Growers Association and the Florida Fruit Exchange ; editor of the Florida Mirror ; the author of books on Florida history ; and the founder and president of Florida Historical Society .
Friedrich Wilhelm , Prince of Wied ( German : Friedrich Wilhelm Heinrich Konstantin Fürst von Wied ; 2 June 1931 -- 28 August 2000 ) was the grandson of William Frederick , 6th Prince of Wied .
Samuel Juster , AIA , ( February 12 , 1896 -- May 1982 ) was a minor American architect who practiced in mid-20th - century New York and New Jersey .
Michalis Oikonomou ( also Mihalis Ikonomou or Michael Economou ; Greek : Μιχάλης Οικονόμου , 1888 - -1933 ) was a Greek impressionist painter .
Airlangga ( also spelled Erlangga ) , regnal name Rakai Halu Sri Lokeswara Dharmawangsa Airlangga Anantawikramottunggadewa ( born 991 in Bali , Indonesia -- died 1049 in Java ) , was the only raja of the Kingdom of Kahuripan .
Tine Bryld ( née Begtrup ; 18 December 1939 -- 21 April 2011 ) was a social worker , writer , radio personality and editor of letter to the editor pages .
Syed Zahoor Shah Hashmi ( Urdu : سید ظہور شاہ ہاشمی‎ ) ( 21 April 1926 -- 4 March 1978 ) , known as Syed Hashmi ( سید ہاشمی ) , was an academic , poet , writer , and philosopher in Pakistan who is widely regarded as having inspired the Balochi literature .
John Minshull aka Minchin ( born c.1741 ; died 23 October 1793 at Kingston upon Thames , Surrey ) was a famous English cricketer during the 1770s .
John Hatchell PC ( 1788 - -1870 ) was an Irish lawyer and politician .
John Plumb ( 6 February 1927 -- 6 April 2008 ) was an English abstract painter who emerged in Britain after World War II . Plumb was born in Luton , and he went to the Byam Shaw School in London at the age of 20 .
Jonathan H. Carter ( died 1887 ) was a North Carolina - born planter , sailor , and Confederate States of America gunboat builder .
Lisbetha Olsdotter ( died November 1679 ) was a Swedish woman , who was executed on a number of different charges after having dressed as a man , served as a soldier and married a woman .
Hans Neusidler ( also Neusiedler , Newsidler ) ( c.1508 -- 2 February 1563 ) , was a German composer and lutenist of the Renaissance .
Paolo Andreani ( 27 May 1763 -- 11 May 1823 ) was an Italian who made the first balloon flight over Italian soil .
Alleppey Sheriff , also known as A. Sheriff ( 1940 -- 2 December 2015 ) , was an Indian film script writer and director in Malayalam movies .
Richard Q. Yardley ( 1903 - 1979 ) was an editorial cartoonist for The Baltimore Sun , Maryland , United States .
Filippo Gherardi ( 1643 - -1704 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
Misbaholdiwan Adab was the pen name of Kurdish poet Abd - Allah Beg b. Ahmed Beg Babamiri , ( 1860 - -1918 ) , also known by his title Misbah al - Diwan .
Damkhat Reachea ( died 1508 ) was a Cambodian king and emperor , Thomuro Reachea uncle 's successor , which is known relatively few on his life .
Fernand Dehousse ( French : ( də.us ) ; 3 July 1906 -- 10 August 1976 ) was a Belgian politician .
Viredo Espinosa ( 1928 - 2012 ) was a Cuban Abstract Expressionist artist .
Habib Ali Kiddie ( December 7 , 1929 -- 1987 ) was a Pakistani field hockey player from 1950 to 1964 .
John Arthur Phillips FRS , FCS ( 18 February 1822 -- 5 January 1887 ) was a British geologist , metallurgist , and mining engineer .
Stefano Ronchetti - Monteviti ( 1814 - -1882 ) was an Italian composer , music educator , and college administrator .
Æthelric I ( died 1038 ) was an Anglo - Saxon Bishop of Selsey .
Charlie Dibbs ( 3 April 1905 -- 22 November 1960 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for the Collingwood Magpies in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the 1920s and 30s .
Raúl Borges Requena ( 4 February 1882 -- 24 November 1967 ) was a renowned Venezuelan pedagogue , guitarist and composer .
Luis Arístides Fiallo Cabral ( 8 May 1876 -- Santo Domingo , 20 March 1931 ) was a scientist ( astronomer , medical laboratory scientist ) , physician , lawyer , architect , writer , philosopher and politician from the Dominican Republic .
Henry Rutgers Marshall ( 22 July 1852 -- 3 May 1927 ) was an American architect and psychologist .
Frederick Victor Dickins ( 1838 - -1915 ) was a British surgeon , barrister , orientalist and university administrator .
Magda Cordell McHale ( née Lustigova ) ( June 24 , 1921 in Hungary -- February 21 , 2008 in Sloan ( near Buffalo ) , New York ) was an artist , futurist , and educator .
Charlie Sneddon ( 10 June 1930 -- 1992 ) was a Scottish professional footballer who played as a centre half .
Sir John Delamare ( c. 1320 -- 1383 ) was a knight at the court of King Edward III of England and the builder of Nunney Castle in Somerset .
Thanh Hải died because of cirrhosis on 15 December 1980 at Huế city .
Arturo Chini Ludueña ( name also spelled Artur Quini Ludueña ; born October 21 , 1904 in Cañada de Gómez ; died in 1993 ) was an Argentine professional football player .
Maniram Dutta Baruah , popularly known as Maniram Dewan ( Assamese : মণিৰাম দেৱান ) ( 17 April 1806 -- 26 February 1858 ) , was an Assamese nobleman in British India .
Sir George Bracewell Smith , 2nd Bt MBE , always called Guy Bracewell Smith , ( 12 December 1912 -- 18 September 1976 ) , was a City of London business man who owned the Ritz Hotel and several others .
Benjamin Thorpe ( 1782 -- 19 July 1870 ) was an English scholar of Anglo - Saxon .
Mary Treadgold ( 16 April 1910 -- 14 May 2005 ) was a British author of books for children and adults , a literary editor and a BBC producer .
Thomas Middlemore ( 1842 -- 16 May 1923 ) was an English mountaineer who made multiple first ascents during the silver age of alpinism .
Marko Cheremshyna ( Ukrainian : Марко Черемшина ) ( other name : Ivan Semaniuk , Іван Семанюк ) , ( born 13 June 1874 in Kobaky , Galicia ; died 25 April 1927 in Kobaky ) was a Ukrainian writer of Hutsul background .
Paul Grebner ( Latin : Grebnerus ) ( fl . 1560 - -1590 ) was a German schoolteacher , and writer of a celebrated prophecy .
Joannes Burmeister ( 1576 - -1638 ) was a Neo - Latin poet laureate of the German Baroque period , famed for his Christian adaptations of the classical Roman poets Martial and Plautus .
Makkikha II was Patriarch of the Church of the East from 1257 until his death in 1265 .
Sir Walter Yonge , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1625 -- 21 November 1670 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1660 and 1670 .
Matthew Pitt ( died 18 April 1624 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1621 to 1622 .
August Wiltberger ( 17 April 1850 -- 2 December 1928 ) , was a German royal music director , composer and professor at a teachers ' seminary .
Robert Sibthorpe or Sibthorp ( died 1662 ) was an English clergyman who gained notoriety during the reign of King Charles I of England for his outspoken defense of the divine right of kings .
George Douglass Sherley ( 1857 - -1917 ) was an author , journalist , and poet .
Arieh Dulzin ( pronounced : Dulchin ; Hebrew : אריה דולצ'ין‎ , 1913 - -1989 ) was a Zionist activist who served as a Minister without Portfolio in the Israeli government between December 1969 and August 1970 , though he was never a member of the Knesset .
Yitzhaq Shami ( Hebrew : יצחק שמי‎ ) ( August 4 , 1888 -- March 1949 ) was a Hebrew writer , one of the earliest modern Hebrew literature writers in Palestine , prior to Israeli statehood .
John Frederick Perkins ( 5 May 1910 , in Paignton , Devon -- 14 May 1983 ) was an English entomologist .
Alexander Kircher ( 26 February 1867 -- 16 September 1939 ) was an Austrian - German marine- and landscape painter and an illustrator .
Elder John Crandall ( 1618 - 1676 ) was a Baptist minister from England and one of the founding settlers of Westerly , Rhode Island .
Dhanaji Jadhav ( 1650 - -1708 ) was a warrior of the Maratha Empire .
Major Sir Charles James Buchanan , 4th Baronet ( 16 April 1899 -- 1984 ) was High Sheriff of Nottinghamshire in 1962 .
Charles Muir Campbell died 12 October 1874 from kidney stones and is buried at Block 7 , Lot 261 , of the famous Oak Ridge Cemetery , not far from his friend , Abraham Lincoln .
Amalendu Guha ( 30 January 1924 -- 7 May 2015 ) was a historian , economist and poet from Assam , India .
Emilio Villalba Welsh ( died 7 September 1992 ) was a prolific Argentine screenwriter .
Elizabeth Laurenson Simpson ( 1916 - -1996 ) , better known as Sloan Simpson , was a fashion consultant , TV / radio personality , fashion model , and actor .
Lina Marín ( born Felipa Cartas Orozco ; died in 1989 ) was a Mexican actress who participated in both American and Mexican films .
Trine Krogh ( 18 January 1955 -- 3 May 2014 ) was a Norwegian swimmer .
George Cotes ( or Cotys ) ( died 1556 ) was an English Catholic bishop .
Anne Elizabeth Ball ( 1808 - -1872 ) was an Irish botanist , amateur algologist , and botanical illustrator .
Pierre Pavillon ( 1612 - 1670 ) was a French architect and sculptor .
Eva Fong Chang ( 1897 - -1991 ) was a Chinese and Native American painter who was one of the first Asian American Women to widely exhibit in the United States .
Len Harvey ( 11 July 1907 -- 28 November 1976 ) was an English boxer .
Alexander Grant McLean ( 1824 -- 28 September 1862 ) was a Surveyor General of New South Wales , ( then a colony , now a state of Australia ) .
Helen Deutsch ( 21 March 1906 -- 15 March 1992 ) was an American screenwriter , journalist and songwriter .
Chuni Lal Katial ( 1898 -- 1978 ) was a South Asian doctor and politician , who became the first UK 's South Asian mayor , after being elected mayor of Finsbury in 1938 .
Felipe Seade ( 1912 -- 18 January 1969 ) was a painter and teacher of Lebanese descent who spent most of his life in Uruguay .
Hugh Dunbar ( 27 June 1903 -- 17 July 1985 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Kendal Flanagan ( 19 ? ? -- 27 November 1999 ) was an Australian film and television director in regular employment from the late 1970s .
Frans Ackerman ( born c. 1330 , Ghent -- 22 July 1387 , Ghent ) , sometimes given as Franz , Francis or French Ackerman , was one of the most famous Flemish statesmen of the 14th century .
Monica Baldwin ( 1893 - -1975 ) was a British writer , a niece of British Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin , who was a canoness regular for 28 years .
Lucile Garner , later Lucile Garner Grant , ( 1910 - 2013 ) was Canada 's first flight attendant .
Oronhyatekha ( 10 August 1841 -- 3 March 1907 ) , ( `` Burning Sky '' or `` Burning Cloud '' in the Mohawk language , also carried the baptismal name Peter Martin ) , was a Mohawk physician , scholar , and a unique figure in the history of British colonialism .
Jacob Lampert ( 1856 , London - 1921 , St. Louis , Missouri ) was a wealthy cigar manufacturer based in St. Louis , Missouri .
Judith Meuli ( 1938 - 2007 ) was an American feminist activist and scientist .
Maxwell Finland ( March 15 , 1902 -- October 25 , 1987 ) was an American scientist , medical researcher , an expert on infectious diseases .
António de Almeida Santos , GCL ( 15 February 1926 -- 18 January 2016 ) , was a Portuguese lawyer , politician and government minister .
Knud Nellemose ( 12 March 1908 , Copenhagen -- 14 January 1997 , Copenhagen ) was a prolific Danish sculptor who is remembered for his figures of sportsmen and his statues of famous Danes .
Lawrence Fletcher ( died 1608 ) was a Jacobean actor , and man of mystery .
Edmond Albanach de Burgh , 1st Mac William Íochtar , born before 1315 , died 1375 .
Friedrich Ruthardt ( 9 December 1802 -- 23 May 1862 ) was a German oboist and composer .
Dick Joice ( 1921 in Great Ryburgh , Norfolk -- 1999 ) was a British regional television presenter renowned in the East of England for his Anglia Television programmes - particularly the Bygones show that ran from 1967 for twenty years .
Reverend Henry Weston Smith ( Preacher Smith ) ( b. January 10 , 1827 in Ellington , Connecticut -- died August 20 , 1876 between Deadwood and Crook City , South Dakota ) was an early resident of Deadwood , South Dakota .
Richard Handcock , 2nd Baron Castlemaine ( 14 May 1767 -- 18 April 1840 ) , known as Richard Handcock until 1839 , was an Irish peer and politician .
Edward Pytts ( 1606 - 3 November 1672 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1654 and 1660 .
Walter Hawken Tregellas ( 1831 - -1894 ) , miscellaneous writer , born at Truro , Cornwall , UK on 10 July 1831 , was a professional draughtsman and writer of historical , biographical and other works .
Colin Blythe ( born 30 May 1879 , Deptford --died 8 November 1917 , Belgium ) , also known as Charlie Blythe , was a Kent and England left arm spinner who is regarded as one of the finest bowlers of the period between 1900 and 1914 -- sometimes referred to as the `` Golden Age '' of cricket .
James Augustine Power ( 14 September 1903 -- 9 February 1975 ) was a Liberal party member of the Canadian House of Commons and a lawyer .
Blessed Victoria Díez Bustos de Molina ( Seville , 11 November 1903 - Hornachuelos , 12 August 1936 ) was a Spanish teacher and lay religious woman .
Pál Engel ( 27 February 1938 -- 21 August 2001 ) was a Hungarian medivealist historian and archivist , member of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences .
Sir Hans Adolf Krebs ( English /krɛbz/ or /krɛps/ ) ( 25 August 1900 -- 22 November 1981 ) was a German - born British physician and biochemist .
Robert Jay Wolff ( 1905 - -1978 ) was an early pioneer of the American abstract art . His paintings are in the collections of the Brooklyn Museum and the Guggenheim .
Sir ( William Owen ) Campbell Adamson ( 26 June 1922 -- 21 August 2000 ) was a British industrialist who was best known for his work as Director - General of the Confederation of British Industry from 1969 to 1976 .
André Chave ( 1799 - 1868 ) was a French landowner and real estate developer in Marseille .
Simin Behbahani ( Persian : سیمین بهبهانی‎‎ ; 20 June 1927 -- 19 August 2014 ) was a prominent Iranian contemporaneity poet , lyricist and activist .
Edward Slow ( 1841 -- 16 February 1925 ) was a poet born in Wilton , Wiltshire , England .
Felipe Herrera ( 17 June 1922 -- 17 September 1996 ) was a Chilean economist , lawyer , academic and political socialist .
Ismael Montes Gamboa ( 5 October 1861 -- 16 October 1933 ) was a Bolivian general and political figure .
Ramavtar Tyagi , popularly known as `` Tyagi '' ( 17 March 1925 - 12 April 1985 ) was a Hindi poet .
Jesús Sanoja Hernández ( Tumeremo , Bolívar state 27 June 1930 - Caracas , 9 June 2007 ) , was a Venezuelan journalist , historian and writer , who authored Entre golpes y revoluciones ( 2007 ) .
Sultan Ahmed Mirza was the eldest son of Abu Sa'id Mirza on whose death he became the Timurid ruler of Samarkand and Bukhara from 1469 till 1494 .
Edmund Petty ( c. 1621 -- 1661 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
Edith Halpert or Edith Gregor Halpert ( née Edith Gregoryevna Fivoosiovitch ( Fein ) ) ( 1900 - -1970 ) was a pioneering New York City dealer of Modern art . Halpert brought recognition and market success to many avant - garde American artists over her forty - year career from 1926 through the 1960s .
Elisabeth of Świdnica ( ca . 1315 -- 8/9 February 1348 ) was a member of the Piast dynasty in the Świdnica - Jawor branch and by marriage Duchess of Opole .
Alejandro Scopelli Casanova ( 12 May 1908 -- 23 October 1987 ) was an Italian Argentine football player and coach .
Deborahe Glasgow ( 1965 -- 25 January 1994 ) was an English Lovers rock singer of Guyanese parentage , who was active from the late 1970s to the beginning of the 1990s .
Pierre Gadoys ( c. 1594 -- October 1667 ) is recognized as the first farmer at Montreal .
Margaret Maddocks , née Margaret Kathleen Avern ( 10 August 1906 -- October 1993 ) , was a British writer of 17 gothic and romance novels .
Dr. Paul Alfred Biefeld ( 22 March 1867 -- 21 June 1943 ) was a German - American electrical engineer , astronomer and teacher .
Quispe Sisa ( ca . 1518 -- 1559 ) , also known as Inés Huaylas Yupanqui , was an Inca princess who played a role in the Spanish conquest of the Inca Empire .
Tom Holley ( November 15 , 1913 -- September 1992 ) was a professional footballer who played for Sunderland , Barnsley and Leeds United .
Colin Fletcher ( 14 March 1922 -- 12 June 2007 ) was a pioneering backpacker and writer .
Emma Danieli ( 14 October 1936 -- 21 June 1998 ) was an Italian actress and television personality .
Rudolf Nafziger ( 11 August 1945 -- 13 July 2008 ) was a German footballer who was part of the Bayern Munich team of the late-1960s .
Giuseppe Pozzobonelli died in Milan on 27 April 1783 , and his remains were buried in the North nave of the Cathedral of Milan .
Robert Devereux , 3rd Earl of Essex KB PC ( 11 January 1591 -- 14 September 1646 ) was an English Parliamentarian and soldier during the first half of the seventeenth century .
Hans Jacob Scheel ( born 23 August 1714 in Copenhagen , died 21 January 1774 in Fredrikstad ) was a Dano - Norwegian Major - General , Chamberlain at the Royal Court , Commandant of Fredrikstad Fortress from 1766 to 1774 and owner of Frogner Manor .
Eusebio Peñalver Mazorra ( 1936 - -2006 ) was an Afro - Cuban anti - Castro political prisoner who was captured in 1960 during the Cuban governments War Against the Bandits and spent 28 years in prison before being released in 1988 .
Leo Brewer ( 13 June 1919 - -22 February 2005 ) was an American physical chemist , considered to be the founder of modern high - temperature chemistry .
Antonio Carini ( 1872 - -1950 ) was an Italian physician , bacteriologist and professor .
Rodrigo Gutiérrez Girón ( died 1193 ) was a magnate and ricohombre from Palencia who played a key role in the Medieval history of the Iberian Peninsula .
Giovanni Battista Primi ( died 1657 ) was an Italian marine landscape and portrait painter .
François Vranck ( alternative spellings Vrancke , Vrancken , Franchois Francken ) , ( Zevenbergen , 1555 ? -- The Hague , 11 October 1617 ) was a Dutch lawyer and statesman who played an important role in the founding of the Dutch Republic .
Richard Golding or Goldynge ( died 1520 ) was an Irish judge who was twice Chief Baron of the Irish Exchequer .
Robin Levett ( 14 October 1925 -- 14 August 2008 ) was an Australian travel writer , novelist , philanthropist , pilot , and breeder of racehorses anointed the `` First Lady of Australian Racing '' in the mid-1990s .
Sulekha Sanyal ( 15 June 1928 -- c. 1962 ) was a Bengali woman writer and activist .
Silvester Jenks ( c. 1656 -- December 1714 ) was an English Catholic priest and theologian .
George Washington Hosmer ( born in Canton , Massachusetts , in 1804 ; died there , 5 July 1881 ) was a United States educator .
Gheorghe Cosma ( born 1892 , died 1969 ) was a Romanian Major - General during World War II . He began his career in 1940 as Chief of Staff Higher Technical Department .
David Cecil , 3rd Earl of Exeter ( c. 1600 - -1643 ) was an English peer and member of the House of Lords .
Rev Patrick Bell ( 12 May 1799 -- 22 April 1869 ) was a Church of Scotland minister and inventor .
V. Subbiah ( 7 February 1911 -- 1993 ) was an Indian communist politician from Pondicherry ( now Puducherry ) .
Willibald Hahn ( 31 January 1910 -- 31 May 1999 ) was an Austrian footballer and football manager .
Bernard Grebanier ( March 8 , 1903 -- March 1977 ) was an American drama historian , critic , writer and poet , most notable for his studies of the works of William Shakespeare .
Henry Butler Clarke ( 9 November 1863 -- 10 September 1904 ) was a lecturer on Spanish at the University of Oxford 's Taylor Institution from 1890 to 1894 , and an author of books about Spanish literature and history .
Vilayattasseri Mullambalath Balachandran ( 25 November 1924 -- 9 January 2010 ) , known as Vimcy , was a sports writer from Kerala .
Kleo Pleyer ( 1898 - -1942 ) was a Nazi politician and academic ( historian and sociologist , professor at the Königsberg Albertina University and Eberhard Karls University of Tübingen ) .
James Ley , 1st Earl of Marlborough ( ca . 1552 - -1629 ) was an English judge and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1597 and 1622 .
Pieter Hendrik van Zuylen van Nijevelt ( 1 July 1782 in Kampen -- 25 January 1825 in Utrecht ) was a Dutch count and baron who served as a general in the French and Dutch armies during the Napoleonic era and later .
Christian Leden ( born Christian Refsaas ; 17 July 1882 -- 19 November 1957 ) was a Norwegian ethno - musicologist and composer .
Lorena Rojas ( born Seydi Lorena Rojas Gonzalez ; 10 February 1971 -- 16 February 2015 ) was a Mexican actress and singer , best known for her leading roles in popular telenovelas .
Count Peter Kirillovich Essen ( 11 August 1772 -- 23 September 1844 ) was a Russian General of the Infantry in 1819 and a count ( 1833 ) of Baltic German origin .
William Raimond Baird ( 1848 - -1917 ) was the namesake of Baird 's Manual of American College Fraternities and publisher of its early editions .
Chase Price ( 1731 - 28 June 1777 ) was an 18th - century British lawyer and politician .
Robert Alistair McAlpine , Baron McAlpine of West Green ( 14 May 1942 -- 17 January 2014 ) , often known as Alistair McAlpine , was a British businessman , politician and author who was an advisor to Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher .
Sir Joseph Hickson ( 23 January 1830 -- 4 January 1897 ) was a Canadian railway executive .
Aed mac Ruaidrí Ua Conchobair , killed 1159 , was Crown Prince of Connacht , Aed was one of at least two sons of King Ruaidrí Ua Conchobair by different women .
Frank Seymour ( 14 May 1904 -- 7 May 1987 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the VFL and Northcote in the VFA .
Samuel Meeker ( 1763 - -1831 ) was a prominent merchant businessman who played a substantial role in the development of banking , shipping , and insurance systems in the early post - revolutionary days of Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Liang Desheng ( Chinese : 梁德绳 ; Pinyin : Liáng Déshéng ; 1771 - -1847 ) was a Chinese poet and writer active during the Qing Dynasty .
William Bradbery ( 11 July 1776 -- 11 August 1860 ) , an entrepreneur , was the first person in England to cultivate and sell watercress on a commercial basis .
Michiel ten Hove ( 24 February 1640 , The Hague -- 24 March 1689 , The Hague ) was ad interim Grand Pensionary of Holland in 1688 and 1689 .
David Ogilvy , 9th Earl of Airlie ( 16 December 1785 -- 20 August 1849 ) was a British peer .
Wander Johannes de Haas ( 2 March 1878 -- 26 April 1960 ) was a Dutch physicist and mathematician .
Jan van Brakel ( ca . 1638 -- 10 July 1690 ) was a Dutch Rear Admiral who distinguished himself on many occasions during the Second and Third Anglo - Dutch wars and the Nine Years War .
John Wellborn Root , Jr. ( 1887 - -1963 ) was a significant United States architect based in Chicago .
Giuseppe Antonio Torricelli ( 1662 - -1719 ) was an Italian sculptor and gem - engraver of the late Baroque active in Florence , often using colorful and semi - precious pietra dura , a type of workmanship that became a specialty of Florence .
Natteri Veeraraghavan ( 1913 - 2004 ) was an Indian physician , microbiologist and medical researcher , known for his contributions to the understanding of diseases like Rabies , Tuberculosis and Leprosy .
Heinrich Körting ( 15 March 1859 -- 19 July 1890 ) was a German philologist , a brother of Gustav Körting .
François - André Vincent ( 30 December 1746 -- 4 August 1816 ) was a French neoclassical painter .
Ailbhe of Ceann Mhara ( died 814 ) was an Irish cleric .
Gloria Ferrandiz ( died 1970 ) was an Argentine actress of the classic Argentine cinema era .
Edward Sacheverell Chandos - Pole ( 1 March 1792 -- 19 January 1863 ) was a Guards officer and High Sheriff of Derbyshire in 1827 .
Countess Mary von Waldersee ( 3 October 1837 -- 4 July 1914 ) , born Mary Esther Lee , was an American - born philanthropist in Germany .
Julian Brind MW ( 5 November 1942 -- 19 December 2010 ) was a British Master of Wine and director of buying wines , beers , spirits and soft drinks for the Waitrose supermarket chain .
Colonel Josiah Snelling ( 1782 - -20 August 1828 ) was the first commander of Fort Snelling , a fort located at the confluence of the Mississippi and Minnesota rivers in Minnesota .
Nicholas Clagett the Younger , D.D. ( 1654 - -1727 ) , was an English controversialist .
Joseph Goodall ( 1760 - -1840 ) was an English cleric and Provost of Eton .
Robert Feys ( 19 December 1889 -- 13 April 1961 ) was a Belgian logician and philosopher , who worked at the University of Leuven ( Belgium ) .
Hidaya Sultan al - Salem , ( 1936 -- 20 March 2001 ) , sometimes transliterated as Hedaya , was a Kuwaiti journalist and author , who owned and edited the one of Kuwait 's earliest political magazines al - Majalis in Kuwait City , Kuwait .
Dorothy Clutterbuck ( 19 January 1880 -- 12 January 1951 ) , was a wealthy Englishwoman who was named by Gerald Gardner as a leading member of the New Forest coven , a group of pagan Witches into which Gardner claimed to have been initiated in 1939 .
Nikolay Nikolayevich Sokolov ( Russian : Никола́й Никола́евич Соколов ) ( 28 August 1930 -- 2009 ) was a Soviet athlete who competed mainly in the 3000 metre steeplechase .
Raffaele Piria ( 20 August 1814 -- 18 July 1865 ) , an Italian chemist from Scilla , lived in Palmi , who converted the substance Salicin into a sugar and a second component , which on oxidation becomes salicylic acid , a major component of the analgesic drug Aspirin ( acetylsalicylic acid ) .
Milan Levar ( c. 1954 -- 28 August 2000 ) was a Croatian whistleblower , a former officer in the Croatian army .
John Seton , Lord Barns ( died 1594 ) was a Scottish diplomat , courtier and judge .
William McMillan ( born Carrickfergus , County Antrim , Ireland ; died Carrickfergus , 1991 ) , commonly referred to as Billy McMillan , was an Irish footballer who played for Belfast Celtic and Ballymena United .
Panayotis Potagos ( 1839 - 1903 ) was a Greek physician and explorer from Arcadian Vytina .
Yu Xingwu ( Chinese : 于省吾 ; 1896 - -1984 ) was a Chinese philologist and exegesis interpreter .
Jacob de Wet II ( 1641 , Haarlem -- 1697 , Haarlem ) , also spelled de Witt , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Giovanni Casini ( 1689 - -1748 ) was known as il Varlunga ( based on his native town in Tuscany ) .
Nadia Boudesoque de Haro Oliva ( 11 April 1917 -- 17 January 2014 ) , born Albertina Charlotte Boudesoque Noblecourt , was a French - born Mexican fencer and actress .
John Patrick Brasier - Creagh , best known as Patrick Creagh ( 23 October 1930 - 19 September 2012 ) was a British poet and translator .
Jakob Marzel Sternberger ( 1750 - -1822 ) was the first mayor of the town of Kadaň after the municipal reform of Joseph II . He was a mayor from 1788 till 1822 .
Tömöriin Artag ( Mongolian : Төмөрийн Артаг ; born April 10 , 1943 , died 1993 ) was a Mongolian wrestler .
Edwin Duhon ( 11 June 1910 in Broussard , Louisiana -- 26 February 2006 in Westlake , Louisiana ) was an American musician and co - founder of the Hackberry Ramblers , a band playing a combination of Cajun music , Western swing , and country music .
Buffalo Bird Woman ( ca . 1839 - 1932 ) was a traditional Mandan Hidatsa woman who lived on the Fort Berthold Reservation in North Dakota .
Christos Daralexis ( Greek : Χρήστος Δαραλέξης , 1870 - 1951 ) was a Greek historian , a politician and a theatrical writer .
Ma Anand Yashu ( 9 October 1956 -- 3 December 2007 ) was an Indian - Spanish flautist .
William C. Conway ( May 15 , 1865 -- 1969 ) was the leader of a mystical sect in the Latter Day Saint movement that combined the teachings of Joseph Smith with Druidry and some of the ideas of Aleister Crowley and the Ordo Templi Orientis .
( Pierre Joseph ) Auguste Bravard ( 18 June 1803 -- 28 March 1861 ) was a French mining engineer turned palaeontologist .
Georgina King Lewis ( 1847 to 1924 ) was described as a `` Friend of the Oppressed '' .
Sir John Boyd , 1st Baronet Boyd ( 29 December 1718 , St Kitts , Leeward Islands - 24 January 1800 , Danson Hill ) was a sugar merchant and vice - chairman of the British East India Company .
Frank J. Reilly A.N.A. ( 1906 - -1967 ) was an American painter , illustrator , muralist , and teacher .
Richard Corbould ( 1757 in London -- 1831 in London ) was an English artist , sometimes misspelt `` Corbold '' .
Hans Leo Przibram ( ˈpʃɪbram ) ( 7 July 1874 -- 20 May 1944 ) was an Austrian biologist who founded the biological laboratory in Vienna .
Jana Milčinski ( born Jana Podkrajšek ) ( 5 December 1920 -- 13 April 2007 ) was a Slovene writer , journalist and translator .
Sir Clifford Charles Butler FRS ( 20 May 1922 -- 30 June 1999 ) was an English physicist , best known for the discovery of the hyperon and meson types of particles .
Sir Geoffrey Pole of Lordington , Sussex ( c. 1501 or 1502 - November 1558 ) was an English knight who supported the Catholic Church in England and Wales when Henry VIII of England was establishing the alternative Church of England with himself as leader .
David John Little QC ( d. 16 April 1984 ) was an Ulster Unionist Party politician in the Parliament of Northern Ireland , a barrister and county court judge .
E. M. Almedingen ( born Marta Aleksandrovna Almedingen , also known as Martha Edith Almedingen or von Almedingen ) ( 1898 - -1971 ) was a British novelist , biographer and children 's author of Russian origin .
Andries Both ( 1612/1613 - 23 March 1642 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age genre painter , one of the bamboccianti , and brother of Jan Dirksz Both .
Stuart Alexander Donaldson ( born 4 December 1854 in Sydney , Australia , died 29 October 1915 ) was a schoolmaster , clergyman and Master of Magdalene College , Cambridge .
Edzard Cirksena ( born : Edzard Edzardisna ; died : 1441 ) was an East Frisian chieftain at Greetsiel , Norden , Emden and Brokmerland .
Tulga or Tulca ( Gothic : Tulga ; living 642 ) was Visigothic King of Hispania , Septimania and Galicia from 640 to 642 , if his father died in December 640 , as some sources state .
Pat Fillingham FRAes ( 27 February 1914 -- 17 July 2003 ) was an English test pilot for the de Havilland company .
Edward Lutwyche Parker ( 1785 - -1850 ) , was a United States Presbyterian clergyman .
Gilbert Bozon ( 19 March 1935 -- 21 July 2007 ) was a French swimmer and Olympic medalist .
Colonel John Drinkwater Bethune ( 9 June 1762 -- 16 January 1844 ) , born John Drinkwater , was an English army officer and military historian , and was well known for his journal , which he kept during the Great Siege of Gibraltar .
Agustín Nieto Caballero was a Colombian pedagogue(1889 - 1975 ) ; who , in 1914 , founded Gimnasio Moderno , a prestigious private school , located in Bogotá .
Norah Lofts , née Norah Ethel Robinson , ( 27 August 1904 -- 10 September 1983 ) was a 20th - century best - selling British author .
Judah Cassuto ( 1808 , Amsterdam -- March 10 , 1893 , Hamburg ) was hazzan ( cantor ) of the Portuguese - Jewish community of Hamburg .
Sir Henry Bedingfeld ( 1509 - -1583 ) , of Oxburgh Hall , King 's Lynn , Norfolk , was the eldest son of Edmund Bedingfeld ( 1479/80 - 1553 ) and his wife , Grace ( d. in or after 1553 ) , the daughter of Henry , first Baron Marney .
Ivor Kirchin ( 21 January 1905 -- 22 January 1997 ) was a British band leader , and the father of noted composer Basil Kirchin ( 1927 - -2005 ) .
Mendel Portugali ( 1888 -- 13 January 1917 ) was one of the leading figures in the Second Aliyah and a founder of the Hashomer movement .
Rudolf Stahlecker ( 25 November 1898 in Sternenfels near Pforzheim -- 26 October 1977 in Urach ) was a German geologist and biology teacher .
D. Rajendra Babu ( Kannada : ರಾಜೇಂದ್ರ ಬಾಬು ) ( 30 March 1951 -- 3 November 2013 ) was a Kannada film maker and screenplay writer .
Giuseppe Serembe ( Arbërisht : Zef Serembe ; 6 March 1844 -- 1901 ) was an Arbëresh lyric poet .
In 1676 Gualterus Gysaerts collaborated with his uncle David Teniers the Younger on a series of 19 garland paintings depicting the martyrs of Gorkum .
George Molyneux ( July qtr . 1875 -- 14 April 1942 ) was a professional footballer who played for Everton , Southampton and Southend United , and later became Southend 's manager .
Al - Tufayl ibn Amr al - Dawsi ( died 633 ) was the chief of the Banu Daws tribe from Tihama in pre - Quranic times .
Jim Coucher ( 22 December 1874 -- 13 June 1935 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Zoe Golescu ( 1792 - -1879 ) was a Romanian revolutionary who participated in the Wallachian Revolution of 1848 .
Bill Ladbury ( 14 October 1891 -- June 1917 ) was an English boxer who was British , European , and World flyweight champion .
Richard Edgcumbe , 2nd Earl of Mount Edgcumbe PC ( 13 September 1764 -- 26 September 1839 ) , styled Viscount Valletort between 1789 and 1795 , was a British politician and writer on music .
Leon Danielian ( 31 October 1920 -- 8 March 1997 ) was an American ballet dancer , teacher , choreographer , and educator .
Mary Saunderson ( 1637 - -1712 ) , later known as Mary Saunderson Betterton after her marriage to Thomas Betterton , was an actress and singer in England during the 1660s and 1690s .
Sir Errol Manners K.B.E ( 1883 - -1953 ) was a distinguished Royal Navy admiral and author on theology and British Israelism .
James Pound ( 1669 - -1724 ) was an English clergyman and astronomer .
Eugen Sänger ( 22 September 1905 -- 10 February 1964 ) was an Austrian aerospace engineer best known for his contributions to lifting body and ramjet technology .
Adam Hope ( 8 January 1813 -- 7 August 1882 ) was a Canadian businessman and senator .
Stanisław Puchalski , of Puchała coat of arms ( 5 January 1867 in Wapowce - 16 January 1931 in Warsaw ) was an Austro - Hungarian and Polish general .
I Gusti Ketut Pudja ( 19 May 1908 -- 4 May 1977 ) was an Indonesian Politician , and also first governor of Lesser Sunda .
Hallfreðr Óttarsson or Hallfreðr vandræðaskáld ( Troublesome Poet ) ( ca . 965 -- ca . 1007 ) was an Icelandic skald .
Ian Ridley ( 15 February 1934 -- 13 November 2008 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Melbourne in the VFL .
Herman van Swanevelt ( 1603 -- 1655 ) was a Dutch painter and etcher from the Baroque era .
Bonnie Bronson ( 1940 - -1990 ) was an American painter and sculptor and one of Portland , Oregon 's most prominent artists during the 1970s--1980s .
William Victor Higgins ( June 28 , 1884 -- August 23 , 1949 ) was an American painter and teacher , born at Shelbyville , Indiana .
Tom Pazik ( 1940 - 1993 ) began his dance training in Detroit , Michigan where he studied under Sandra Severo .
George Farwell ( 3 October 1911 -- 6 August 1976 ) was an Australian novelist , freelance journalist , broadcaster and travel writer .
