Edwin Rowlands ( 15 March 1867 -- 6 August 1939 ) was a Welsh Christian missionary in northeast India and Burma .
Job Male ( August 24 , 1808 -- 1891 ) was the first Mayor of Plainfield , New Jersey , serving from 1869 - -1870 and 1877 - -1878 and finally 1887 - -1890 .
James Michael Ullman ( 1925 - -1997 ) was an American novelist and newspaper writer / editor known for his work in and about the Chicago area .
Jacob Gaukel Stroh ( September 25 , 1848 - 1935 ) was a local Historian of Waterloo County , Ontario .
Corporal Roland Griffiths - Marsh MM , ( 22 April 1923 - 29 December 2012 ) was an Australian soldier and author .
Paul Follot ( 17 July 1877 -- 1941 ) was a French designer of luxury furniture and decorative art objects before World War I ( 1914 - -18 ) .
Dougal Graham , born in the Raploch , Stirlingshire , Scotland , around 1724 and died in 1779 , became the skellat bellman of Glasgow at some time around 1770 .
Erich Förste ( 11 February 1892 -- 10 July 1963 ) was a German naval officer who served in the Kaiserliche Marine , the Reichsmarine and the Kriegsmarine , eventually reaching the rank of Admiral during World War II .
Sydney Henry Armitstead ( 13 June 1837 - 29 January 1912 ) was an English cricketer , an alumnus of Charterhouse School whose cricketing career including two first class matches : for the Gentlemen of the North in 1862 and the Marylebone Cricket Club in 1864 .
Finn Strømsted ( 9 June 1925 -- 4 July 2003 ) was a Norwegian poet and graphical artist .
Frederick of Cieszyn ( Polish : Fryderyk cieszyński ; b. 1480/83 - d. June 1507 ) , was a Polish prince member of the House of Piast in the Cieszyn branch .
Thomas Yalden ( 2 January 1670 -- 16 July 1736 ) was an English poet and translator .
Hamish Imlach ( 10 February 1940 , Calcutta , British India - 1 January 1996 , Motherwell , Scotland ) was a Scottish folk singer .
Lambert Sustris ( c. 1515 - 1520 -- c. 1584 ) was a Dutch painter active mainly in Venice during the Mannerist style .
Prince Michael Imeretinsky AFC ( Georgian : მიხეილ იმერეტინსკი , Mikheil Imeretinski ; Russian : Михаил Георгиевич Имеретинский , Mikhail Georgyevich Imeretinsky ) ( 27 January 1900 -- 14 April 1975 ) was a British military officer of Georgian royal descent .
Christian Jane Fergusson ( 14 September 1876 - 5 January 1957 ) , was a Scottish painter , who was associated with the Glasgow School and known for her landscape and still life works .
Tuoba Yihuai ( Chinese : 拓跋翳槐 ; pinyin : Tuòbá Yīhuái ; died 338 ) ruled as prince of the Tuoba Dai 329 - -335 and 337 - -338 .
Charlie Hay ( 4 November 1881 -- 23 August 1945 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Dagfinn Dahl ( 28 January 1887 -- 1967 ) was a Norwegian barrister who specialized in insurance law .
Paolo Casati ( in Latin , Paulus Casatus ) ( 1617 -- 22 December 1707 ) was an Italian Jesuit mathematician .
Irwin Freundlich ( 1908 - -1977 ) was a prominent teacher at Juilliard starting in 1935 .
Franz Kaufmann ( 5 January 1886 -- 17 February 1944 ) was a German jurist and victim of the Holocaust .
Charles Wrey Gardiner ( 1901 -- 13 March 1981 ) was an English writer and poet , editor and publisher , born in Plymouth .
Beilby Thompson ( 17 April 1742 -- 10 June 1799 ) was a British landowner and politician , the son of Beilby Thompson ( died 1750 ) and Sarah Dawes ( d. 1773 ) .
Richard Fortescue ( c. 1517 - -1570 ) of Filleigh , North Devon was an English Member of Parliament and prominent land - owner and member of the Devonshire gentry , ancestor to the Earls Fortescue .
Arne Paasche Aasen ( 18 June 1901 -- 1 November 1978 ) was a Norwegian politician , journalist and poet , who worked for the labour movement .
James Mackin ( December 25 , 1822 , Newburgh , Orange County , New York -- March 1887 ) was an American merchant , banker and politician .
Francis Engleheart ( 1775 - -1849 ) , was an English engraver .
Sir William Burnett , KCB , FRS ( 16 January 1779 -- 16 February 1861 ) was a British physician who served as Physician - General of the Royal Navy .
Chunibala Devi , born circ . 1875 -- 1955 in Kolkata , was an Indian character actress best known for her performance in Satyajit Ray 's Pather Panchali , where she played the old aunt , Indira Thakrun , to Apu and Durga .
Cecil Guy Ridley CBE ( 21 June 1885 - 15 November 1947 ) was an English barrister and Master in Lunacy .
George Hersee ( 29 December 1924 -- 11 April 2001 ) was a BBC engineer , who is most famous for his development of Test Card F. This design came about after Hersee was asked to intervene by the committee charged with the creation of technical standards for the new colour TV services .
Adil Mansuri ( 18 May 1936 -- 6 November 2008 ) was a well - known poet , playwright , and calligrapher .
Edward Garbett ( 1817 - -1887 ) , was a religious figure and writer of the 19th century .
Dermot FitzGerald ( 20 March 1935 -- 5 February 2006 ) was a leading Irish businessman and philanthropist .
Pape Alioune Diop ( died 26 September 2012 ) was a Senegalese football coach who managed the Senegalese national team at the 1986 African Cup of Nations .
Li Jiang ( 李絳 ) ( 764 -- March 8 , 830 ) , courtesy name Shenzhi ( 深之 ) , formally Duke Zhen of Zhao Commandery ( 趙郡貞公 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Xianzong .
Endesha Ida Mae Holland ( 1944 - 2006 ) was a scholar , playwright , and civil rights activist .
George Douglas Verity ( 4 June 1933 -- 24 August 2012 ) was an English cricketer , mountain climber , hotelier , and professional golfer .
Buford John Schramm ( 14 October 1938 -- 28 April 2004 ) , better - known as B.J. Schramm , was a businessman and developer of light personal helicopters .
James Blythe Rogers ( born in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania , 11 February 1802 ; died there , 15 June 1852 ) was a United States chemist .
Paweł Cyms ( 1894 - 1949 ) was a soldier of the Imperial German Army and captain of infantry in the Second Polish Republic .
Henry Hylton , de jure 12th Baron Hylton ( 1586 -- 30 March 1641 ) was an English nobleman , considered eccentric and sometimes given the name the Mad Baron .
Prince Heinrich of Bavaria ( 24 June 1884 -- 8 November 1916 ) was a member of the Bavarian Royal House of Wittelsbach and a highly decorated Army officer in the First World War .
Rao Sahib S. Vaiyapuri Pillai ( 1891 - -1956 ) was a renowned scholar and Professor of Tamil .
Bernhard Moritz Snethlage ( 28 May 1753 , Tecklenburg -- 19 November 1840 , Berlin ) was a German educator .
Raymond Sheppard ( 1913 - -1958 ) was a British artist and illustrator of books for children and adults .
Aegidius Gelenius ( 10 June 1595 -- 24 August 1656 ) was one of the most respected Cologne historians of his time .
John Penny ( died 1520 ) was an English priest , successively Bishop of Bangor , 1504 - -1508 , and Bishop of Carlisle , 1508 - -1520 .
Ranjan Roy Daniel ( also referred as R. R. Daniel or Rajan Roy ) ( 11 August 1923 -- 27 March 2005 ) was an Indian Nagercoil born physicist who worked in the fields of cosmic rays and space physics , and remained Director Chairman of Tata Institute of Fundamental Research .
Lucien Durosoir ( 1878 - 5 December 1955 ) was a French composer and violinist whose works were rediscovered thanks to manuscripts found by his son Luc .
Tadeusz Kurcyusz ( pseudonyms : Fiszer , gen . Mars , Morski , Żegota ) ( 15 October 1881 - 22 or 23 April 1944 ) was a colonel of the Polish Army .
Edward Hall or Halle ( 1497 - -1547 ) , was an English lawyer , Member of Parliament , and historian , best known for his The Union of the Two Noble and Illustre Families of Lancastre and Yorke , commonly known as Hall 's Chronicle .
Joseph Stanley Crowther , known as Stan Crowther , ( 30 May 1925 -- 10 March 2013 ) was British Labour Member of Parliament for Rotherham from the 1976 by - election until his retirement in 1992 .
Märta Torén ( 21 May 1925 -- 19 February 1957 ) was a Swedish stage and film actress of the 1940s and 1950s .
Claës - Axel Wersäll ( 26 June 1888 -- 12 February 1951 ) was a Swedish gymnast .
Emil Friedrich Knoblauch ( 2 December 1864 , Groß Karnitten in Kreis Mohrungen -- 10 February 1936 ) was a German botanist .
Shirley Ximena Hopper Russell ( 1886 - -1985 ) , also known as Shirley Marie Russell , was an American artist best known for her paintings of Hawaii and her still lifes of Hawaiian flowers .
Giovanni Vigliotto ( c. 1930 - -1991 ) was a name of a multiple bigamist and fraudster who married 105 women in 14 countries between 1949 and 1981 and abandoned them .
Jan Verveer ( 27 August 1775 -- 22 August 1838 ) was a major general in the Royal Netherlands Army .
Amin Abd al - Hadi ( Arabic : أمين عبد الهادي ; l897 - -1967 ) was the former head of the Supreme Muslim Council .
Juliette May Fraser ( 1887 in Honolulu -- 1983 in Honolulu ) was an American painter , muralist and printmaker .

Mallikarjuna Raya ( or Deva Raya III ) ( 1446 - -1465 CE ) was an emperor of the Vijayanagara Empire from the Sangama Dynasty .
John Somers , 1st Baron Somers , PC , PRS ( 4 March 1651 -- 26 April 1716 ) was an English Whig jurist and statesman .
Sándor Krasznai ( also known as Sándor Krämer ; 1932 - -2009 ) was a Hungarian athlete , engineer and constructor .
Michael Sundin ( 1 March 1961 -- 23 July 1989 ) was an English television presenter , actor , dancer and trampolinist , who is best remembered for his short time as a Blue Peter presenter ( 1984 - -85 ) .
Raymond Jeener ( 1904 - 1995 ) was a Belgian molecular biologist and professor at the Universite Libre de Bruxelles ( ULB ) .
The Reverend Doctor William Lambie Nelson ( 20 September 1808 -- 13 June 1887 ) .
Heinrich LXII , Prince Reuss Younger Line ( German : Heinrich LXII Fürst Reuß jüngere Linie ; 31 May 1785 -- 19 June 1854 ) was the first Prince Reuss Younger Line from 1848 to 1854 .
Randi Heide Steen ( 15 December 1909 -- 12 November 1990 ) was a Norwegian soprano singer .
Győző Soós ( 11 November 1948 -- c. 26 August 2015 ) was a Hungarian politician , Member of Parliament between 1994 and 2006 ( MSZP ) .
Joseph Elkington ( baptised 1 January 1740 at Stretton - on - Dunsmore , died October 1806 ) was an English agriculturalist , lauded by parliament for his reforms to land drainage .
Efraim Taburi ( Hebrew : אפרים תבורי‎ , born Efraim Popik on 5 September 1900 , died 7 April 1957 ) was a Zionist activist and politician .
Jacob Fahlström ( 1795 - -1859 ) , aka Father Jacob , was the first Swede ever to settle in Canada .
Carl Reuterskiöld ( ca.1923 - March 20 , 2006 ; known to his associates as Charlie ) was the founding CEO of the Belgium - based Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunication ( SWIFT ) , a position which he held for a decade from SWIFT 's founding in 1973 until 1983 .
Lenore Thomas Straus ( 1 November 1909 -- 16 January 1988 ) was an American sculptor and author .
Major - General Clifford Thomason Beckett CB , CBE , MC ( 1891 - -1972 ) of the Royal Artillery , had a distinguished military career including being Acting General Officer Commanding Malta in 1942 .
Keith Forbes ( 28 May 1906 -- 7 September 1996 ) is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the Essendon Bombers .
Mukarram Khan Atif ( Birth : unknown -- Death : 17 January 2012 ) was a Pakistani journalist and reporter working for Dunya News and Deewa Radio .

Darshan Singh Pheruman ( 1 August 1885 -- 27 October 1969 ) was an Indian freedom fighter , Sikh activist and politician .
Georges Cochon ( 1879 - 1959 ) was a tapestry maker , an anarchist and the secretary of the Federation of Tenants .
Michael J. Coffey ( c. 1840 County Cork , Ireland -- March 22 , 1907 Brooklyn , New York City ) was an American politician from New York .
Behram Contractor ( 1930 -- 9 April 2001 ) , also known as Busybee , was a figure in Indian journalism .
Cotton Tufts ( born in Medford , Massachusetts , 30 May 1734 ; died in Weymouth , Massachusetts , 8 December 1815 ) was a Massachusetts physician .
Sir John Fowell , 2nd Baronet ( 14 August 1623 -- 8 January 1677 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1659 and 1677 .
József Vészi , Hungarian writer , journalist , poet , translator , editor and deputy ; born at Arad 6 November 1858 , died 1940 .
Jonathan Silver ( 1949 - -1997 ) was an entrepreneur from Bradford who was responsible for restoring Salts Mill as a thriving cultural , retail and commercial centre .
John Wesley Work , Jr. ( August 6 , 1871 or 1873 - September 7 , 1925 ) was the first African - American collector of folk songs and spirituals , and also a choral director , educationalist and songwriter .
Gustav Mann ( 1836 - -1916 ) was a German botanist who led expeditions in West Africa and was also a gardener at the Royal Botanic Gardens , Kew .
Edmund Oldhall ( after 1390 -- 1459 ) was an English - born cleric and judge in fifteenth- century Ireland ; he was Bishop of Meath and acting Lord Chancellor of Ireland .
Riaz - ur - Rehman Bhatti ( 1940 , in India -- 10 July 1966 ) was a cricketer .
Lawrence Tenney Stevens ( 1896 - 1972 ) was an American sculptor who was one of the progenitors of the `` Cowboy High Style '' movement in western American art and furniture .
Ferdinando Stanhope ( died 1643 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1643 .
Fazl - e - Haq Khairabadi ( 1797 - - 20 August 1861 ) was one of the main figures of the Indian Rebellion of 1857 .
George L. Graziadio , Jr. ( 1919 - 2002 ) was an American commercial real estate developer , banker and philanthropist .
James McBey ( 23 December 1883 -- 1 December 1959 ) was a largely self - taught artist and etcher whose prints were highly valued during the later stages of the etching revival in the early 20th century .
Petre Antonescu ( 1891 - -1957 ) was a Romanian Brigadier - General during World War II . In 1941 , he became Head General - Secretary of the Department Ministry of Defense .
Stan Rule ( 17 January 1924 -- 12 August 2007 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Jan Regulski ( 1760 - 28 July 1807 ) was a Polish glyptic artist and medalist .
Bille Brown AM ( 11 January 1952 -- 13 January 2013 ) born as William Gerald Brown was an Australian stage , film and television actor and acclaimed playwright .
Martinus Fabri ( died May 1400 ) was a North Netherlandish composer of the late 14th century .
Thomas Palfreyman ( died 1589 ? ) was an English author and musician .
Antonio Vela Cobo ( 1629 - 1675 ) was a Spanish Baroque painter , sculptor and gilder .
Robert of Knaresborough ( St. Robert ) ( c. 1160 -- 24 September 1218 ) was a hermit who lived in a cave by the River Nidd , Knaresborough , North Yorkshire .
Paul Trousdale ( 1915 - -1990 ) was an American real estate developer .
Liutpert ( or Liutbert ) ( died 702 ) was the Lombard king of Italy from 700 and to 702 , with interruption .

Jessie Payne Margoliouth née Smith ( 1856 - -1933 ) was a Syriac scholar .

Antonio Barluzzi ( 26 September 1884 -- 14 December 1960 ) was an Italian Franciscan monk and architect .
John Wesley Hunt ( 1773 - -1849 ) was a prominent businessman and early civic leader in Lexington , Kentucky .

Frederick George Holweck ( born Friedrich Georg Holweck ; 1856 - -1927 ) was a German - American Roman Catholic priest and scholar , hagiographer and church historian .

Veslemøy Haslund ( 8 April 1939 -- 7 November 2005 ) was a Norwegian actress and stage producer .

Prokopios Lazaridis ( Greek : Προκόπιος Λαζαρίδης , 1859 - 1923 ) was a Greek Orthodox metropolitan bishop , who served as a head in a number of bishoprics during the late Ottoman period .

George Campbell Hay ( 1915 - -1984 ) was a Scottish poet and translator , who wrote in Scottish Gaelic , Lowland Scots and English .
Lolong ( died 10 February 2013 ) was the largest crocodile in captivity .
Robert Tighe ( or Teigh or Tjghe , sometimes misspelled Leigh ) , ( born in Deeping , Lincolnshire , died 1620 ) was an English cleric and linguist .
Charles Woodmason ( c. 1720 - -March 1789 ) was an author , poet , Anglican clergyman , American loyalist , and West Gallery psalmodist .
Mareez , born Abbas Abdulali Vasi ( Gujarati : અબ્બાસ અબ્દુલઅલી વાસી , 22 February 1917 -- 19 October 1983 ) , was a Gujarati poet , mainly popular for his Ghazals .
Oscar Heidenstam ( 1911 - -1991 ) was a Cyprus - born British bodybuilding champion , who later became president of the World Amateur Body Building Association ( WABBA ) , the National Amateur Bodybuilders Association ( NABBA ) , and NABBA International .
Scato Swu ( 1924 - 7 April 2014 ) was an Indian social worker and politician from Nagaland .
Petro Kalnyshevsky ( 1691 ? -- 31 October 1803 ) was the last Koshovyi Otaman of the Zaporozhian Host , serving in 1762 and from 1765 to 1775 .
Edward Rupert Burrowes ( 1903 - -1966 ) was an artist and art teacher who founded the Working People 's Art Class ( WPAC ) , the first established art institution in Guyana .
Mariano Guadalupe Vallejo ( 4 July 1807 -- 18 January 1890 ) was a Californio military commander , politician , and rancher .
Paul Niculescu - Mizil ( Romanian pronunciation : ( ˈpa.ul nikuˈlesku miˈzil ) ; 25 November 1923 -- 5 December 2008 ) was a Romanian communist politician .
Louis de Tousard ( 1749 - 1817 ) was a French artillerist who served in the American Continental Army under La Fayette , and later was given a US commission .
Fernando Ansúrez II ( died 978 , shortly after 23 April ) was the Count of Monzón , Peñafiel , and Campos from 950 and one of the most powerful noblemen of his generation in the Kingdom of León .
Shapurji Edalji ( 1841 or 1842 - -1918 ) was probably the first person from South Asia to be made the vicar of an English parish .
Lieutenant Francisco Gonzalo Marín , also known as Pachín Marín ( March 12 , 1863 -- November 1897 ) , was a poet and journalist who fought alongside José Martí as a member of the Cuban Liberation Army .
Richard Munday ( c.1685 - 1739 ) was a prominent colonial American architect and builder in Newport , Rhode Island .

Isaac Augustus Wetherby ( 1819 - 1904 ) or I.A. Wetherbee was an American painter and photographer .

Maximilian Joseph von Tarnóczy ( Hungarian : Tarnózy Miksa ) ( 24 October 1806 -- 4 April 1876 ) was an Austrian Cardinal and Archbishop .

Bjarne Orten ( 22 December 1919 - 14 January 2011 ) is a Norwegian civil servant .
Leopold Bürkner ( 29 January 1894 - 15 July 1975 ) was a German naval officer who served on torpedo boats in World War I. In the post - war period he served on a pocket battleship that patrolled the Spanish coast during the Spanish Civil War and then commanded a light cruiser .
Odoardo Barri ( 13 September 1844 -- January 1920 ) is the pseudonym of Edward Slater .

Narushima Ryūhoku ( 成島柳北 ) was a Japanese author and scholar who lived from 1837 - 1884 .

Juan Banderas ( executed 1833 at Arizpe ) was the leader of the Yaqui during part of the Yaqui Wars , specifically from 1825 until 1833 .
Peter Percival ( 24 July 1803 -- 11 July 1882 ) was a British born missionary , linguist and a pioneering educator in Sri Lanka and South India during the British colonial era .
Arthur Scherbius ( 30 October 1878 -- 13 May 1929 ) was a German electrical engineer who patented an invention for a mechanical cipher machine , later sold as the Enigma machine .
Henry Boot ( 1851 - -1931 ) was the founder of Henry Boot PLC . Henry Boot was the eldest surviving son of Charles and Ann Boot .

Jean De Bie ( 9 May 1892 -- 30 April 1961 ) was a Belgian football ( soccer ) player .
Sir John Bourke of Brittas ( 1550 -- 20 December 1607 ) , commonly called `` Captain of Clanwilliam '' , was born about the middle of the 16th century .

Catharina Margaretha Linck ( died 1721 ) was a Prussian woman who for most of her adult life presented herself as a man .
Saint Donatian ( 4th century - 390 ) is the patron saint of Bruges , Belgium , where his relics were enshrined in the ninth century .

Eileen Beasley ( 1921 -- 12 August 2012 ) was a Welsh teacher who , along with her husband Trefor , conducted a campaign of civil disobedience in the 1950s against the Rural District Council of Llanelly in a demand for council rate bills in the Welsh language .
Robert Whitworth ( 1734 -- 30 March 1799 ) was an English land surveyor and engineer , who learnt his trade under John Smeaton and James Brindley , and went on to become one of the leading canal engineers of his generation .

Johann Joseph Fux ( German : ( ˈfʊks ) ; c. 1660 -- 13 February 1741 ) was an Austrian composer , music theorist and pedagogue of the late Baroque era .
Kimberly Rogers ( c. 1961 -- 9 August 2001 ) was a Canadian whose death in 2001 , while under house arrest for welfare fraud , caused extensive controversy around Ontario Works ( the Ontario government 's welfare system ) .
Marc Delafontaine ( Born at Celigny , 1837 - -1911 ) was a Swiss chemist who in 1878 , along with Jacques - Louis Soret , first observed holmium spectroscopically .

H. Louis Nichols ( 7 November 1916- 25 April 2010 ) was an attorney who resided in Dallas , Texas .
Anne Hastings , Countess of Shrewsbury ( c. 1471 - -1520 ) was an English noblewoman who served as a lady - in - waiting to Queen consort Catherine of Aragon , the first wife of King Henry VIII of England .
Colonel Thomas Holbein Hendley CIE ( 21 April 1847 -- 2 February 1917 ) was a British medical officer in the Indian Medical Service and an amateur authority on Indian art . He studied at St. Bartholomew 's Hospital in London , where he was the gold medallist .

Johann Georg Haeselich ( also Haselick ; 30 August 1806 - 6 December 1894 ) was a German genre painter and lithographer .

Henry Beadman Bryant ( 1824 - -1892 ) was an author and co - founder and namesake of Bryant & Stratton College and Bryant University in Smithfield , Rhode Island .
Suzanne Bloch ( born in Geneva in 1907 - died in New York in 2002 ) was a Swiss - American musician and an influential pioneer of Early Music Revival during the 20th century .
Jules Semler - Collery ( 1902 - 1988 ) was a French composer , conductor and teacher .
William Abel Pantin FBA ( 1 May 1902 -- 10 November 1973 ) was an historian of mediaeval England who spent most of his academic life at the University of Oxford .
Louis Massignon ( 25 July 1883 -- 31 October 1962 ) was a Catholic scholar of Islam and a pioneer of Catholic- Muslim mutual understanding .
Dawachi ( Chinese : 达瓦齐 ; pinyin : dáwǎqí ; Mongolian : Даваач ; died 1759 ) was the last khan of the Dzungar Khanate from 1753 until his defeat at the hands of Qing and Mongol forces at Ili in 1755 .
Arthur Wolcott Yates ( died 1930 ) was a Brigadier General in the United States Army .
Dou Kang ( died 621 ) , courtesy name Daosheng , was an official and general during the Sui and Tang dynasties who briefly served as a chancellor early in the reign of Emperor Gaozu of Tang .
Robert B. Ingebretsen ( 30 March 1948 -- 2 March 2003 ) was a pioneer in the development of digital sound .
Samuel Snowden ( born c.1765 - died 1850 ) was a 19th - century African - American abolitionist and pastor of the May Street Church , one of the first black Methodist churches in Boston , Massachusetts .

Luís Carlos Nunes da Silva , nicknamed Carlinhos ( 19 November 1937 -- 22 June 2015 ) , played for Flamengo between 1958 and 1969 .
Wally Chalmers ( 16 September 1890 -- 17 November 1966 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Edward Harwood ( of Darwen ) ( 1707 - -1787 ) was an English composer of hymns , anthems and songs .
John Joseph Dougall ( 1860 -- 5 September 1934 ) was Mayor of Christchurch in 1911 - -1912 .
Robert Bruford ( 28 June 1868 -- 29 December 1939 ) was a British farmer and agriculturist who developed his activities into the political field .
Ulrich Bettac ( 2 May 1897 -- 20 April 1959 ) , born Ulrich Ewald Berthold Bettac , was a German - born Austrian actor and theatre director .
John Love Jones ( 1885 -- 21 December 1913 ) was a Welsh footballer who played in the Football League for Stoke and Middlesbrough , and he also made two appearances for Wales .
Leonard Hodgson ( 24 October 1889 in Fulham , London -- 15 July 1969 in Leamington Spa ) was an Anglican priest , philosopher , theologian , historian of the early Church and Regius Professor of Divinity at the University of Oxford from 1944 to 1958 .
Samoset , also Somerset , ( c. 1590 - -1653 ) was an Abenaki sagamore and the first Native American to make contact with the Pilgrims of Plymouth Colony .
Dr. Royal Wasson Sorensen ( April 25 , 1882 -- October 27 , 1965 ) was the inventor of the vacuum switch , professor of electrical engineering and head of the electrical engineering department at California Institute of Technology , and was also noted for his work in high voltage transmissions and air pollution .
George S. Cooper ( December 14 , 1864 -- 1929 ) was an American architect and builder from Washington , D.C. During his 40-year career , he was responsible for designing around 850 properties , including homes , commercial buildings and apartment buildings , several of which are listed on the National Register of Historic Places ( NRHP ) .
Jack Cannan ( 14 January 1899 -- 22 November 1965 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Edgar Baitzel ( 17 May 1955 -- 11 March 2007 ) was a German opera director and artistic administrator .
Zdenko Vinski ( 3 May 1913 -- 13 October 1996 ) was a notable Croatian archaeologist .
Wilfried Herling was killed on 28 November 1943 , when straffed on take - off by 15 IAP Yak 1s led by Kpt Leontiy .
Khouw Kim An , Majoor der Chinezen ( 1875 - 1945 ) was a prominent Chinese Indonesian public figure , patrician and landowner who served as the last Majoor der Chinezen ( `` Major of the Chinese '' ) of Batavia , Dutch East Indies ( now Jakarta ) .
Peter Francis Chenu ( 1760 - 1834 ) was a British sculptor of French birth working in the late 18th and early 19th century .
Ivan Maček ( 28 May 1908 -- 1 April 1993 ) was a Yugoslav Communist politician from Slovenia who served as the President of the People 's Assembly of SR Slovenia from 1963 to 1967 .
Wang Ruofei ( 11 October 1896 -- 8 April 1946 ) was a high - ranking member of the Chinese Communist Party .
Gianluigi Gasparetti ( 26 March 1958 -- 12 April 2013 ) , known by the pseudonym Oöphoi , was an Italian ambient musician .
Carlo Savina ( 2 August 1919 - 23 June 2002 ) was an Italian composer and conductor who composed , arranged , and conducted music for films - and is especially remembered for being the music director of films such as The Godfather ( 1972 ) , Amarcord ( 1973 ) , and The Bear ( 1988 ) .
Francis Rawle ( 1660 -- 5 March 1727 ) , originally from England , was a Quaker and colonist in Philadelphia , where he served in administrative positions and was a member of the assembly .
Emilio Vieyra ( 12 October 1920 -- 25 January 2010 ) , sometimes credited as Raúl Zorrilla , was an Argentine film director , actor , screenwriter and film producer , between 1950 and the 1990s .
Prince Joseph Ferdinand of Saxe - Coburg and Gotha ( full name Joseph Ferdinand Maria Michael Gabriel Raphael Gonzaga ; 21 May 1869 - 13 August 1888 ) , known in Brazil as Dom José Fernando , was a prince of the house of Saxe - Coburg - Gotha .
Dirk Albert Hooijer ( 30 May 1919 -- 26 November 1993 ) , often only known by his author abbreviation D. A. Hooijer , was a Dutch paleontologist .
Charles Liddell ( 1813 - 10 August 1894 ) , was an English railway engineer .
Otar Chkheidze ( 28 November 1920 . Village Kelktseuli , region of Gori , Georgia -- 2007 ) Georgian writer , literary man , PhD ( 1949 ) .
Nicolai Lumholtz ( 19 September 1729 -- 20 June 1819 ) was a Danish - Norwegian bishop .
Wilhelm Wegener ( 29 April 1895 -- 24 September 1944 ) was a German general of infantry , serving during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves and Swords .
Ramnad Krishnan ( 14 September 1918 - 29 January 1973 ) was a vocalist in the Carnatic tradition .
Samuel Chandanappally ( 13 May 1940 -- 3 July 2000 ) , who was born C.D. Samuel , was an Indian writer , college professor and orator .
Max Johannes Arildskov ( February 17 , 1896 -- 1986 ) was a Danish National Socialist political activist and collaborator prior to and during World War II .
Muhammad Abu Mansur al - Maturidi ( 853 - -944 AD ) ( Persian : محمد بن محمد بن محمود أبو منصور ماتریدی سمرقندی حنفی‎‎ ) was a scholar of Islamic jurisprudence and Qur'anic exegesis .
Anthony Bonvisi ( 1470s-1558 ) was an Italian emigrant to England .
James Hain Friswell ( 8 May 1825 -- 12 March 1878 ) was an English essayist and novelist .
Horace R. Cayton , Jr. ( 1903 - -1970 ) was a prominent American sociologist , newspaper columnist , and author who specialized in studies of working - class black Americans , particularly in mid-20th - century Chicago .
Artie Cambridge ( 25 December 1901 -- 30 July 1955 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
James Yimm Lee ( Chinese : 嚴鏡海 , published as James Y. Lee ) ( 1920 - 1972 ) was an American martial arts pioneer , teacher , author , and publisher .
Tsokye Dorje ( Tibetan : གཙོ་སྐྱེས་རྡོ་རྗེ , Wylie : mTs'o skyes rdo rje , 1450 - -1510 ) was a regent of Tibet who ruled in 1491 - -1499 .
Elizabeth Cowell ( 1912 - -1998 ) was a British broadcaster and the first woman television announcer .
Mhic Mac Comhaltan Ua Cleirigh ( died 1025 ) was King of Ui Fiachrach Aidhne .
Alexander Bonini ( ca . 1270 -- 1314 ) was an Italian Franciscan philosopher , who became Minister General of the Order of Friars Minor .
Vice Admiral Sir William Clarkson , KBE , CMG ( 26 March 1859 -- 21 January 1934 ) is regarded as the co - founder of the Royal Australian Navy ( RAN ) , in which he served as a senior commander .
Jassa Singh Ramgarhia ( 1723 - -1803 ) was a prominent Sikh leader during the period of the Sikh Confederacy .
Kessie Govender ( 1942 - -2002 ) was a pioneering voice in South African protest theatre , a playwright , actor and theatre director , who founded the Stable Theatre , a Durban - based theatre company in 1970 and is most known for his play , Working Class Hero ( 1979 ) and The Shack ( 1979 ) .
Alexander Peckover , 1st Baron Peckover FRGS , FSA , FLS ( 16 August 1830 -- 21 October 1919 ) , was a British Quaker banker , philanthropist and collector of ancient manuscripts .
Ivy Granstrom ( September 28 , 1911 -- April 14 , 2004 ) was a blind Canadian Masters athlete .
Barbro Eriksdotter ( Bielke ) ( died 1553 ) , known in history as Barbro Påle ( In English : `` Barbara Stake '' ) was a Swedish noble and land lord .
Nguyễn Văn Lém ( referred to as Captain Bảy Lốp ) ( 1931 or 1932 -- 1 February 1968 ) was a member of the National Liberation Front who was summarily executed in Saigon by General Nguyễn Ngọc Loan during the Tet Offensive .
Leigh Mercer ( 1893 - -1977 ) was a noted British wordplay and recreational mathematics expert .
Thorfinn of Hamar ( died 1285 ) was the Bishop of the Ancient Diocese of Hamar in medieval Norway .
Diego Marín Aguilera ( 1757 - -1799 ) was a Spanish inventor who was an early aviation pioneer .
Jagannath Sarkar ( 25 September 1919 -- 8 April 2011 ) was an Indian Communist leader , freedom fighter , and writer on social issues .
George Burnett Barton ( 9 December 1836 -- 12 September 1901 ) was an Australian lawyer , journalist and historian .
Aliki Diplarakou , Lady Russell ( Greek : Αλίκη Διπλαράκου ; 28 August 1912 -- 30 October 2002 ) , was the first Greek contestant to win the Miss Europe title .
Francis Maseres ( 15 December 1731 -- 19 May 1824 ) was an English lawyer .
Andrée Clair ( May 5 , 1916 - 1982 ) was a writer who was born in France , but is associated with Niger .
Hans Eleonardus Møller ( 8 November 1804 -- 12 September 1867 ) was a Norwegian politician and businessperson .
Bill Bowe ( 29 January 1879 -- 11 March 1920 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sigurd Christian Brinch ( 3 October 1874 -- 1956 ) was a Norwegian manager and politician .
Vice Admiral Vicente Merino Bielich ( 1889 - 1977 ) was a Chilean naval officer and political figure .
Christa Williams ( born : Christa Bojarzin 5 February 1926 -- 28 or 29 July 2012 ) was a German pop singer most popular in the late 1950s and early 1960s .
William C. Kingsley ( 1833 - 1885 ) was a construction contractor who is best known for being was one of the main figures involved in the creation of the Brooklyn Bridge
Jan Leśniak ( 1898 -- 1976 in Vienna ) was a Polish military intelligence officer in the Interbellum and World War II .
Ratu Josefa Celua ( circa 1855 -- 1886 ) was a Fijian chief from the island of Bau .
Edward Clarke Lowe ( 15 December 1823- March 30 , 1912 ) was an English educator and a key participant in the foundation and development of the Woodard Schools .
Maria Rosetti ( born Marie Grant ; 1819 -- February 25 ( O.S. February 13 ) 1893 ) was a Guernsey born Wallachian and Romanian political activist , journalist , essayist , philanthropist and socialite .
Laurence Michelmore ( 1909 -- April 10 , 1997 ) was UNRWA 's Commissioner - General from 1964 to 1971 .
Solomon Eccles ( 1618 - -1683 ) , also known as Solomon Eagle , was an English composer .
Hope Stevens ( 1905 in Tortola -- 1982 in Queens , New York ) was a lawyer and political activist .
Henry Frederick Beaumont DL JP ( 10 March 1833 , Scarborough -- 13 October 1913 , Ascot ) was a British Liberal and Liberal Unionist politician .
Edwin Alexander Forbes ( 1860 - -1915 ) , who served as the Adjutant General of California from 4 January 1911 to 18 June 1915 , is known as the Father of the California Cadet Corps .
William Ward , 3rd Viscount Dudley and Ward ( 21 January 1750 -- 25 April 1823 ) was a British peer and politician .
Umanji ( c. 1968 -- 26 February 2008 ) , born Maruti Johannes Nkuna , was a South African musician and singer - songwriter .
Hugh Buhrich ( 25 April 1911 -- 18 June 2004 ) was a German architect who arrived in Australia as a refugee from Nazi Germany before World War II . Buhrich 's practice , of 40 years , covered commercial and domestic projects .
Sir John Barnard Byles ( 11 January 1801 -- 3 February 1884 ) was a British barrister , judge and author of books on law and the economy .
Helen Fairchild Smith ( died 1926 ) was the daughter of Augustus William Smith .
William Carrick ( Russian : Вильям Андреевич Каррик ) ( 31 December 1827 -- 11 November 1878 ) was a Scottish - Russian artist and photographer .
Edward Bernard `` Bernie '' Kirwan Ward ( 2 April 1909 -- 5 March 1983 ) was a journalist most notable for his work with the Daily News in Perth , Western Australia .
Louis Henri de Pardaillan de Gondrin , marquis de Montespan ( 1640 -- 1 December 1691 ) , was a French nobleman , most notable as the husband of Louis XIV 's mistress Madame de Montespan .
Göran Liljestrand ( 16 April 1886 -- 16 January 1968 ) , Swedish pharmacologist , known for the discovery of the Euler - Liljestrand mechanism .
Potapy Emelianov ( 1884 , Ufa Guberniya , Russian Empire - 14 August 1936 , Karelian ASSR , USSR ) was a Russian Catholic priest and confessor .
Henry Jeanes ( 1611 - -1662 ) was an English clergyman and puritan controversialist .
Barbara Leonie Picard ( 17 December 1917 -- 15 December 2011 ) was a British writer of children 's books , known best for historical fiction and for retellings of ancient myths and medieval legends .
Dr. Peter Cormac Sutherland ( 1822 - 30 November 1900 ) Born in Newlands of Forse , near Latheron , Caithness , Scotland .
George Picknell ( 29 November 1813 -- 26 February 1863 ) was an English cricketer active from 1835 to 1854 who played for Sussex .
Marcella Lotti della Santa ( sometimes incorrectly called Marcellina ) ( September 1831 - 9 February 1901 ) was an Italian opera singer who had an active international career during the 1850s and 1860s .
Foster Bell ( 1814 - 1857 ) was a British jockey who most notably won the 1845 Epsom Derby on The Merry Monarch .
Vito Taccone ( 6 May 1940 -- 15 October 2007 ) was an Italian road cyclist .
Jean Poton de Xaintrailles ( 1390 ? -- 7 October 1461 ) , a minor noble of Gascon origin , was one of the chief lieutenants of Joan of Arc .
William Byrd I ( 1652 -- 4 December 1704 ) was a native of Shadwell , London , England .
Charles Perry or Chuck Perry ( 1937 - -1999 ) , was the founding president of Florida International University in Miami , having pushed for the university 's founding from 1943 until 1965 .
Dr. Branko Švarc ( 1894 - -1972 ) was Croatian judge and Mayor of Koprivnica .
Walter de Merton ( c. 1205 -- 27 October 1277 ) was Bishop of Rochester and founder of Merton College , Oxford .
Enrique Flamini also known as Enrico Flamini ( 17 April 1917 -- 11 January 1982 ) was an Argentine - Italian footballer and manager .
Isaac Reed ( 1 January 1742 -- 5 January 1807 ) was an English Shakespearean editor .
Baron John Both de Bajna ( Croatian : Ivan Bot od Bajne , Hungarian : bajnai Both János ; ? -- 1493 ) was a Hungarian nobleman from the Both family , who served as , alongside Emeric Derencsényi , Ban of Croatia , Slavonia and Dalmatia in 1493 .
His Worship John Cottesmore SL JP ( died 29 August 1439 ) was a British justice of unknown origin .
Guillermina Green ( 1922 - -2006 ) , also known as Guillermina Grin , was a Spanish film actress .
Yazid ibn al - Walid ibn ' Abd al - Malik or Yazid III ( 701 -- 25 September 744 ) ( Arabic : يزيد بن الوليد بن عبد الملك‎ ) was an Umayyad caliph .
Erwin Knoll ( 1931 - -1994 ) was an American journalist who was editor of The Progressive from 1973 to 1994 .
John Kuzhinapurath , OIC , ( 1904 - -1994 ) was among the first priests who united with the Catholic Church along with Archbishop Mar Ivanios on 20 September 1930 in the process of the formation of the Syro - Malankara Catholic Church .
Carl Peter Holbøll ( born 31 December 1795 in Copenhagen -- deceased 1856 in the North Atlantic ) was an officer in the Danish Royal Navy , Greenland colonial officer and explorer of the Greenlandic fauna .
Petro Mirchuk ( Ukrainian : Петро Мірчук ) ( 1913 - -1999 ) was a Ukrainian writer living in United States and a leading member of the Ukrainian liberation movement ( Organization of Ukrainian Nationalists ) .
General John Burgoyne ( 24 February 1722 -- 4 August 1792 ) was a British army officer , politician and dramatist .
Alexander Roderick McLeod ( c. 1782 -- 11 June 1840 ) was a fur trader and explorer who began his career with the North West Company in 1802 .
Michael J. Cullen ( 1884 - -1936 ) was an American entrepreneur and salesman of Irish descent , perhaps best known as the founder of the King Kullen grocery store chain , widely considered to be the first supermarket founded in America .
Shaban Gashi ( 1939 - -1990 ) was a Yugoslav cinematographer and photographer .
Frederick Piper ( 23 September 1902 -- 22 September 1979 ) was an English actor who appeared in over 80 films and many television productions in a career spanning over 40 years .
Peter William Clayden ( 20 October 1827 -- 19 February 1902 ) was a British Nonconformist and Liberal journalist and author .
Reverend Richard Boys MA ( 1785 - -1867 ) was a Church of England clergyman and author , most notable for his tenure as Chaplain on St. Helena at the time of Napoleon Bonaparte 's exile there .
Samuel Fischer , later Samuel von Fischer ( 24 December 1859 -- 15 October 1934 ) , was a Hungarian - born German publisher , the founder of S. Fischer Verlag .
Hugo Erich Meyer von Klinggräff ( 7 June 1820 in Klein Watkowitz , Stuhm -- 3 April 1902 in Paleschken , Stuhm ) was a German botanist specialist of bryophytes .
Piotr Wawrzyniak ( 30 January 1849 in Wyrzeka -- 9 November 1910 in Poznań ) was a Polish priest , economic and educational activist , patron of the Union of the Earnings and Economic Societies ( Związek Spółek Zarobkowych i Gospodarczych ) .
Ghiyath al - Din Kaykhusraw II or Ghiyāth ad - Dīn Kaykhusraw bin Kayqubād ( Persian : غياث الدين كيخسرو بن كيقباد‎‎ ) was the sultan of the Seljuqs of Rûm from 1237 until his death in 1246 .
Nikolaus Gerbel ( or Gerbellius ) ( c. 1485 -- 1560 ) was a German humanist , jurist and doctor of both laws .
Raoul III of Tosny ( † c. 1126 ) , seigneur de Conches - en - Ouche , was an Anglo - Norman nobleman of the house of Tosny .
Simon Henry Adolph , Count of Lippe - Detmold ( born : 25 January 1694 ; died : 12 October 1734 ) was a ruler of the county of Lippe .
Pope Eusebius ( from Greek Εὐσέβιος `` pious '' ; died 17 August 309 or 310 ) was the Bishop of Rome from 18 April to his death in 309 or 310 .
Empress Liu E ( 劉娥 ) ( died 314 ) , courtesy name Lihua ( 麗華 ) , formally Empress Wuxuan ( 武宣皇后 , literally `` the martial and responsible empress '' ) was an empress of the Chinese / Xiongnu state Han Zhao .
Daniel Camargo Barbosa ( 22 January 1930 -- 13 November 1994 ) was a Colombian psychopathic serial killer .
Nafiz Bezhani ( 1928 - -2004 ) was an Albanian jurist , politician and writer .
Wolf Huber ( c. 1485 -- June 3 , 1553 ) was an Austrian painter , printmaker , and architect , a leading member of the Danube School .
Anton Fils ( also Antonín Fils , Johann Anton Fils , Johann Anton Filtz ) , 22 September 1733 ( baptized ) -- 14 March 1760 ( buried ) was a German classical composer .
Adolf Rusch von Ingweiler ( ca . 1435 - 26 May 1489 in Straßburg ) was a notable German printer and publisher .
Murray Hantman ( 1904 - -1999 ) was a painter , muralist , and teacher .
Norman Mitchell Driver , better known as Norman Mitchell ( 27 August 1918 -- 19 March 2001 ) was an English television , stage and film actor .
Alan Wheatley ( 19 April 1907 -- 30 August 1991 ) was an English actor and former radio announcer .
John Swinton , Lord Swinton ( 1723 - -1799 ) was a Scottish lawyer , judge and writer .
Adam Kok III ( 16 October 1811 - 30 December 1875 ) was a leader of the Griqua people in South Africa .
Gbenga Adeboye ( 1959 - April 2003 ) was a Nigerian singer , comedian , radio presenter and master of ceremony .
Rebecca Agatha Armour ( 25 October 1845 -- 24 April 1891 ) was a Canadian teacher and novelist born in Fredericton , New Brunswick .
Lena Gurr ( 1897 - -1992 ) , was an American artist who made paintings , prints , and drawings showing , as one critic said , `` the joys and sorrows of everyday life . ''
M. Antoine Craan ( 17 January 1931 -- 12 January 2010 ) was a Haitian - Canadian soccer player and one of the first black professional soccer players in Quebec province .
Andrew Hannah ( 17 September 1864 -- 17 June 1940 ) was a Scottish international footballer who missed just two games at right back in Everton 's 1890 - -91 title winning season .
Georg Braathe ( 15 December 1903 -- 23 May 1968 ) was a Norwegian long - distance runner who specialized in the 5000 and 10,000 metres .
Tudor Ganea ( 1922 - -1971 ) was a Romanian mathematician , known for his work in algebraic topology , especially homotopy theory .
Mihemed Şêxmûs Salih ( 1948 - -1989 ) , also known as Mihemed Şêxo in Kurdish , was one of the most important Kurdish folk singers .
Abdul Razak Abdul Hamid ( 7 July 1925 -- 18 July 2013 ) was a Malaysian academic and the only Malaysian survivor of the atomic bombing of Hiroshima on 6 August 1945 .
Antonio Beltrami ( 1724 - -1784 ) was an Italian painter active in the late - Baroque and Neoclassic periods .
Aldo Massola ( September 9 , 1910 -- July 6 , 1975 ) was an Italian - Australian anthropologist , a curator at the National Museum of Victoria in Melbourne from 1954 to 1964 , who overcame scandal in his personal life to author a number of influential books about Victoria 's indigenous Koori population .
George Stiff ( 1807 - -1873 ) was an English engraver and newspaper proprietor .
Huda bin Abdul Haq ( also known as Ali Ghufron , Muklas or Mukhlas ) ( February 1960 -- 9 November 2008 ) was an Indonesian who was convicted and executed for his role in coordinating the 2002 Bali bombings , an act of terrorism .
Lancelot Ridley ( died 1576 ) , was an English clergyman , known as a theological writer , and rector of St James ' Church , Stretham , Cambridgeshire .
Danny Powell ( 29 May 1922 -- 27 January 2013 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Anna Vigfúsdóttir á Stóru - Borg ( died 1571 ) , was an active Icelandic landlord .
Wilhelm Roser ( 26 March 1817 -- 16 December 1888 ) was a German surgeon and ophthalmologist .
Walter Brooks ( 1 April 1832 - 14 March 1907 ) was a Professor of Music and an organist based in Birmingham .
Vijaya Raje Scindia ( 12 October 1919 -- 25 January 2001 ) born Lekha Divyeshwari and known popularly as the Rajmata of Gwalior , was a prominent Indian political personality .
Ngô Văn Chiêu ( 28 February 1878 -- 1932 ) was the first disciple of Đức Cao Đài .
Charles Henry Pearson ( 7 September 1830 -- 29 May 1894 ) was a British - born Australian historian , educationist , politician and journalist .
John Poyntz ( ca . 1485 -- 1544 ) was an English courtier and politician , Member of Parliament for Devizes in 1529 .
Peter Alexander Hay ( 1866 - -1952 ) R.I. , R.S.W. , R.B.C. was a Scottish genre , still - life , portrait and landscape watercolourist .
Ernest Melville Charles Guest DFC ( May 1920 -- 4 October 1943 ) was a Southern Rhodesian Royal Air Force pilot of the Second World War .
Andargachew Messai ( 25 March 1902 - 16 August 1981 ) was an Ethiopian diplomat and the husband of Princess Tenagnework Haile Selassie of Ethiopia , the eldest child of Emperor Haile Selassie and Empress Menen Asfaw .
Pierre - Philippe Thomire ( 1751 - -1843 ) a French sculptor , was the most prominent bronzier , or producer of ornamental patinated and gilt - bronze objects and furniture mounts of the First French Empire .
Shunkan ( 俊寛 ) ( c. 1143 -- 1179 ) was a Japanese monk who , after taking part in the Shishigatani plot to overthrow Taira no Kiyomori , was exiled along with two others to Kikai - ga - shima .
Lê Văn Hưu ( 1230 - -1322 ) was an historian of the Trần Dynasty .
Ivan Fredericks ( 1864 - -1904 ) , known as Russian Jack ( Русский Джек ) , was a goldminer of the Western Australian gold rush in the 1880s .
Rev. Hon . Edward Lyttelton ( 23 July 1855 -- 26 January 1942 ) was an English sportsman , schoolmaster and cleric from the Lyttelton family .
Sam Ybarra ( 1945 - 1982 ) was a United States Army soldier who served in the Tiger Force commando unit attached to the 101st Airborne Division during the Vietnam War .
Gerry Henry ( 5 October 1920 -- 1979 ) was a professional footballer who played for Leeds United , Bradford Park Avenue , Sheffield Wednesday and Halifax Town .
Christine Sophie von Gähler , née von Ahlefeldt , ( 1745 -- 18 July 1792 ) , was a Danish noble and courtier , known for her love life and unconventional life style , known in history as one of the Three Graces of the Danish royal court .
Ananus ben Ananus ( Hebrew : חנן בן חנן Hanan ben Hanan Greek : Ἀνάνου Ἄνανος `` Ananos son of Ananos '' var : Ananias , Latin : Anani Ananus or Ananus filius Anani ) , d. 68 CE , was a Herodian - era High Priest of Israel in Jerusalem , Iudaea Province .
Cellach Cualann mac Gerthidi ( died 715 ) was the last Uí Máil king of Leinster .
William Strang , 1st Baron Strang GCMG KCB MBE ( 2 January 1893 -- 27 May 1978 ) was a British diplomat who served as a leading adviser to the British Government from the 1930s to the 1950s and as Permanent Under - Secretary at the Foreign Office from 1949 to 1953 .
Joost Baljeu ( 1 November 1925 -- 1 July 1991 ) was a Dutch painter , sculptor and writer .
Mariyam Kaba'afa'anu Rani Kilege ( died 1691 ) , was a Sultana consort of the Maldives , married to sultan Ibrahim Iskander I of the Maldives .
Thomas Sparke ( 1548 - -1616 ) was an English clergyman , who represented the Puritan point of view both at the 1584 Lambeth Conference and the 1604 Hampton Court Conference .
Andrew Rutherford , 1st Earl of Teviot ( died 4 May 1664 ; sometimes spelt `` Rutherfurd '' ) was a Scottish soldier .
Petar Zinaić ( died 2008 in Belgrade at the age of 90 ) was a Serb Partisan who was the first member of the force to be investigated for war crimes by the Republic of Croatia .
Acting Captain Michael Floud Blaney GC ( 14 November 1910 -- 13 December 1940 ) , known as Max Blaney , was posthumously awarded the George Cross for defusing enemy bombs during the Blitz in 1940 .
Thomas Boleyn , 1st Earl of Wiltshire , 1st Earl of Ormond , 1st Viscount Rochford KG KB ( c. 1477 -- 12 March 1539 ) was an English diplomat and politician in the Tudor era .
Henriette Louise de Bourbon ( Henriette Louise Marie Françoise Gabrielle ; 15 January 1703 -- 19 September 1772 ) was a French Princess by birth and a member of the House of Bourbon .
Archibald Seton ( 1758- 30 March 1818 ) was a Scottish East India Company colonial administrator , Resident and Civil servant .
James Sterling Tippett ( September 7 , 1885 in Memphis , Missouri -- 1958 ) was an American educator and children 's writer .
Baron Johann Wilhelm von Müller ( 4 March 1824 -- 24 October 1866 ) was a German ornithologist and explorer .
João Rodrigues Esteves ( c. 1700 - -c . 1751 ) was a portuguese composer of religious music .
Arvid Kurck ( also known as Arvid Kurki , born 1464 in Vesilahti , died 22 July 1522 in Öregrund ) was the Roman Catholic Bishop of Turku from 1510 to 1522 .
Adityawarman then founded the royal dynasty of Minangkabau in Pagarruyung and presided over the central Sumatra region to take control of the gold trade between 1347 and 1375 .
Frank O'Connor ( born Michael Francis O'Donovan ; 17 September 1903 -- 10 March 1966 ) was an Irish writer of over 150 works , best known for his short stories and memoirs .
Bertha Felicitas Sophie Freifrau von Suttner ( Baroness Bertha von Suttner , née Countess Kinsky , Gräfin Kinsky von Wchinitz und Tettau ; 9 June 1843 -- 21 June 1914 ) was a Czech - Austrian pacifist and novelist .
Peter Handford ( 21 March 1919 -- 6 November 2007 ) was an English location sound recordist .
Henrik Bech ( c.1718 -- 1776 ) was a Danish - born wood carver who settled in Norway from around 1750 .
Charles James Apperley ( 1777 -- 19 May 1843 ) , English sportsman and sporting writer , better known as Nimrod , the pseudonym under which he published his works on the chase and on the turf , was born at Plasgronow , near Wrexham , in Denbighshire , North Wales in 1777 .
Sisto Fabri ( 1540 - -1594 ) was a theologian and canon lawyer of the Dominican Order who was appointed Master of the Sacred Palace by Pope Gregory XIII serving from 1580 to 1583 , and Master of the Order of Preachers from 1583 to 1589 .
Sahana Devi ( Bengali : সাহানা দেবী ) ( 1897 - -1990 ) was an Indian singer , she was a widely listened to singer of Rabindra Sangeet .
Sir John Finet or Finett ( 1571 - -1641 ) was the English Master of the Ceremonies in the Stuart court .
Keith Falconer Fletcher was born in Altamont , New York , on September 24 , 1900 and died in Modesto , California , in 1987 .
Adam Opel ( 9 May 1837 -- 8 September 1895 ) was the founder of the German automobile company Adam Opel AG .
Dharma Manikya II ( ruled 1714 - 1733 ) was the king of Tripura Kingdom from 1714 until 1733 , although his power was greatly diminished in 1732 with the rise to power of Jagat Manikya with the aid of the Nawab of Bengal , Shuja - ud - Din Muhammad Khan .
Ifor Pritchard ( 1940 - 9 October 2010 ) was an artist and former art teacher predominantly at Ysgol Sir Huw Owen , Caernarfon in North Wales , retiring in 1992 .
Alija Alijagić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Алија Алијагић ; 1896 -- 8 March 1922 ) was a Bosnian communist and assassin known for murdering Milorad Drašković .
Dr Ronald Ian Currie FRSE CBE ( 1928 - 1996 ) was a Scottish marine biologist .
Edward Montagu , 1st Baron Montagu of Boughton KB ( aka Sir Knight Edward Montague of Boughton Castle ) ( 1563 -- 15 June 1644 ) was an English politician .
Archibald Paton Thornton ( 1921 -- 19 February 2004 ) was an academic and historian .
Sofia Lovisa Gråå née Palm , ( 1749 -- 8 May 1835 ) was a Swedish educator of actors , and noted for innovations that in modern times would be described as feminist .
Sir William Scott , 6th Baronet ( 26 July 1803 -- 12 October 1871 ) was a Scottish Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1829 to 1830 and 1859 to 1870 .
Aditya I ( c. 870 -- c. 907 CE ) , the son of Vijayalaya , was the Chola king who extended the Chola dominions by the conquest of the Pallavas and occupied the Western Ganga Kingdom .
William Douglas Allen ( 27 July 1914 -- 7 May 2008 ) was a physicist and electrical engineer .
Sir Nicholas de Loveyne ( died 24 September 1375 ) was a major English property owner and courtier , who held a number of senior positions in the service of King Edward III .
Marjorie Best ( 10 April 1903 -- 14 June 1997 ) was an American Hollywood costume designer best known for her period designs .
Friedrich Gabriel Sulzer ( 10 October 1749 -- 14 December 1830 ) was a German physician from Gotha , Thuringia .
Sir Bevis Bulmer ( 1536 - -1615 ) was an English mining engineer during the reigns of Elizabeth I and James I. He has been called ' one of the great speculators of that era ' .
Stanley Dimbleby ( 27 November 1916 -- 17 October 1992 ) was an English footballer who played at left - half for Hull City and Port Vale .
William E. Henry ( 1918 - -1994 ) was an American psychologist who worked on projective personality assessment , particularly in relation to executive leadership .
Jean Balthasar Tricklir ( 1750 -- 29 November 1813 ) was a French cellist and composer of German descent .
Jacob Stainer ( c. 1619 -- 1683 ) was the earliest and best known Austrian luthier .
John Arnull ( 1753 - 1815 ) was an English flat racing jockey .
Dennis Griffiths ( 8 December 1933 -- 24 December 2015 ) was a British journalist and newspaper historian .
Johanna Magdalena Catharina Judith van Dorth ( 7 May 1747 , Warnsveld - 22 November 1799 , Winterswijk ) , known as Freule Van Dorth ( Lady of Dorth ) , was a Dutch orangist and aristocrat .
Mosalikanti Thirumala Rao ( Telugu : మొసలికంటి తిరుమలరావు ) ( b : 29 January 1901 - d : 1970 ) was an Indian freedom activist and Parliament member .
Dejazmatch Haregot Abbai ( Abay ) KCVO ( Knight Commander of the Victorian Order ) ( 1909 - 1979 ) was an Eritrean businessman and politician .
Luigi Pistilli ( 19 July 1929 -- 21 April 1996 ) was an Italian actor of stage , screen , and television .
Sir David Napley ( 25 July 1915 -- 24 September 1994 ) was an English solicitor .
Joachim Sadrozinski ( 9 September 1907 -- 29 September 1944 ) was a German officer who took part in the 20 July plot .
Louis Philippe de Bombelles ( German : Ludwig Philipp von Bombelles ; 1 July 1780 - 7 July 1843 ) was an Austrian count and diplomat .
Robert Priday ( 29 March 1925 -- 30 September 1998 ) was a South African footballer who played as a midfielder for Liverpool F.C. in The Football League .
Melvin H. Ribble ( 11 January 1870 Nodaway , Iowa -- 3 May 1964 Lincoln , Nebraska ) was an American cornetist , baritone hornist , and prolific composer and arranger of concert band music .
Mohammed Kaghat ( 1942 - -2001 ) is a Moroccan playwright , actor and stage director .
Alberto Collo ( 6 May 1883 -- 7 May 1955 ) was an Italian actor who appeared in more than a hundred and thirty films during his career , mostly during the silent era .
Gertrude Bugler ( 1897 -- 1992 ) was a British stage actress of the Edwardian Era best known for acting in plays adapted by Thomas Hardy .
Henry de Vere , 18th Earl of Oxford KB ( 24 February 1593 -- June 1625 ) was an English aristocrat , courtier and soldier .
Ladislau de Souza Mello Netto ( 1838 - -1894 ) was a Brazilian botanist and director of the Brazilian National Museum in Rio de Janeiro .
Pieter Harting ( 27 February 1812 -- 3 December 1885 ) was a Dutch biologist and naturalist , born in Rotterdam .
Agnes Marion McLean Walsh ( née Gibson ; 10 June 1884 -- 12 August 1967 ) was head matron of King Edward Memorial Hospital , a Western Australian maternity hospital .
James Hinks ( born 1829 in Mullingar , Ireland - died 1878 ) bred and named the English Bull Terrier in the 1860s , as well as the English White Terrier .
Tom Sadlier ( 21 February 1890 -- 26 July 1960 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy and Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Paul Emmert ( 1826 - 1867 ) , who is also known as Paul Emert , was an artist born near Berne , Switzerland in 1826 .
Saint Henry Morse ( 1595 -- 1 February 1645 ) was one of the Catholic Forty Martyrs of England and Wales .
Florent le Comte ( 1655 -- 1712 ) , was a French writer and engraver .
Waheed uz - Zaman Kiranawi ( Arabic : وحيد الزمان‎ ) ( 1930 - 1995 ) was an Sunni Islamic scholar from India .
Gulielmus Bucanus ( Guillaume Du Buc , in English William Bucanus ) ( died 1603 ) was a Swiss - French Calvinist theologian .
Bernard Youens ( born Bernard Arthur Popley ; 28 December 1914 -- 27 August 1984 ) was an English character actor , best remembered for his portrayal of the workshy , beer - swilling Stan Ogden in Coronation Street from 1964 until his death in 1984 .
Marjorie Lynette Sigley ( 22 December 1928 -- 13 August 1997 ) , also known as Sigi , was an English artist , writer , actress , teacher , choreographer , theatre director and television producer .
The Honourable Sir Humphrey Maud KCMG ( 17 April 1934 -- 10 November 2013 ) was a British diplomat .
Julius Hirsch ( 7 April 1892 -- declared dead 8 May 1945 ) was a German international footballer who was killed during the Holocaust .
Carlo Ignazio Monza ( c. 1680 or 1696 - 9 May 1739 ) was an Italian composer .
Christopher Deighton ( died 1605 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1572 and 1605 .
François Deguelt ( born Louis Deghelt , 4 December 1932 -- 22 January 2014 ) was a French singer , best known for his participation on behalf of Monaco in the Eurovision Song Contests of 1960 and 1962 .
Sir George Francis Hill KCB ( 22 December 1867 - -18 October 1948 ) was the Director and Principal Librarian of the British Museum ( 1931 - -1936 ) .
James Bertie , 1st Earl of Abingdon ( 16 June 1653 -- 22 May 1699 ) , styled Hon . James Bertie until 1657 and known as the 5th Baron Norreys from 1657 until 1682 , was an English nobleman .
Rosalie von Rauch ( Rosalie Wilhelmine Johanna ; 29 August 1820 -- 5 March 1879 ) , was a German noblewoman and since 1853 , Countess of Hohenau .
Marie Hicks ( December 20 , 1923 -- 19 April 2007 ) was an African American civil rights activist best known for leading thousands of pickets in 1965 - 1966 around the wall at Girard College .
Iovan Tsaous ( Greek : Γιοβάν Τσαούς , from the Turkish word çavuş , meaning `` sergeant '' ) ( 1893 - -1942 ) , was a Greek musician and composer of rebetiko songs from Pontus .
Tombs & Treasure ( Taiyou no Shinden Asteka II in Japan ) is an adventure game originally developed by Nihon Falcom in 1987 for the PC-8801 , PC-9801 , FM-7 and X1 Japanese computer systems .
NFL ' 97 is a follow - up video game to Sega 's classic Joe Montana series on the Sega Mega Drive / Genesis .
Nervous Brickdown ( known as SuperLite 2500 Brickdown and published by Success in Japan ) is a breakout clone video game developed by the French team Arkedo Studio and published by Eidos Interactive for Nintendo DS .
RealSports Boxing is a boxing based video game developed by Atari and released in 1987 for the Atari 2600 .
Pipe Mania is a puzzle game developed in 1989 by The Assembly Line for the Amiga .
The Gay Nighties is a 1933 American Pre - Code comedy film featuring Clark & McCullough and directed by Mark Sandrich .
Rahtree Reborn ( Thai : บุปผาราตรี 3.1 ) ( also known as Buppah Rahtree 3.1 ) is a 2009 Thai comedy - horror film written and directed by Yuthlert Sippapak .
Money Movers is a 1978 Australian crime action drama film directed by Bruce Beresford .
Everything 's Ducky is a 1961 comedy film directed by Don Taylor and written by Benedict Freedman annd John Fenton Murray .
Second Best Bed is a 1938 British comedy film directed by Tom Walls and starring Walls , Jane Baxter and Veronica Rose .

Ivan Petrella holds a Bachelor 's degree from Georgetown University 's School of Foreign Service , a Masters of Theological Studies from Harvard Divinity School and a Ph.D. in Religion and Law from Harvard University 's Committee on the Study of Religion in the Graduate School of Arts and Sciences .
Angela Hill grew up in Corpus Christi , Texas and graduated from the University of Texas at Austin in 1972 with a Bachelor of Arts degree in Journalism .
After his education , Raymond Barre was professor of economics at Institut d'Etudes Politiques de Paris ( Sciences Po ) .
Donald Malcolm Maxwell ( b 1934 , Watford , England - d 2007 , Scottsdale , Arizona ) was the 19th President of Pacific Union College .
Eli Upfal is a computer science researcher currently a professor in the computer science department at Brown University .
Saadi Lahlou is Professor in Social Psychology , in the Department of Social Psychology at the London School of Economics .
Owen Bennett - Jones is a freelance British journalist and one of the hosts of Newshour on the BBC World Service .
Robert W. Brodersen ( born November 1 , 1945 ) is a professor of electrical engineering , now emeritus , and a founder of the Berkeley Wireless Research Center ( BWRC ) at the University of California , Berkeley .
Heinrich Rombach ( 10 June 1923 in Freiburg i m Breisgau -- 5 February 2004 in Würzburg ) was a German philosopher and professor of philosophy at the University of Würzburg .
Franco P. Preparata is a computer scientist , the An Wang Professor , Emeritus , of Computer Science at Brown University .
Barbara Sturgeon is a British radio presenter and winner of two Sony Radio Awards for a show she presented on BBC Radio Kent during the 1980s .
Boaventura de Sousa Santos is a Professor at the School of Economics at the University of Coimbra , Distinguished Legal Scholar at the University of Wisconsin - Madison Law School , Global Legal Scholar at the University of Warwick and Director of the Centre for Social Studies ( CES ) at the University of Coimbra .
Marco Keiner ( * 13 . April 1963 in Überlingen , Germany ) is Director , Environment , Housing and Land Management Division at the United Nations Economic Commission for Europe ( UNECE ) .
L. John Doerr ( born June 29 , 1951 ) is an American venture capitalist at Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers in Menlo Park , California , in Silicon Valley .
Harold Garfinkel ( October 29 , 1917 -- April 21 , 2011 ) was an American sociologist , ethnomethodologist , and a Professor Emeritus at the University of California , Los Angeles .
Bruno Bosteels ( Dutch : ( ˈbɔsteːls ) ; born 1967 , Leuven , Belgium ) is a literary critic , a translator , and Professor of Romance Studies at Cornell University .
Bo Asplund currently serves as United Nations Secretary - General 's Deputy Special Representative for Afghanistan , the United Nations Resident Coordinator and the Humanitarian Coordinator in Afghanistan .
Pierre L. van den Berghe ( born 1933 ) is professor emeritus of sociology and anthropology at the University of Washington , where he has worked since 1965 .
John Castell ( aka John Castle ) ( c.1280 - -1426 ) was a Master of University College , Oxford , and later a Chancellor of the University of Oxford .
Derek Gregory Ph.D. ( Cantab ) FBA , FRSC ( born 1 March 1951 ) is a British academic and world - renowned geographer who is currently Peter Wall Distinguished Professor and Professor of Geography at the University of British Columbia in Vancouver .
Fred W. Friendly ( October 30 , 1915 -- March 3 , 1998 ) was a president of CBS News and the creator , along with Edward R. Murrow , of the documentary television program See It Now .
David E. Spencer is a professor of economics at Brigham Young University .
Robert Melson ( born 1937 ) is professor emeritus of political science and a member of the Jewish studies program at Purdue University , in Indiana , United States .
Hamid Mirzadeh ( Persian : حمید میرزاده , born November 29 , 1950 ) is an Iranian politician and academic who is the 3rd and current president of the Islamic Azad University system .
Brad Buckley ( born 1952 in Sydney ) is an artist , activist , urbanist and Professor of Contemporary Art and Culture at Sydney College of the Arts , University of Sydney .
Uk Heo is a professor of political science in the University of Wisconsin-- Milwaukee .
Maria Mavroudi ( born 1967 ) is a history professor at University of California , Berkeley .
Maged N. Kamel Boulos is a British health informatician , scientist and Professor of Digital Health currently based at the Alexander Graham Bell Centre of Digital Health , University of the Highlands and Islands , having worked before that at the University of Plymouth , at the University of Bath and at City University London .
Keith DeRose ( born April 24 , 1962 ) is an American philosopher teaching at Yale University in New Haven , Connecticut , where he is currently Allison Foundation Professor of Philosophy .
Ernst Mohr was a professor of mechanical engineering at the University of Wuppertal .
Shrawan Kumar is the John R. and Louise S. Parker distinguished professor of mathematics at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill .
Abdul Kamara is the United Nations Joint Special Representative in Darfur .
Patchen Markell ( born August 30 , 1969 ) is an associate professor of political science at the University of Chicago .
