Hernán Lara Zavala ( born 28 February 1946 ) is a Mexican novelist and academic at the National Autonomous University of Mexico .
Edward Loranus Rice ( 1871 - 1960 ) was a biologist and educator who served as the acting president of Ohio Wesleyan University .
Leon Katz ( born July 10 , 1919 ) is professor emeritus of drama at Yale University .
Murray Rosenblatt ( born September 7 , 1926 ) is a statistician specializing in time series analysis who is a professor of mathematics at the University of California , San Diego .
Huỳnh Công Út , known professionally as Nick Ut ( born March 29 , 1951 ) , is a photographer for the Associated Press ( AP ) who works out of Los Angeles .
Kate McAll is Executive Producer , Radio Drama at BBC Wales .
Alfonso Gómez - Lobo ( January 1 , 1940 -- December 31 , 2011 ) was a professor of metaphysics and moral philosophy at Georgetown University known for his critical evaluations of modern day ethics .
Lenni Montiel is the United Nations Assistant Secretary - General for Economic Development in the Department of Economic and Social Affairs .
Hugh Heclo ( born 1943 ) is a Clarence J. Robinson Professor of Public Affairs at George Mason University , in the United States .
Richard T. Sullivan ( died 1981 ) was a novelist , short - story writer , and member of the faculty of the University of Notre Dame .
Nihad Awad ( Arabic : نهاد عوض ) is the Executive Director and Founder of the Council on American - Islamic Relations ( CAIR ) .
Bernhard Gröschel studied Slavic Studies , General Linguistics , Phonetics and Communication Studies at the University of Bonn .
Michael Brian Cookson OBE ( born 22 June 1951 ) is the president of the Union Cycliste Internationale ( UCI ) , having been elected to the post in September 2013 .
Joseph L. Armstrong was a professor at Duke University ( at the time , called `` Trinity College '' ) best known for reforming Duke 's curriculum in the late nineteenth century , changing it to a German research university model with the help of John Franklin Crowell .
A. Michael Noll ( born 1939 , Newark , New Jersey ) is an American engineer , and professor emeritus at the Annenberg School for Communication and Journalism at the University of Southern California .
Allan H. MacDonald is an theoretical condensed matter physicist and the Sid W. Richardson Foundation Regents Chair Professor of Physics at The University of Texas at Austin .
Bhubaneswar Mishra ( or Bud Mishra , born 9 November 1961 ) is an Indian American computer scientist and professor at the Courant Institute of Mathematical Sciences of New York University .
Lonnie D. Bentley ( born 1957 ) is an American computer scientist , and Professor and former Department Head of Computer and Information Technology at Purdue University , known with Kevin C. Dittman and Jeffrey L. Whitten as co - author of the textbook Systems Analysis and Design Methods , which is now in its 7th edition .
Daniel Fessler is a Professor of Biological Anthropology at the University of California , Los Angeles , working in the fields of evolutionary psychology , evolutionary anthropology , and evolutionary medicine .
Joseph Blenkinsopp , an academic theologian and Old Testament scholar , is the John A. O'Brien Professor Emeritus of Biblical Studies in the Department of Theology at the University of Notre Dame .
Fergus Nicoll is a journalist and author , currently presenting Business Matters on the BBC World Service .
Demetrios Bernardakis ( Greek : Δημήτριος Βερναρδάκης , Dimitrios Vernardakis , also transliterated Dimitrios Bernardakis , Mytilene 3 December 1833 - -25 January 1907 ) was a polymath writer and Professor of History at the National and Kapodistrian University of Athens .
Laurie N. Gottlieb , RN , PhD , is a Professor , School of Nursing , McGill University , Montreal , Canada , where she holds the Flora Madeline Shaw Chair of Nursing .
Victor Lange ( 13 July 1908 -- 29 June 1996 ) was a renowned Germanist , known primarily for his work at Princeton University .
David Cooperrider ( born July 14 , 1954 ) grew up in Oak Park Illinois , and is the Fairmount Minerals Chair and Professor of Social Entrepreneurship at the Weatherhead School of Management at Case Western Reserve University , and Faculty Director at the Center for Business as an Agent of World Benefit at Case .
Andrew McCallum is a professor and researcher in the computer science department at University of Massachusetts Amherst .
Arthur Gordon Clough ( 26 August 1934 , Salford , Lancashire -- 6 April 1996 , London ) , was an English radio presenter and journalist , primarily known for his work on BBC Radio 4 .
Eric Ober is an American broadcasting executive who served as president of CBS News from 1990 to 1996 and of Food Network from 1997 to 2000 .
Karel Jungwiert ( born 1 November 1944 ) is a Czech lawyer , and has been the Judge of the European Court of Human Rights in respect of the Czech Republic since the country 's accession to the Council of Europe in 1993 .
Reginald Gibbons ( born 1947 ) is an American poet , fiction writer , translator , literary critic , artist , and Professor of English , Classics , and Spanish and Portuguese at the Northwestern University School of Professional Studies .
James Mabbe or Mab ( 1572 - -1642 ) was an English scholar and poet , and a Fellow of Magdalen College , Oxford .
Jonathan Lear is the John U. Nef Distinguished Service Professor in the Committee on Social Thought , professor of philosophy , and Roman Family Director of the Neubauer Collegium on Culture and Society at the University of Chicago .
Joseph Henrich holds the Canada Research Chair in Culture , Cognition and Coevolution at the University of British Columbia , where he is a professor in the departments of psychology and economics .
Thomas A. DuBois is a Folklorist , scholar of Sámi culture , and a professor at the University of Wisconsin-- Madison .
Ian Bartlett is a horse racing commentator and occasionally was an analyst for the BBC .
Magdalena Środa ( née Magdalena Ciupak , b. January 7 , 1957 in Warsaw ) is a Polish philosopher , professor of ethics at the University of Warsaw , and a feminist author .
Sverre Steen ( 1 August 1898 -- 23 June 1983 ) was a Norwegian historian , a professor at the University of Oslo , and known to the public through his radio series Langsomt ble landet vårt eget .
Susan Brantly is an American scholar in Scandinavian literature and a professor at the University of Wisconsin-- Madison .
Jaegwon Kim ( born September 12 , 1934 ) is a Korean - American philosopher who is now an emeritus professor at Brown University , but who also taught at several other leading American universities .
Ingrid Eide ( born 12 July 1933 in Oslo ) is a Norwegian sociologist , United Nations official and politician for the Labour Party .
Rao S. Govindaraju is the Christopher B. and Susan S. Burke Professor of Civil Engineering at Purdue University .
Mark Doyle is a former world affairs correspondent for BBC News .
Howard M. Bahr has been a professor of Sociology at Brigham Young University ( BYU ) since 1973 and was director of field research for the Middletown IV study in 1999 .
Lin He ( born 1975 ) is an associate professor of cell and developmental biology at the University of California , Berkeley , in the Department of Molecular and Cell Biology , where she leads a lab focusing on identifying non - coding RNA which may play a role in tumorigenesis and tumor maintenance .
Frederick Michael Burdekin OBE , FREng , FRS is a British civil engineer , and emeritus professor at University of Manchester Institute of Science and Technology .
Hans M. Kristensen ( born April 7 , 1961 ) is director of the Nuclear Information Project at the Federation of American Scientists .
A former research assistant professor at the University of New Mexico in Albuquerque , Dr. Rebecca W. Keller worked in the molecular biology field .
John Pickstone ( 29 May 1944 -- 12 February 2014 ) was a British historian of science and the Wellcome Research Professor in the Centre for the History of science , Technology and Medicine , in the Faculty of Life Sciences of the University of Manchester .
Daniel Langton is Professor of the History of Jewish - Christian Relation in the department of Religions & Theology at the University of Manchester , England .
Allyne L. Merrill ( 1863 -- February 26 , 1941 ) was an American physicist who served as faculty secretary of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology ( MIT ) from 1906 to June 1934 .
Christina Jutterström ( born March 27 , 1940 ) is a Swedish journalist , former chief editor for Dagens Nyheter between 1982 and 1995 and for Expressen between 1995 and 1996 .
Jean - Dominique Merchet ( born in Besançon , 26 October 1959 ) is a French journalist working for Marianne .
Cheshire Calhoun is Professor of Philosophy at Arizona State University and research professor at the Center for the Philosophy of Freedom at the University of Arizona .
Jeff Greenberg is a social psychology professor at the University of Arizona .
Étienne Fourmont ( Chinese : 傅爾蒙 ; pinyin : Fù Ěrméng ; 23 June 1683 -- 8 December 1745 ) was a French scholar and Orientalist who served as professor of Arabic at the Collège de France and published grammars on the Arabic , Hebrew , and Chinese languages .
Richard Huxtable ( born 1974 ) is the Deputy Director and Professor in Medical Ethics and Law at the Centre for Ethics in Medicine , at the University of Bristol .
Hilary Cunningham Scharper is a novelist and associate professor of cultural anthropology at the University of Toronto .
Aseem Prakash is Professor of Political Science and the Walker Family Professor for the Arts and Sciences at University of Washington - Seattle .
Sucharit Sarkar ( born in 1983 in Calcutta ) is an assistant Professor at Princeton University .
William Andrew Irwin ( 1884 - 1967 ) was Professor of Old Testament Languages and Literature at the University of Chicago and Southern Methodist University , where his papers can be found today .
Sid Gilman is a neurologist and expert on Alzheimer 's disease at the University of Michigan .
Irwin Weil ( born 1928 ) is a Professor Emeritus in the Department of Slavic Languages and Literature at Northwestern University .
Henry Courtenay Fenn , more commonly known as H. C. Fenn , ( February 26 , 1894 -- July 1978 ) was an American sinologist and architect of Yale University 's Chinese language program .
Foster Provost is Professor of information systems and NEC Faculty Fellow at New York University 's Stern School of Business .
Carolyn Quinn ( b. 22 July 1961 ) is a British journalist best known for her work on BBC Radio 4 as a political correspondent and for presenting the Today programme and PM .
Angela Cropper ( c. 1946 -- 12 November 2012 ) of Trinidad and Tobago served as Assistant Secretary - General and Deputy Executive Director of the United Nations Environment Programme ( UNEP ) .
Annette Huber - Klawitter ( née Huber , born 23 May 1967 ) is a German mathematician at the University of Freiburg .
Joanna Aizenberg is a professor of chemistry and chemical biology at Harvard University .
Bill Damaschke is an animated film producer and former chief creative officer at DreamWorks Animation .
Jens Bangsbo is a Danish published author on physiology and sports science , and a scholar in those fields , being a professor at University of Copenhagen .
Forest Dewey Dodrill ( January 26 , 1902 -- June 28 , 1997 ) born in Webster Springs , West Virginia was a doctor at Harper University Hospital at Wayne State University in Michigan who performed the first successful open heart surgery using a mechanical pump .
Martin Sixsmith ( born 24 September 1954 ) is a British author and radio / television presenter , primarily working for the BBC .
Gabriele Oettingen is a Professor of Psychology at New York University and the University of Hamburg .
Christopher Dale Pratt ( Chinese : 白紀圖 ) , CBE , was the Chairman and Executive Director of Cathay Pacific Airways Limited and Swire Pacific Limited .
Alexander Ebner ( born 19 October 1967 ) is a German social scientist and Professor of Social Economics , esp . Economic Sociology and Political Economy at Goethe University Frankfurt .
Whitney Warren ( January 29 , 1864 -- April 23 , 1943 ) was an architect with Charles Delevan Wetmore ( 1866 - -1941 ) at Warren and Wetmore in New York City .
Vijay K. Dhir ( born 1943 ) is the former Dean of the University of California , Los Angeles ( UCLA ) Henry Samueli School of Engineering and Applied Science , holding the position from March 2003 to January 2016 .
Alan Andrew Watson , FRS , ( born 26 September 1938 in Edinburgh ) is an Emeritus Professor at the University of Leeds , UK .
Percival Everett ( born 1956 ) is an American writer and Distinguished Professor of English at the University of Southern California .
Sherry Bebitch Jeffe is a Senior Fellow at the USC Sol Price School of Public Policy at the University of Southern California .
David Cockburn ( born 12 October 1949 ) studied philosophy at St Andrews and Oxford , and has taught at Swansea , the Open University , and , until 2010 , has spent over 30 years at the University of Wales , Lampeter , where he teaches courses on the philosophy of mind , Spinoza , Wittgenstein among others .
Bonamy Dobrée ( 2 February 1891 -- 3 September 1974 ) , British academic , was Professor of English Literature at the University of Leeds from 1936 to 1955 .
Friedrich Stadler ( born July 17 , 1951 in Zeltweg , Styria ) is an Austrian historian of science and philosopher of science , and professor for history and philosophy of science at the University of Vienna .
John P. Wolfe ( born August 12 , 1970 ) is an American chemist and a professor of chemistry at the University of Michigan .
Luis Villa is an American attorney and programmer , and currently works as Senior Director of Community Engagement at the Wikimedia Foundation .
Hartmut Winkler ( born 1953 ) has been a Professor of Media Studies , Media Theory and Media Arts at the University of Paderborn in Germany since April 1999 .
Jean Martirez ( born January 19 , 1963 ) is a Filipino - American newscaster who formerly co - anchored the KTTV FOX 11 Morning News for 17 years , with Tony McEwing .
Leo Marx ( born November 15 , 1919 ) was a professor at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and an author known for his works in the field of American studies .
Friedrich Karl Max Vierhapper ( 7 March 1876 in Weidenau -- 11 July 1932 ) was an Austrian plant collector , botanist and professor of botany at the University of Vienna .
Edwin Harrison McHenry ( January 25 , 1859 - August 21 , 1931 ) was the fourth vice - president of the New York , New Haven and Hartford Railroad and first vice - president of the Consolidated Railway of Hartford , Connecticut .
Robert E. Horn ( born 1933 ) is an American political scientist who taught at Harvard , Columbia , and Sheffield ( U.K. ) universities , and has been a visiting scholar at Stanford University 's Center for the Study of Language and Information .
James R. Kincaid is an American academic , currently the Aerol Arnold Professor of English at the University of Southern California .
Ronald Inden is an American Indologist , and professor emeritus in the Departments of History and of South Asian Languages and Civilizations at the University of Chicago and is a major scholar in South Asian and post - colonial studies .
Jon McKenzie is a Professor of English at the University of Wisconsin - Madison and the Director of the University of Wisconsin - Madison 's DesignLab .
Julian Parkhill ( born 1964 ) FRS is a Head of Pathogen Genomics at the Wellcome Trust Sanger Institute in Cambridge , UK .
Agatha Sangma was born in New Delhi to P. A. Sangma , the former speaker of the Lok Sabha , and Soradini K. Sangma .
Genseric was an illegitimate son of King Godigisel ; he is assumed to have been born near Lake Balaton ( Hungary ) around 389 .
Manoj Tuli ( born 11 July 1960 ) , better known as Kumar Gaurav , is an Indian film actor and son of late actor Rajendra Kumar .
Prince Norodom Yuvaneath ( born October 17 , 1943 in Phnom Penh ) is the first son of the late king of Cambodia , Norodom Sihanouk and Princess Sisowath Pongsanmoni .
Waleran de Beaumont , 4th Earl of Warwick ( 1153 -- 12 December 1204 ) was the younger son of Roger de Beaumont , 2nd Earl of Warwick and Gundred de Warrenne , daughter of William de Warenne , 2nd Earl of Surrey and Elizabeth de Vermandois .
Paul Mendelssohn Bartholdy was the second son of the composer Felix Mendelssohn Bartholdy and Cécile Charlotte Sophie Jeanrenaud .
Sir Richard Bulstrode ( 1610 -- 3 October 1711 ) was an English author , diplomat and soldier , a son of Edward Bulstrode ( 1588 - -1659 ) .
Professor Dmytro Antonovych was the son of a Ukrainian historian Volodymyr Antonovych , the husband of Kateryna Antonovych , the father of Marko Antonovych and Mykhailo Antonovych .
Well Armed was sired by Tiznow out of the stakes - winning mare Well - Dressed , which places Seattle Slew on the top and bottom of his pedigree .
Masoud Barzani succeeded his father , the Kurdish nationalist leader Mustafa Barzani , as the leader of the KDP in 1979 .
Carl Sibbern ( 11 April 1809 -- 17 May 1880 ) was a Norwegian politician , son of Valentin Christian Wilhelm Sibbern .
Zahir Qadir is the son of Abdul Qadir a senior member of the anti - Taliban United Islamic Front ( Northern Alliance ) , and one of the first Vice Presidents of the Afghan Transitional Administration .
Thomas de Vere , 8th Earl of Oxford ( c. 1336 -- September 1371 ) was the second but first surviving son of John de Vere , 7th Earl of Oxford , and Maud de Badlesmere .
Jiiva was born as Amar to film producer R. B. Choudary and Mahjabeen on 4 January 1984 in Chennai , Tamil Nadu .
Karthik Sivakumar ( born 25 May 1977 ) , better known by his stage name Karthi , is an Indian film actor who works in the Tamil film industry .
Cthylla ( the Secret Daughter of Cthulhu ) is a fictional character in the Cthulhu Mythos of H. P. Lovecraft .
Zhao Kuo ( 趙括 ; died 260 BC ) was a general of the State of Zhao in Warring States period , son of the famous general Zhao She , during the epic Battle of Changping between the States of Zhao and Qin in ancient China .
Eve Frank or Eva Frank ( 1754 -- 1816 or 1817 ) , born in Nikopol , Ottoman Empire ( now Bulgaria ) under the name Rebecca or Rachel , was the daughter of Jacob Frank , the claimant to the position of Jewish Messiah in the 18th century , and his wife Hannah Kohen .
Jean - Jacques De Gucht is the son of Karel De Gucht , former European Commissioner for Trade Policy , Belgian Minister of Foreign Affairs and chairman of the Flemish Liberals and Democrats .
Almutawakel ( foaled in 1995 in Great Britain , died in 2007 ) was a British Thoroughbred racehorse sired by Machiavellian and the Irish stakes - winning Green Desert mare , Elfaslah .
Infanta Beatrice of Coimbra ( 1435 - -1462 ) was the 5th child of Infante Peter , Duke of Coimbra , and Isabella of Urgell .
Narayana Varman ruled Kamarupa from the Varman dynasty for the period 494 - 518 , was son of Kamrupi King Mahendra Varman and Queen Suvrata .
Bred by Tartan Farms , the muscular bay Ogygian left his mark on 1980s racing as the `` swift but star - crossed '' fastest son of Damascus .
Badshah Begum was born in 1703 as a Mughal princess and was the daughter of Mughal Emperor Farrukhsiyar and his first wife , Gauhar - un - Nissa Begum .
Kang Tongbi or Kang Tung Pih ( Chinese : 康同璧 ; pinyin : Kāng Tóngbì ; 1887 - -1969 ) was the daughter of Kang Youwei , a Chinese reformer and political figure of the late Qing dynasty and early Republican era .
Born in Wangfujing , Beijing , Yuyan was the second son of Pucheng ( 溥偁 ) and Jinggui ( 敬貴 ) , a lady of the Fuca ( 富察 ) clan .
Flirting Around was a bay horse standing 15.3½ hands high with no white markings bred in Kentucky by John W. Winnett Jr. He was sired by Round Table a three - time American Turf Champion who was named Horse of the Year in 1958 .
Cathleen Mann was born in Newcastle upon Tyne on 31 December 1896 to the Scottish portrait painter Harrington Mann , the second of his three daughters .
Jules Barthélemy - Saint - Hilaire ( 19 August 1805 -- 24 November 1895 ) was a French philosopher , journalist , statesman , and possible illegitimate son of Napoleon I of France .
Born in Halle , North Rhine - Westphalia , Monica Theodorescu is the daughter of the German , former Romanian , dressage rider George Theodorescu and the German show jumping rider Inge Theodorescu ( born as Inge Fellgiebel ) .
The sire of Dark Ronald , Bay Ronald , was a moderate handicap racehorse and a useful sire .

The Lane Cove River , a northern tributary of the Parramatta River , is a youthful tide - dominated , drowned valley estuary west of Sydney Harbour , located in Sydney , New South Wales , Australia .

The Hacking River i flows generally north north - east before reaching its mouth and emptying into Port Hacking at a line between Grays Point and Point Danger , about 4 kilometres ( 2.5 mi ) east of the suburb of Engadine , west of Yowie Bay .
Siltstone is a sedimentary rock which has a grain size in the silt range , finer than sandstone and coarser than claystones .
Philippists was the designation usually applied in the latter half of the sixteenth century to the followers of Philipp Melanchthon .
Coventry Cathedral , also known as St Michael 's Cathedral , is the seat of the Bishop of Coventry and the Diocese of Coventry , in Coventry , West Midlands , England .
Howlite was discovered near Windsor , Nova Scotia in 1868 by Henry How ( 1828 - -1879 ) , a Canadian chemist , geologist , and mineralogist .
Peano axioms or the Peano postulates , are a set of axioms for the natural numbers presented by the 19th century Italian mathematician Giuseppe Peano .
The Brücke Museum in Berlin houses the world 's largest collection of works by Die Brücke ( `` The Bridge '' ) , an early 20th - century expressionist movement .
Odenplan is a plaza located in the district Vasastaden in central Stockholm , Sweden , named after the old Norse god Odin .
Bologna Cathedral ( Italian : Cattedrale Metropolitana di San Pietro , Cattedrale di Bologna ) , dedicated to Saint Peter , is the cathedral of Bologna in Italy , and the seat and the metropolitan cathedral of the Archbishop of Bologna .
Pigeonite is named for its type locality on Lake Superior 's shores at Pigeon Point , Minnesota , United States .
Gaspeite , a very rare nickel carbonate mineral , with the formula ( Ni , Fe , Mg)CO3 , is named for the place it was first described , in the Gaspé Peninsula , Québec , Canada .
Macdonaldite was first described in 1965 and named for Gordon A. MacDonald ( 1911 - -1978 ) an American volcanologist at the University of Hawaii .
The Teylers Stichting ( English : Teylers Foundation ) is a Dutch foundation founded with the heritage of the Dutch 18th century cloth merchant and banker Pieter Teyler van der Hulst to support the people in need and encourage worship , science and art ( ter ondersteuning van behoeftigen en ter aanmoediging van godsdienst , wetenschap ) .
Sant'Andrea in Via Flaminia ( English : Saint Andrew on Via Flaminia ) is a Roman Catholic church dedicated to St Andrew the Apostle in Rome , Italy .
In mathematics , a Hadamard matrix , named after the French mathematician Jacques Hadamard , is a square matrix whose entries are either + 1 or −1 and whose rows are mutually orthogonal .
The Avogadro constant is named after the early 19th - century Italian scientist Amedeo Avogadro , who , in 1811 , first proposed that the volume of a gas ( at a given pressure and temperature ) is proportional to the number of atoms or molecules regardless of the nature of the gas .
5318 Dientzenhofer is a minor planet orbiting the Sun . It was named after Christoph Dientzenhofer ( 1655 - 1722 ) and his son Kilian Ignaz Dientzenhofer ( 1689 - 1751 ) , members of the Dientzenhofer family of architects .
The Laplace plane or Laplacian plane of a planetary satellite , named after its discoverer Pierre - Simon Laplace ( 1749 - -1827 ) , is a mean or reference plane about whose axis the instantaneous orbital plane of a satellite precesses .
In mathematics , the Noether inequality , named after Max Noether , is a property of compact minimal complex surfaces that restricts the topological type of the underlying topological 4-manifold .
Knorr - Bremse ( `` Bremse '' meaning brake ) is a manufacturer of braking systems for rail and commercial vehicles that has operated in the field for over 100 years .
The Collatz conjecture is a conjecture in mathematics named after Lothar Collatz , who first proposed it in 1937 .
ICMEC coordinates the Help Bring Them Home Campaign in 22 countries , in conjunction with International Missing Children 's Day , to spotlight the issue of child abduction around the world , and to suggest to parents some steps they can take to protect their children .
Mendeley , named after the biologist Gregor Mendel and chemist Dmitri Mendeleyev , was founded in November 2007 by three German PhD students and is based in London .
A Beatle boot is a style of boot that has been worn since the 1960s made popular by the English rock group The Beatles , for whom they were originally made .
Architype Van Doesburg is a geometric sans - serif typeface based upon a 1919 alphabet designed by Theo van Doesburg , a cofounder of the De Stijl art movement .
The park was opened in 1865 and originally named the `` Nieuwe Park '' , but later renamed to `` Vondelpark '' , after the 17th - century playwright and poet Joost van den Vondel .
Sankey diagrams are named after Irish Captain Matthew Henry Phineas Riall Sankey , who used this type of diagram in 1898 in a classic figure ( see panel on right ) showing the energy efficiency of a steam engine .
In abstract algebra and analysis , the Archimedean property , named after the ancient Greek mathematician Archimedes of Syracuse , is a property held by some algebraic structures , such as ordered or normed groups , and fields .
Ulexite was named for the German chemist Georg Ludwig Ulex ( 1811 - -1883 ) who first discovered it .
The European Academy of Sciences established the Blaise Pascal Medal in 2003 to recognise an outstanding and demonstrated personal contribution to science and technology and the promotion of excellence in research and education .
Haitz 's law is named after Roland Haitz ( 1935 - 2015 ) , a scientist at Agilent Technologies among others .
Lacanianism is the study of , and development of , the ideas and theories of the dissident French psychoanalyst Jacques Lacan .
Shigellosis , also known as bacillary dysentery or Marlow syndrome , in its most severe manifestation , is a foodborne illness caused by infection by bacteria of the genus Shigella .
The Turing machine was invented in 1936 by Alan Turing , who called it an a - machine ( automatic machine ) .
The name Plan 9 from Bell Labs is a reference to the Ed Wood 1959 cult science fiction Z - movie Plan 9 from Outer Space .
The Philips Sport Vereniging ( Dutch pronunciation : ( ˈfilɪps ˌspɔrt fəˌreːnəɣɪŋ ) , English : Philips Sports Union ) , abbreviated as PSV and internationally known as PSV Eindhoven ( ˌpeːjɛsˈfeː ˈɛi̯ntˌɦoːvə(n ) ) is a sports club from Eindhoven , Netherlands .

Knight Without Armour ( styled as Knight Without Armor in some releases ) is a 1937 British historical drama film made by London Films and distributed by United Artists .
The Sky Walker seems to be a man walking in the air over Chicago , pushing a barrel - sized object .
Brewster McCloud is a 1970 movie , directed by Robert Altman , about a young recluse ( Bud Cort , as the title character ) who lives in a fallout shelter of the Houston Astrodome , where he is building a pair of wings so he can fly .
What a Hero ! is a 1992 Hong Kong action comedy film directed by Benny Chan and starring Andy Lau and Maggie Cheung .
After a decade of emigration , Zimbabweans now refer to London as Harare North .
Satellite City was a Welsh sitcom which started out originally as a radio show on BBC Radio Wales in 1994 and then evolved into a TV version made by BBC Wales and was first broadcast in 1996 .
The drama was centred on the fictional comprehensive school of Grange Hill in the ( equally fictitious ) borough of North London called `` Northam '' ( although when filming moved to Liverpool in 2003 , it ceased to have any specific location ) , and follows the lives of the students as they progress through school .
Remember the End is the second novel by the American writer Agnes Sligh Turnbull ( 1888 - -1982 ) and it is set in Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania from the 1890s to World War I. The protagonist Alex MacTay is a Scotsman who is called to be a poet , but instead emigrates to America .
Aimée & Jaguar is a 1999 German drama film set in Berlin during World War II . It was written and directed by Max Färberböck , based upon Erica Fischer 's book , chronicling the actual lives of Lilly Wust and Felice Schragenheim during that time .
The Mackinnons was a BBC Scotland drama series , which started in 1977 .

The tribe Dalbergieae is an early - branching monophyletic clade of the flowering plant subfamily Faboideae or Papilionaceae .
Chayote ( Sechium edule ) is an edible plant belonging to the gourd family Cucurbitaceae , along with melons , cucumbers and squash .

The Antiguan racer ( Alsophis antiguae ) is a harmless rear - fanged ( opisthoglyphous ) grey - brown snake that was until recently found only on Great Bird Island off the coast of Antigua , in the Eastern Caribbean .

Philinoidea is a taxonomic superfamily of sea slugs , specifically headshield slugs , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Cephalaspidea .
Laverania is a subgenus of the Plasmodium genus of parasitic protozoa .
The Fueguian sprat or Falkland sprat , Sprattus fuegensis , is a herring - like , marine fish in the family Clupeidae found in the subtropical southwest Atlantic Ocean from 40 ° S to Tierra del Fuego and the Falkland Islands .
Paronychomys is an extinct genus of Cricetidae that existed in Arizona during the Hemphillian period .

Cyclocheilichthys is a genus of ray - finned fish in the family Cyprinidae containing approximately eight valid species .

Palparidiini is an antlion tribe in the subfamily Palparinae .
The Germain 's swiftlet ( Aerodramus germani ) is a species of swift .

Meligramma is a genus of hoverflies in the subfamily Syrphinae .
The Algerian three - toed skink or seps tridactyle de l'Algerie ( Chalcides mertensi ) is a species of skink .
Protoclaviger is an extinct Early Eocene transitional fossil myrmecophile of the rove beetle subfamily Pselaphinae , and a stem group of the modern supertribe Clavigeritae , of which Claviger is a representative .
Sterculioideae is a subfamily of the Malvaceae family containing evergreen and deciduous trees and shrubs .
Trimerocephalus is a genus of eyeless trilobites from the order Phacopida , family Phacopidae .
Selenipedium is a genus of the Orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) ( Subfamily Cypripedioideae ) .
Solenaspis is a monotypic genus of hoverfly from the family Syrphidae , in the order Diptera .
Elaphoglossoideae is a subfamily of the Dryopteridaceae family of ferns , based on the previously published family Elaphoglossaceae Pic . Serm .
Calliostomatinae is a subfamily of gastropods , belonging to the family Calliostomatidae .
Copelatinae is a subfamily of diving beetles , in the Dytiscidae family .
The Koepcke 's hermit , ermite de Koepcke , or ermitaño de Koepcke ( Phaethornis koepckeae ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Conasprelloides is a subgenus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Rhopalosilpha wasmanni is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Rhopalosilpha .
Swainson 's flycatcher ( Myiarchus swainsoni ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Catantostomatidae is an extinct family of marine gastropods included in the Vetigastropoda and placed in the superfamily Pleurotomarioidea
Atractus is a genus of colubrid ground snakes in the Dipsadinae subfamily .
Gasteria armstrongii ( Gasteria nitida var . armstrongii ) is a dwarf succulent plant native to South Africa , in the genus Gasteria .
The Diplodactylidae are a family in the suborder Gekkota ( geckos ) , with about 137 species in 25 genera .
Damasonium is a genus of six species of flowering plants in the family Alismataceae , commonly known as starfruit and by the older name thrumwort .
Priacanthus is a genus of marine fishes belonging to the family Priacanthidae , the bigeyes .
The Maui Nui finch ( Telespiza ypsilon ) is an extinct member of the genus Telespiza in the family Fringillidae .
Gracilechinus is a genus of sea urchins in the family Echinidae .
Holcocera is a gelechoid moth genus of the Blastobasidae family .
Paraxanthias is a genus of crabs in the family Xanthidae , containing one exclusively fossil species and the following extant species :
Drastea is a monotypic genus of moth in the Acrolophidae family .
The Zapata wren ( Ferminia cerverai ) is a medium sized grayish - brown bird that lives in dense shrubs of the Zapata Swamp , Cuba .
Niemeyera is a genus of plants in the Sapotaceae family described as a genus in 1870 .
Archidela is a genus of beetles in the family Carabidae that was formed from the breakup of Cicindela .
Alloherpesviridae is a family of viruses within the order Herpesvirales .
Zarigani ( Cambaroides japonicus ) is a species of crayfish endemic to Japan .
Thaumatomyrmex is a Neotropical genus of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae , found from Mexico to Brazil .
Stachytarpheta is a plant genus in the verbena family ( Verbenaceae ) .
The Alta Floresta antpitta ( Hylopezus whittakeri ) is a species of antpitta of the Grallariidae family discovered in 2012 .
Like other members of the family Alvarezsauridae , the forelimbs of Parvicursor were short and stubby , with hands all but completely reduced to a single large claw , possibly useful for opening tough termite mounds or other types of digging .
Haggard 's leaf - eared mouse ( Phyllotis haggardi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Kashmir cave bat ( Myotis longipes ) is a species of vesper bat .
Acroloxidae , commonly known as river limpets , are a taxonomic family of very small , freshwater snails , aquatic pulmonate gastropod limpet - like mollusks with a simple flattened conical shell in the clade Hygrophila .
The Long - headed hill rat ( Bunomys prolatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Rubovietnamia is a genus of plants in the Rubiaceae , native to Vietnam and southern China .
The Atlantic petrel ( Pterodroma incerta ) is a gadfly petrel endemic to the South Atlantic Ocean .
Cutleriales is an order in the brown algae ( class Phaeophyceae ) .
Tudorella is a genus of land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiidae .
Miliolacea is one of five superfamilies belonging to the Miliolida , ( suborder Miliolina in Loeblich & Tappan 1988 ) .
Roth 's tree frog or the northern laughing tree frog ( Litoria rothii ) is a tree frog native to northern Australia and southern Papua New Guinea .
Oreolais is an alternatively named genus for 2 species of bird in the Cisticolidae family most often placed in the genus Apalis .
The Canterbury mudfish , Neochanna burrowsius , also known as the kowaro , is found only on the Canterbury Plains in New Zealand .
Wilkiea is a genus of dioecious trees and shrubs of the family Monimiaceae .
The Serpent Island gecko ( Nactus serpensinsula ) is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
Xiurenbagrus is a genus of torrent catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Amblycipitidae .
Heterixalus ( commonly known as the Madagascan reed frog ) is a genus of frogs in the Hyperoliidae family .
Silphedolestids are no longer recognized as a valid grouping , and Silphictidoides is now considered a basal member of the clade Baurioidea .
The Morongo desert snail ( Eremarionta morongoana ) is a species of land snail in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
The Lulu 's tody - flycatcher or Johnson 's tody - flycatcher ( Poecilotriccus luluae ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Agelaius is a genus of blackbirds in the New World family Icteridae .
Chondrostoma ( from the Ancient Greek roots χόνδρος ( khondros , `` lump '' ) + στόμα ( stoma , `` mouth '' ) = `` lump - mouth '' ) is a genus of ray - finned fish in the family Cyprinidae .
The Oxyporinae are a subfamily of the Staphylinidae discovered in 1839 by Erichson .
It is the only species in the genus Santanachelys , which itself is a member of the extinct family Protostegidae .
Apis cerana , or the Asiatic honey bee ( or the eastern honey bee ) , is a species of honey bee found in southern and southeastern Asia , including China , Pakistan , India , Korea , Japan , Malaysia , Nepal , Bangladesh , Papua New Guinea and Solomon Islands .
Parietobalaena is an extinct genus of baleen whale , belonging to the family Pelocetidae .
The Chilean flicker ( Colaptes pitius ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
The Peruvian sheartail ( Thaumastura cora ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Evalina is a small genus of sea snails , pyramidellid gastropod mollusks in the tribe Chrysallidini within the family Pyramidellidae .
Salticus is a spider genus of the Salticidae family ( jumping spiders ) .
Ablerus is a genus of chalcid wasps belonging to the family Aphelinidae .
The Brazilian heart - tongued frog , Phyllodytes kautskyi , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Brazil .
Compared to Osteolaemus , which has a small body and blunt snout , Brochuchus has a more generalized crocodylid anatomy .
Leucettida is an order in the subclass of Calcinea .
Tropaeolum peregrinum , the canary - creeper , canarybird flower , canarybird vine , or canary nasturtium , is a species of Tropaeolum native to western South America in Peru and possibly also Ecuador .
The Navassa Island iguana ( Cyclura cornuta onchiopsis ) was a subspecies of rhinoceros iguana that was found on the Caribbean island of Navassa .
Argonauta argo , also known as the greater argonaut , is a species of pelagic octopus belonging to the genus Argonauta .
Peltophryne is a genus of true toads , family Bufonidae , from the Greater Antilles ( Cuba , Isla de Juventud , Hispaniola , Puerto Rico ) .
Doleserpeton is an extinct , monospecific genus of dissorophoidean temnospondyl within the family Amphibamidae that lived during the Upper Permian , 285 million years ago .
The Oecophorinae are the nominate subfamily of moths in the concealer moth family ( Oecophoridae ) .
Senegalia modesta ( commonly called Phulai in Pakistan , Phalāhī ਫਲਾਹੀ پھلاہی ( Punjabi ) in India ) is a species of Acacia commonly found in Pakistan , India and Afghanistan .
Maizaniidae is a family of minute land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Cyclophoroidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Sitka deer or Sitka black - tailed deer ( Odocoileus hemionus sitkensis ) , is a subspecies of mule deer ( Odocoileus hemionus ) , similar to the Columbian black - tailed subspecies ( O. h. colombianus ) .
The European nightcrawler , Eisenia hortensis or Dendrobaena veneta , is a medium - small earthworm averaging about 1.5 grams each when fully grown .
The California butterfly ray ( Gymnura marmorata ) is a species of ray in the family Gymnuridae .
Sturanyella is a genus of land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Helicinidae , the helicinids .
The Hawaiʻi ʻakepa ( Loxops coccineus ) is an endangered ʻakepa native to Hawaiʻi in the Hawaiian Islands .
Phayre 's leaf monkey ( Trachypithecus phayrei ) , also known as Phayre 's langur , is a species of lutung found in Southeast Asia .
The Yap monarch ( Monarcha godeffroyi ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Selenidera is a bird genus containing six species of dichromatic toucanets in the toucan family Ramphastidae .
The Symmocinae are a subfamily of moths in the superfamily Gelechioidea .
Bovine immunodeficiency virus ( BIV ) is a retrovirus belonging to the Lentivirus genus .
Sabuloglossum is a fungal genus in the earth tongue family Geoglossaceae .
Werner 's toad ( Rhaebo nasicus , formerly Bufo nasicus ; in Spanish sapo narigudo ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
The Antillean mango ( Anthracothorax dominicus ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .

The taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 categorizes Tropidodiscidae in the superfamilia Bellerophontoidea within the Paleozoic molluscs of uncertain systematic position with isostrophically coiled shells ( Gastropoda or Monoplacophora ) .
Phanoxyla is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , Phanoxyla hystrix , which is known from northern South America , including Brazil and Ecuador .
Rutelinae is a subfamily of the scarab beetles ( family Scarabaeidae ) .
The Jerusalem artichoke ( Helianthus tuberosus ) , also called sunroot , sunchoke , earth apple or topinambour , is a species of sunflower native to eastern North America , and found from eastern Canada and Maine west to North Dakota , and south to northern Florida and Texas .
The Porto Alegre golden - eyed tree frog , Trachycephalus mesophaeus , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Brazil .
Bolson pupfish ( Cyprinodon atrorus ) is a species of fish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
Dissiliaria is a genus of plants under the family Picrodendraceae described as a genus in 1867 .
Staphida is an alternatively named genus of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
The Luzon Cordillera forest mouse ( Apomys abrae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found only in the Philippines .
Dilsea is a red algae genus in the Dumontiaceae family .
The New Zealand ruffe , Schedophilus huttoni , is a medusafish of the family Centrolophidae found in all southern oceans south of latitude 18 ° S , at depths of up to 1,000 m. Its length is up to 90 cm .
Acartophthalmus is a genus of flies , one of only genera in the family Acartophthalmidae .
Airbreathing catfishes are fishes comprising the family Clariidae of order Siluriformes .
The African pompano ( Alectis ciliaris ) ( also known as the pennant - fish and threadfin trevally ) is a widely distributed species of tropical marine fish in the jack family , Carangidae .
The Ruwenzori turaco ( Ruwenzorornis johnstoni ) is a species of bird in the Musophagidae family .
Platycrossos is a genus of Protocoleopteran beetle in the family Permosynidae .
Thymelicus is a Palearctic genus in the skipper butterfly family , Hesperiidae .
Crithagra is a genus of small passerine birds in the finch family ( Fringillidae ) .
Daphoenictis is an extinct cat - like genus of the family Amphicyonidae ( bear - dogs ) , subfamily Daphoeninae , endemic to North America during the Late Eocene - Oligocene epochs ( 36 - 26 million years ago ) , existing for approximately 10.2 million years .
Betula humilis is a species of birch that can be found in Europe and Asia .
The Lake Tebera rainbowfish ( Melanotaenia herbertaxelrodi ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family endemic to Papua New Guinea .
Thoracopteridae is an extinct family of prehistoric bony fish ; classified with the order Peltopleuriformes .
Callionymus moretonensis , the Queensland stinkfish , is a species of dragonet native to the western Pacific Ocean where it can be found in the waters off of northwestern Australia , Papua New Guinea and Melanesia .
The Cascade torrent salamander ( Rhyacotriton cascadae ) is a species of salamander in the Rhyacotritonidae family .
Micronomus is a subgenus of the Mormopterus genus of bats .
Ratardinae is a small subfamily of moths formerly placed in its own family Ratardidae and related to ( and often included within ) the Cossidae .
Phthinosuchia was named by American paleontologist Everett C. Olson in 1961 , who considered it the most primitive infraorder within Therapsida .
Alamosaurus was in any case an advanced , or derived , member of the group Titanosauria , but its relationships within that group are far from certain .
Umiaites is a Late Jurassic ( Tithonian stage ) ammonitid included in the Olcostephanidae which is part of the Perisphinctaceae .
Flavivirus is a genus of viruses in the family Flaviviridae .
The Coraya wren ( Pheugopedius coraya ) is a species of bird in the Troglodytidae family , the wrens .
Mimocrypta is a genus of moths in the Sesiidae family containing only one species , Mimocrypta hampsoni , which is known from Uganda .
Nudipleura are a clade of sea snails and sea slugs , marine gastropod mollusks within the large clade Heterobranchia .
The Cambodian logsucker ( Garra cambodgiensis ) , also known as stonelapping minnow or false Siamese algae eater , is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Garra .
Polymita , is a genus of large , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
Candaharia is a genus of air - breathing land slugs , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Parmacellidae .
Metaplastes is a genus of katydids crickets in family Tettigoniidae subfamily Phaneropterinae .
The Kei myotis ( Myotis stalkeri ) is a species of vesper bat .
The Idaho pocket gopher ( Thomomys idahoensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Geomyidae .
Acanthastrea is a genus of large polyp stony corals in the family Lobophylliidae .
Hygromiinae ( Tryon , 1866 ) is a taxonomic subfamily of land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
The Rio de Janeiro antwren ( Myrmotherula fluminensis ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Isoperlinae is a subfamily in the family Perlodidae , also known as the perlodid stoneflies , stripetails or springflies .
The Western Saharan spiny mouse ( Acomys airensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found in Mali , Mauritania , Niger , and possibly in Western Sahara , western Chad , and southern Algeria .
Lachnocnema , commonly called woolly legs , is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae found mainly in subsaharan Africa .
Pygicera scripta is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Pygicera .
The Sulawesi nightjar ( Caprimulgus celebensis ) is a species of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
Anginon is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with 12 species .
Pseudemodesa plenicornis is a moth in the Drepanidae family and only species in the Pseudemodesa genus .
Charopidae is a taxonomic family of small air - breathing land snails ( and semi - slugs such as Otoconcha dimidiata ) , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Punctoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Alepidea is a genus of about twenty species in the botanical family Apiaceae , all of which are endemic to Africa .
The Northern yellow - black triplefin ( Enneapterygius gracilis ) , also known as the Northern Australian yellow - black triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Gulls , often referred to as seagulls , are seabirds of the family Laridae in the suborder Lari .
Gastrotheca is a genus of frogs ( family Hemiphractidae ) found in Central and South America .
The Australian raven is distinguished from the Australian crow species by its throat hackles , which are prominent in adult birds .
Paractenodes rudis is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Paractenodes .
Paramartinsia quadrimaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Paramartinsia .
The Mission golden - eyed tree frog or Amazon milk frog ( Trachycephalus resinifictrix ) is a large species of arboreal frog native to the Amazon Rainforest in South America .
Platycerium is a genus of about 18 fern species in the polypod family , Polypodiaceae .
The Surat serotine ( Eptesicus dimissus ) is a species of vesper bat .
The Victorin 's warbler ( Cryptillas victorini ) , or Victorin 's scrub warbler is a species of African warbler , formerly placed in the Sylviidae family .
The Stibadocerinae are a subfamily from the Long - bodied Craneflies family Cylindrotomidae .
The Andean mountain cat ( Leopardus jacobita ) is a small wild cat native to the high Andes that has been classified as Endangered by IUCN because fewer than 2500 individuals are thought to exist in the wild .

The Big - scale pomfret , Taractichthys longipinnis , is a species of pomfret found in the Atlantic ocean , at depths down to 500 metres ( 1,600 ft ) .
Hodgson 's bat ( Myotis formosus ) , also called the copper - winged bat , is a species of vesper bat in the genus Myotis , the mouse - eared bats .
The Suweon tree frog , also spelled Suwon treefrog , Hyla suweonensis , is a species of tree frog found in western South Korea , probably from the Imjin River to the Bay of Asan .
The Dominican green - and - yellow macaw or Atwood 's macaw ( Ara atwoodi ) , also called the Dominican macaw , is an extinct macaw that may have lived on the island of Dominica .
The Siberian chipmunk or common chipmunk ( Eutamias sibiricus ) appears across northern Asia from central Russia to China , Korea , and Hokkaidō in northern Japan .
The Santander dwarf squirrel Microsciurus santanderensis is a small tree squirrel endemic to Colombia .

Hayekina dispar is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Hayekina .
Cadlina is a genus of sea slugs , dorid nudibranchs , shell - less marine gastropod mollusks historically classified in the family Chromodorididae .
Punctelia is a genus of lichens belonging to the Parmeliaceae family .
Charpentieria is a genus of small , very elongate , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Clausiliidae , the door snails , all of which have a clausilium .
Brancoceras is representative of the subfamily Branoceratinae , which makes up part of the acanthoceratacean family Brancoceratidae .
Microschemobrycon is a genus of characins , in the family Characidae , from South America , with seven currently described species .
Sibynophis is a genus of colubrid snakes , commonly called many - toothed snakes , which together with Scaphiodontophis make up the subfamily Sibynophiinae .
Vadonia unipunctata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Vadonia .
Thylodrias is a monotypic genus of beetles in the family Dermestidae containing the single species Thylodrias contractus , known commonly as the odd beetle and tissue paper beetle .

Tylonautilus is a member of the Tainoceratidae which , with other related families , forms the nautiloid superfamily Tainocerataceae .

The Aurelio 's rock lizard ( Iberolacerta aurelioi ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .

Hesperodiaptomus is a genus of copepods in the family Diaptomidae , containing 18 species .

The Chirinda apalis ( Apalis chirindensis ) is a species of bird in the Cisticolidae family .

Sphaerocarpos is one of two genera in the Sphaerocarpaceae .
The Cooper Creek catfish , Neosiluroides cooperensis , is a species of catfish ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Plotosidae , and is the only species of the genus Neosiluroides .
The Florida banded water snake ( Nerodia fasciata pictiventris ) , a subspecies of the banded water snake ( southern water snake - Nerodia fasciata ) , is a nonvenomous natricine colubrid native to the southeastern United States .

The Gila springsnail , scientific name Pyrgulopsis gilae , is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
The Biatorellaceae are a family of lichenized fungi in the order Lecanorales .
The Tasmanian froglet , ( Crinia tasmaniensis ) is a species of ground - dwelling frog that occurs only in Tasmania , Australia .
Siebold 's water snake ( Enhydris sieboldii ) is a species of mildly venomous , rear - fanged , colubrid snake , endemic to Asia .
Blanford 's rosefinch was formerly placed in the genus Carpodacus with the other rosefinches .
The Santa Marta blossomcrown ( Anthocephala floriceps ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
The Opata sucker , or matalote Opata ( Catostomus wigginsi ) , is a species of ray - finned fish in the Catostomidae family .
' Brachyistius frenatus , the Kelp perch , is a species of surfperch native to the eastern Pacific Ocean from British Columbia , Canada to Baja California , Mexico where it is found in kelp forests down to a depth of about 30 metres ( 98 ft ) .
Sulzbacheromyces is a monospecific genus in the family Lepidostromataceae ( the only family ) within the fungal order Lepidostromatales ) .
Cardioceratidae is an extinct ammonite family belonging to the superfamily Stephanocerataceae .
Bannerman 's turaco ( Tauraco bannermani ) is a species of bird in the Musophagidae family .
Vertiginidae , common name the whorl snails , is a family of minute , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs or micromollusks in the superfamily Pupilloidea .
Cibolites is a genus of ammonoid in the family Paraceltitidae of the cephalopod order Ceratitida which lived during the Late Permian .
Opistognathidae , the jawfishes , are a family of fishes classified within the order Perciformes , suborder Percoidei .
The Toba betta ( Betta rubra ) is a species of gourami endemic to Indonesia where it is an inhabitant of peat swamps .
The Ctenostomata are an order of bryozoans in the class Gymnolaemata .
The European bee - eater ( Merops apiaster ) is a near passerine bird in the bee - eater family Meropidae .
The Tristram 's storm petrel ( Oceanodroma tristrami ) is a species of seabird in the storm petrel family Hydrobatidae .
Acrisione is a genus of the tribe Senecioneae and the family Asteraceae and a native of Chile , described as a genus in 1985 .
Propanoplosaurus was by the describers assigned to the Nodosauridae .
Cubeb ( Piper cubeba ) , or tailed pepper is a plant in genus Piper , cultivated for its fruit and essential oil .
Hymenomycetes was the largest class of fungi within the phylum Basidiomycota , but the term is no longer taxonomically relevant .
The Wyanad day gecko ( Cnemaspis wynadensis ) is a species of geckos found in Wayanad , India .
Milne - Edwards ' sportive lemur ( Lepilemur edwardsi ) , or Milne - Edwards ' weasel lemur , is a species of lemur in the family Lepilemuridae .
Paphia is a genus of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Veneridae , the Venus clams .
Father Schoenig 's chocolate ( Parantica schoenigi ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly , endemic to the Philippines .
Panga is the common South African name for Pterogymnus laniarius , a small , ocean - dwelling fish , native to the southeast Atlantic Ocean and southwest Indian Ocean .
Melampyrum is a genus of about 20 species of herbaceous flowering plants in the family Orobanchaceae known commonly as cow wheat .
Pseudochironomus is a genus of European and North American non - biting midges in the subfamily Chironominae of the bloodworm family Chironomidae .
Prestosuchus is an extinct genus of pseudosuchian in the family Prestosuchidae .
Phasianella , common name the pheasant shells , is a genus of small sea snails with a calcareous operculum and a colorfully patterned shell , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Phasianellidae .
Danaoceras is a nautiloid cephalopod from the middle Silurian of central Europe included in the oncoceroid family Polyelasmoceratidae .
The Madagascar sucker - footed bat , Old World sucker - footed bat , or simply sucker - footed bat ( Myzopoda aurita ) is a species of bat in the family Myzopodidae endemic to Madagascar , especially in the eastern part of the forests .
Western chat - tanager , Calyptophilus tertius Eastern chat - tanager , Calyptophilus frugivorus The name Calyptophilus comes from the Greek words kaluptēs , meaning `` hider '' ( derived from kaluptō , meaning `` to cover '' ) and philos , meaning `` loving '' ( derived from phileō , meaning `` to love '' ) .
Querandiornis romani was a species of bird from the clade Tinamidae that lived in the Pleistocene epoch , about 6 million years ago .
Pterogobius is a genus of fish in the goby family , Gobiidae , native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
The Bahamian hutia or Ingraham 's hutia ( Geocapromys ingrahami ) is a species of rodent in the family Capromyidae .
The genus Oligoneuron is considered phylogenetically a basal or near - basal member of the subtribe Astereae .
According to a cladistic analysis performed by the describers , Nanyangosaurus was a basal member of the Hadrosauroidea , more derived than Probactrosaurus and closely related to the Hadrosauridae .
Gerontia pantherina is a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
Unidentiidae is a taxonomic family of sea slugs , specifically aeolid nudibranchs , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Aeolidioidea .
Morphaneflus prolixus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Morphaneflus .
The Mahanadi razorbelly minnow ( Salmophasia untrahi ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Salmophasia .
The Moeopsyllini form a flea tribe in the family Pulicidae .
The Makira starling ( Aplonis dichroa ) , also known as the San Cristobal starling , is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae .
Trachylinae ( also Trachylina , Trachylinida , etc . ) are a cnidarian subclass of the Hydrozoa .
Cenoceras is an extinct genus within the cephalopod mollusk family Nautilidae , which in turn makes up part of the superfamily Nautilaceae .
Sphingulus is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , Sphingulus mus , which is found from the south - eastern part of the Russian Far East and the Korean Peninsula south into eastern China .
The Polykrikaceae ( also known as Polykrikidae ) are a family of athecate dinoflagellates of the order Gymnodiniales .
Xanthocanace is a genus of beach flies in the family Canacidae .
Festuca ( fescue ) is a genus of flowering plants belonging to the grass family , Poaceae ( subfamily Pooideae ) .
Valloniidae is a taxonomic family of small and minute , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Pupilloidea .
Decapterus is a genus of marine fishes in the family in the jack family , Carangidae , commonly known as mackerel scads , round scads , or horse mackerel .
The Bates 's weaver ( Ploceus batesi ) is a species of bird in the Ploceidae family .
Callicarpa ( beautyberry ) is a genus of shrubs and small trees in the family Lamiaceae .
The Cladobranchia are a taxonomic clade of nudibranchs , sea slugs , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Dexiarchia .
The Indian bush lark , Indian bushlark or red - winged bushlark ( Mirafra erythroptera ) is a species of bushlark found in South Asia mainly in India .
Today Valdosaurus is generally considered a member of the Dryosauridae .
Agriopoma is a genus of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the family Veneridae , the venus clams .
The Cubera snapper , Lutjanus cyanopterus , is a species of snapper native to the western Atlantic Ocean from Nova Scotia to the Amazon River in Brazil , though it is rare north of Florida .
Mirror turtle ants ( Cephalotes specularis ) are a species of ant that mimic other , unrelated ants ( Crematogaster ampla ) in order to steal their food .
Bolma is a genus of medium to large sea snails with a calcareous operculum , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .
Acanthina , common name the unicorn snails , is a genus of small predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Peristichia is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Oxymycterus hucucha , also known as the Quechuan Hocicudo , is a species of rodent in the genus Oxymycterus of family Cricetidae from South America .
Gryllus is a genus of field cricket ( Orthoptera , Gryllidae , Gryllinae ) .
Influenza A virus subtype H6N1 , also known as H6N1 , is a subtype of the influenza A virus .
The Southern alligator lizard ( Elgaria multicarinata ) is a common species of lizard native to the Pacific coast of North America .
The Ruwenzori duiker or Ruwenzori red duiker ( Cephalophus rubidus ) is a stocky but small antelope found only in the Ruwenzori Mountains between Uganda and , probably , the Democratic Republic of Congo .
The family Pliopithecidae is an extinct family of fossil catarrhines and members of the Pliopithecoidea superfamily .
The Tumbes sparrow ( Rhynchospiza stolzmanni ) is a species of bird in the family Emberizidae found in Ecuador and Peru .
Like other members of the subfamily Hypoptopomatinae , Pseudotocinclus is primarily herbivorous and is more commonly found at or near the upper portion of the water column .
Some members are listed as threatened or endangered and have been the focus of disputes over development plans ( e.g. Limnanthes floccosa subsp . californica , Limnanthes vinculans ) The Limnanthaceae are members of a recently identified clade ( Brassicales ) of mustard oil producing plants .
Parantica , commonly called Tigers , is an Old World genus of butterflies in subfamily Danainae of family Nymphalidae .
Curveulima is a major genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Eulimidae .
The genus Begomovirus is a genus of viruses , in the family Geminiviridae .
The Iquitos gnatcatcher ( Polioptila clementsi ) is a gnatcatcher ( Polioptilidae ) described as new to science in 2005 .
Augustasaurus is a genus of aquatic sauropterygian reptile belonging to the Pistosauria , a clade containing plesiosaurs and their close relatives .
The Ringneck blenny ( Parablennius pilicornis ) is a species of combtooth blenny widespread in coastal waters of Eastern Atlantic from Spain and Portugal to Möwe Bay , Namibia , in the Mediterranean Sea from Morocco , Algeria , Spain .
× Heucherella is an evergreen perennial flowering plant in the family Saxifragaceae .
Californites is a genus of the Upper Triassic clydonicacean family Clionitidae with a discoidal , evolute shell and radial tuberculate ribs that end in strong ventrolateral spines .
Cyprinion semiplotum , the Assamese kingfish , is a species of cyprinid fish native to southern Asia where it occurs in fresh waters of India , Nepal , Bhutan and Myanmar .
Proteoideae is one of five subfamilies of the flowering plant family Proteaceae .
Lampsilis higginsii is a rare species of freshwater mussel known by the common name Higgins ' eye pearly mussel .
According to phylogenies based on morphological characteristics , Scincogekkonomorpha is the sister taxon of Iguania and together they make up crown group Squamata , the smallest clade including all living snakes and lizards .
Thermothrix is a genus of Gram - negative , nonspore - forming , thermophilic , motile bacteria with a single polar flagellum of the family Burkholderiaceae and class Betaproteobacteria .
The family Montiaceae was newly adopted in the APG III system and includes members of the Caryophyllales formerly listed in Portulacaceae .
The Anthophorini are a large tribe in the subfamily Apinae of the family Apidae .
The Guianan spear - nosed bat ( Phyllostomus latifolius ) is a bat species from South America .
Parabaryssinus lineaticollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Parabaryssinus .
Debaryomyces is a genus of yeasts in the family Saccharomycetaceae .
Barathrites is a genus of cusk - eels found in deep waters of the northwest Atlantic Ocean .
Anapliomera is a genus of trilobite in the order Phacopida , which existed in what is now Illinois , U.S.A. It was described by Demott in 1987 , and the type species is Anapliomera shirlandensis .
Prosantorhinus is an extinct genus of rhinoceros from the lower and middle Miocene .
The Ocellated sand - eel ( Lamnostoma polyophthalma ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
The Amazonian antshrike ( Thamnophilus amazonicus ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae , the antbirds .
The Natal free - tailed bat ( Mormopterus acetabulosus ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae , the free - tailed bats .
According to Teichert , 1964 , Megadisocosorus is a member of one of the two branches of the Armenoceratidae that also includes Nybyoceras and Selkirkoceras .
Cardiapoda is a genus of very small floating sea snails or heteropods , pelagic gastropod molluscs or micromolluscs in the family Carinariidae .
Verreaux 's mouse or Verreaux 's white - footed rat ( Myomyscus verreauxii ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Cimolomyidae is a family of fossil mammal within the extinct order Multituberculata .
Toxophacops is a genus of trilobites from the order Phacopida , family Phacopidae .
The Pacific ladyfish , also known as the Pacific tenpounder and Machete ( Elops affinis ) is a species of fish in the genus Elops , the only genus in the monotypic family Elopidae .
Alpinia is a genus of flowering plants in the ginger family , Zingiberaceae .
Most authors place the genus in the family Lecythidaceae , the sole genus in the subfamily Foetidioideae , but some prefer to treat it as a distinct family , the Foetidiaceae .
Henna ( Lawsonia inermis , also known as hina , the henna tree , the mignonette tree , and the Egyptian privet ) is a flowering plant and the sole species of the Lawsonia genus .
The Kungwe apalis ( Apalis argentea ) is a species in the Cisticolidae family .
In taxonomy , the Archaeoglobales ( Greek / Latin mix for `` old balloon '' ) are an order of the Archaeoglobi .
The Big Bend gambusia ( Gambusia gaigei ) is a rare species of fish in the Poeciliidae family .

Puertasaurus belonged to the clade Titanosauria .
The Baja California killifish ( Fundulus lima ) is a killifish in the Fundulidae family .
Previously included either in the elm family ( Ulmaceae ) or a separate family , Celtidaceae , the APG III system places Celtis in an expanded hemp family ( Cannabaceae ) .
The New Guinea free - tailed bat ( Tadarida kuboriensis ) , sometimes designated the New Guinea mastiff bat , is an extant species of free - tailed bat that inhabits the Chimbu highlands of Papua New Guinea .
The Sumatran crow ( Euploea martinii ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
The Nilgiri flycatcher ( Eumyias albicaudatus ) is an Old World flycatcher with a very restricted range in the hills of southern India .
Selliera is a genus of herbs in the family Goodeniaceae .
Urocissa is a genus of birds in the family Corvidae , a family which contains the crows , jays and magpies .
Azorella is a genus of about 70 species of flowering plants in the family Apiaceae , native to South America , New Zealand and the islands of the Southern Ocean .
Lobolytocerasa Lytoceratid genus included in the Alocolytoceratinae in which only the inner whorls have large swollen ribs , later whorls have wrinkled growth lines which coarsen somewhat , near the aperture .
Piptoporus is a genus of bracket fungi in the Fomitopsidaceae family .
Mullus is a subtropical marine genus of perciform fish of the family Mullidae ( goatfish ) and includes the red mullets , occurring mainly in the southwest Atlantic near the South American coast and in the Eastern Atlantic including the Mediterranean and the Black Sea .
The Javan torrent frog ( Huia masonii ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Cabot 's tragopan ( Tragopan caboti ) is a pheasant found in south - east China .
The Beardslee trout ( Oncorhynchus mykiss irideus f. beardsleei ) , formerly Salmo gairdneri beardsleei ) is a local form of rainbow trout endemic to Lake Crescent in Washington .
The Fujian pond turtle ( `` Mauremys '' × iversoni ) is a possibly also naturally occurring intergeneric hybrid turtle in the Geoemydidae family ( formerly Bataguridae ) produced in larger numbers by Chinese turtle farms as a `` copy '' of the golden coin turtle Cuora trifasciata .
Srimara planicollis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Srimara .
Lamberticeras is an extinct ammonite genus belonging to the family Cardioceratidae .
Rhopalobrachium was a genus of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family but is no longer recognized .
The Centriscidae are a family of fishes from the order Syngnathiformes which includes the snipefishes , shrimpfishes , and bellowfishes .
Rhizothera is a genus of bird in the Phasianidae family , native to Malaysia .
The Magela hardyhead or Mariana 's Hardyhead ( Craterocephalus marianae ) is a species of fish in the Atherinidae family endemic to Australia .
The Central Kashmir vole ( Alticola montosa ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Cape May warbler ( Setophaga tigrina ) is a species of New World warbler .
Brachycerus is a genus of Curculionidae family , Brachycerinae subfamily .
Austrolestes is a genus of medium to large - sized damselflies in the family Lestidae .
Cryptorites scotti is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Cryptorites .
The Scree skink , Oligosoma waimatense , is a species of skink native to several sites throughout the South Island of New Zealand .
The Texas rat snake ( Elaphe obsoleta lindheimeri ) is a subspecies of rat snake , a nonvenomous colubrid found in the United States , primarily within the state of Texas , but its range extends into Louisiana , Arkansas and Oklahoma .
The order Peramelemorphia includes the bandicoots and bilbies : it equates approximately to the mainstream of marsupial omnivores .
Some authorities place the subfamily Arvicolinae in the family Muridae along with all other members of the superfamily Muroidea .
Lymanopoda is a butterfly genus from the subfamily Satyrinae in the family Nymphalidae found in north - western South America .
Bryophyllum ( from the Greek βρῦον/βρύειν bryon / bryein = sprout , φύλλον phyllon = leaf ) is a plant genus of the Crassulaceae family that has sometimes been included within the genus Kalanchoe .
Despite its many similarities to turtles , Eunotosaurus has a skull that shares many characteristics with the skulls of more primitive reptiles , resulting in many studies placing it in the extinct group Parareptilia .
The pleasing lacewings , Dilaridae , are a family of winged insects of the order Neuroptera .
Etroplus canarensis , the Canara pearlspot or banded chromide , is a species of cichlid endemic to South Karnataka in India .

Blitum is a flowering plant genus from the subfamily Chenopodioideae in the Amaranthaceae family .
The New Zealand greater short - tailed bat ( Mystacina robusta ) was one of two species of New Zealand short - tailed bats , a family ( Mystacinidae ) unique to New Zealand .

Ischnagonum carinigerum is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Ischnagonum .
Peringia is a genus of very small snails with gills and an operculum , gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Lasius californicus is a species of ant belonging to the genus Lasius , and was formerly apart of the genus Acanthomyops ( now a subgenus ) .
Spergularia is a genus in the Caryophyllaceae family , containing plants known as sandspurrys and sea - spurreys .
Bocage 's mole - rat ( Fukomys bocagei ) is a species of rodent in the family Bathyergidae .
Avitomyrmex is an extinct genus of bulldog ants in the subfamily Myrmeciinae which contains three described species .
Mucronea is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae with two species restricted to California .
Sander volgensis , the Volga pikeperch or Volga zander , is a species of fish in the perch family Percidae .
Furcifer polleni , also known as the Mayotte chameleon , is a species of chameleon that is endemic to Mayotte in the Comoros Islands .
The Biak glider ( Petaurus biacensis ) is a species of marsupial in the family Petauridae .
Pycnotheca is a genus of hydroids in the family Kirchenpaueriidae .
Zeodera atra is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Zeodera .
Leuciscus is a genus of fish belonging to the family Cyprinidae .
Africanogyrus is a genus of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Cassinia is a large genus of plants in the family Asteraceae , most or all of which are native to the Southern Hemisphere .
Graphoderus is a genus of beetle in family Dytiscidae native to the Palearctic , including Europe , and the Near East .
The Livingstone 's turaco ( Tauraco livingstonii ) is a species of bird in the Musophagidae family , which was named for Charles Livingstone , the brother of David Livingstone .
Lyogyrus is a genus of very small freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
The Mucoraceae are a family of fungi of the order Mucorales , characterized by having the thallus not segmented or ramified .
The Japanese spurdog , Squalus japonicus , is a dogfish , a member of the family Squalidae .
The Sierra de las Minas hidden salamander ( Cryptotriton sierraminensis ) is one of seven species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Scleria is a genus of flowering plants in the sedge family , Cyperaceae .
The Lufira masked weaver ( Ploceus ruweti ) , also known as Ruwet 's masked weaver and Lake Lufira weaver , is a species of bird in the weaver family , Ploceidae .
Trichophthalmus is a genus of beetles which belong to the family Belidae .

Holmgrenanthe petrophila ( rocklady , formerly Maurandya petrophila ) is a rare perennial desert plant in the plantain family ( Plantaginaceae ) , and the sole species of the genus Holmgrenanthe .

Archegosaurus is a member of Archegosauridae and gives its name to the family .
Kalaharituber is a genus of fungi within the Pezizaceae family .
Eremoceras is a genus in the Ellesmeroceratidae which lived during the Early Ordovician , characterized by an orthoconic adult stage , similar to Ellesmeroceras , but with the dorsal side of the adult living chamber somewhat convex , and a juvenile portion that is more gradually expanding and ventrally concave .
The Huon astrapia ( Astrapia rothschildi ) is a species of bird - of - paradise .
The Sulawesi blue flycatcher ( Cyornis omissus ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .

Crossley 's ground thrush ( Geokichla crossleyi ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
Conioselinum is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae family , native to Eurasia and North America .
The Bornean bristlehead ( Pityriasis gymnocephala ) , also variously known as the bristled shrike , bald - headed crow or the bald - headed wood - shrike , is the only member of the passerine family Pityriaseidae and genus Pityriasis .

Walvisteuthis is the only squid genus in the family Walvisteuthidae , consisting of a single species , Walvisteuthis virilis .

The Australian marbled catshark , Atelomycterus macleayi , is a catshark of the family Scyliorhinidae , found in the eastern Indian Ocean , endemic to Western Australia between latitudes 12 ° S and 21 ° S , from the surface to 245 m ( 800 ft ) .
Toronia is a genus of tree in the family Proteaceae that contains a single species , Toronia toru , which is found in New Zealand .

Oligochaeta ( /ˌɒlɪɡəˈkiːtə , -ɡoʊ-/ ) is a class of animals in the phylum Annelida , which is made up of many types of aquatic and terrestrial worms , and including all of the various earthworms .

Badister is a genus of ground beetle in the Carabidae family native to North Africa , the Near East and the Palearctic , including Europe .
Glossogobius hoesei , Hoese 's goby , is a species of goby endemic to the Ayamaru Lakes in West Papua , Indonesia where it can be found on muddy or gravel substrates as well as in small tributary streams .

Abalistes is a small triggerfish genus found in the Indo - Pacific and eastern Atlantic .
Actinoceras is the principal and root genus of the Actinoceratidae , a major family in the Actinocerida , that lived during the Middle and Late Ordovician .
The Abrostolini are a small tribe of moths in the Plusiinae subfamily , consisting of the genera Abrostola and Mouralia .
The Capparaceae ( or Capparidaceae ) , commonly known as the caper family , are a family of plants in the order Brassicales .
The Golden grey mullet ( Liza aurata ) is a fish in the family Mugilidae .
Proteocephalidae is a family of tapeworms in the Proteocephalidea order .
Enneapterygius rhothion , known commonly as the Surf triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Alaska plaice ( Pleuronectes quadrituberculatus ) is a saltwater fish that live in the North Pacific Ocean .
Pileostegia is a genus of 4 species of flowering plants in the family Hydrangeaceae , native to India and eastern Asia .
GB virus C ( GBV - C ) , formerly known as hepatitis G virus ( HGV ) and also known as HPgV is a virus in the Flaviviridae family and a member of the Pegivirus genus , is known to infect humans , but is not known to cause human disease .
Jelinekia barri is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Jelinekia .
Screech owls or screech - owls are typical owls ( Strigidae ) belonging to the genus Megascops .
